column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51852_ShortDesc", "An unadorned axe of iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51852_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Traders had come, and priests of Mitra who walked with bare feet and empty hands, and died horribly, most of them; but soldiers had followed, men with axes in their hands and women and children in ox-drawn wains.</> - Beyond the Black River

This axe could have been crafted at any smithy the length of Hyboria.
Axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes. This axe does not bear any markers of origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51853_ShortDesc", "A tooth-edged sword of bone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51853_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">With an awful shriek the witch sank down, writhing in convulsions, grasping at the naked blade as it was withdrawn, smoking and dripping.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nA mark of the Darfari wish to emulate more advanced cultures, this \"sword\" is more like a flat plank embedded with the teeth of various animals. It swings like a plank as well, so while it may not have the lethality of a well whetted blade, it will still leave a nasty mark on anything it managed to hit.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51854_ShortDesc", "A rudimentary axe created from a jawbone bound to a stout branch")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51854_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> On the heels of the shout came a clamor of blood-freezing screams, the shattering impact of axes on the gate.</> - The Black Stranger

Bladed weapons are generally frowned upon by the worshippers of Yog, but this jawbone is dull enough that it acts more like a club than a sword.
Yoggites believe that the consumption of human flesh gives them the Blessing of Yog for a period of time, which grants them invulnerability to normal weapons.

While Yog is considered a deity in Darfar, scholars in Hyboria classify him as a demon of the Elder night, referencing ancient documents that survived the drowning of Atlantis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51855_ShortDesc", "A macabre weapon of bone fused to rock")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51855_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He wondered how many poor devils had been bludgeoned in their sleep and dragged out of that room and down the road that ran through the shadowed palm groves to the roasting pit.</>  - Shadows in Zamboula

This sinister weapon is made of the bones of a human arm bound to a large fragment of stone. 

Cannibalism is more than a perverted appetite to the men of Darfar: it is an integral element of their cult. This cudgel is one of the ritual objects of the Yoggite religion. It is used to bludgeon human prey so that they can be carried to the sacrifice pit unblemished.

Bone is a brittle substance that breaks easily under even a small amount of force. Anything made of bone will fall apart quickly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51856_ShortDesc", "A macabre weapon of bone fused to rock")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51856_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He wondered how many poor devils had been bludgeoned in their sleep and dragged out of that room and down the road that ran through the shadowed palm groves to the roasting pit.</>  - Shadows in Zamboula

Cannibalism is more than a perverted appetite to the men of Darfar: it is an integral element of their cult. This cudgel is one of the ritual objects of the Yoggite religion. It is used to bludgeon human prey so that they can be carried to the sacrifice pit unblemished.

Bone is a brittle substance that breaks easily under even a small amount of force. Anything made of bone will fall apart quickly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51901_ShortDesc", "A hood of thick, dark material")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51901_LongDesc", "The Executioner was once a man but cursed by the gods to walk the dunes of the Exiled Lands until repentant. This never happened, and as the Executioner became more and more corrupted, he became less and less of a man, until the corruption was all that remained.\n\nThis hood has inlaid metal sheets, providing ample protection.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51902_ShortDesc", "A formal dagger used for ritualistic killings")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51902_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> She has instituted human sacrifice, and since her mating with Constantius, no less then five hundred men, women and children have been immolated. Some of these have died on the altar she has set up in the temple, herself wielding the sacrificial dagger, but most have met a more horrible doom. </> - A Witch Shall be Born

The devotees of Set are spread far and wide in the lands of Stygia and the Old Serpent demands human sacrifice as a part of his worship.

These daggers are crafted in the thousands at the forges of Luxur and then spread to the priesthood of the Serpent god.

While the rituals of Set are many and depraved, the fastest is bending a victim over an altar and cutting their heart from their chest.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51903_ShortDesc", "A robe of thick, dark material")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51903_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

They dress in black robes which serve to protect them against the searing heat of the volcano where they make their home.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51904_ShortDesc", "A hood of thick, dark material")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51904_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

This hood covers the head and conceals the face, allowing the wearer to proceed with dark deeds in complete anonymity.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51905_ShortDesc", "Handwraps made of a thick, dark material")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51905_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

These handwraps provide coverage against the warmth of the volcano, while allowing the hands to remain nimble enough to work the volcanic soil that clings to the caldera.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51906_ShortDesc", "A pair of thick leather sandals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51906_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

These sandals offer good grip on the rough stone that covers the inside of the volcano. While they are not designed to withstand the extremes of the lava flows that run along the volcano floor, they still provide some protection against the scorching heat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51907_ShortDesc", "A skirt of thick, dark material")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51907_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

This skirt is often worn by cultists who work the volcanic soil to grow crops. The additional mobility provided by the skirt is useful for those who spend their days bending and crouching.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51911_ShortDesc", "One-handed short spear that can be jabbed or thrown")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51911_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As they swept past the black mouth of a gorge that opened into the Pass, a javelin swished through the air and thudded home behind the stallion's straining shoulder.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Light weight enough to be wielded with a shield, the javelin is a common front line weapon in battles. 

Push, stab, push, stab is a motto of infantry the world over.

In addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51912_ShortDesc", "A light axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51912_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> And it was suspicious. It lifted its head, its eyes glowing like balls of fire, and growled low in its throat. And at that instant Conan hurled the axe. </> - Beyond the Black River

The Vanir raiders who plague the lands of the Cimmerians and Aesir often carry these light axes on their belts during their raids.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51922_ShortDesc", "A short spear of the Darfari style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51922_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Black men came up the river in long boats with skulls grinning on the prows, or stole stooping through the trees, spear in hand.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Adorned with feathers and tipped with flint, this short spear represents the pinnacle of Darfari weapons.

The Darfari use these spears for hunting game, first pinning their prey with well-aimed throws and then harassing their prey with swift, sharp stabs.

The feathers on the shaft are taken from the ferocious, but colourful, elephant birds that roam the grasslands on the very edges of Darfar.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51931_ShortDesc", "An ornate pike made in the Stygian style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51931_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The horde had formed into a huge wedge, of which the tip was the Stygians and the body, the mailed asshuri, flanked by the nomads. In close formation, shields lifted, they rolled onward, while behind them a tall figure in a motionless chariot lifted wide-robed arms in grisly invocation.</> - Black Colossus

The Stygian armies are famed for using chariots into battle. This frees their hands to use either the bow or the spear to great effect.

The Stygian spear is heavy, two handed, and bronze tipped. Wielded with the momentum of a charging chariot it is devastating to infantry and cavalry alike.

Stygian hunters use the broad bladed spears to hunt lions and rhinoceros on the rocky plains around the Styx river.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51932_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51932_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It wheeled at the thud of her soft boots on the floor, but even as it turned, her keen blade lashed down, and a fierce exultation swept her as she felt the edge cleave solid flesh and mortal bone.</> - Red Nails

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the head of this throwing axe and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51938_ShortDesc", "An axe forged from star metal and balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51938_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a queen by fire and steel and slaughter...</> - Queen of the Black Coast

This impossibly sharp throwing axe is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51941_ShortDesc", "An ancient greatsword marked in strange runes")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51941_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">You shall go down the dark road to Acheron, which is the road of silence and the night. The dark empire, unreborn, shall remain a legend and a black memory.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This greatsword, made from an ancient design, seems to suck away the warmth and daylight. A relic of the past, the shape of it calls up shadow-haunted memories of ape-gods squatting on shattered altars.
It whispers ceaselessly to its bearer and slowly, inevitably, tears their sanity apart.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51942_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers forged from an ancient design")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51942_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'It's too ancient to be holy. Who ever saw metal like it in a sane world?'</> - The God in the Bowl

These daggers are designed in imitation of a style long since faded into the mists of time.

Capable of cutting and dicing, slashing and slaying, daggers are for those who like to get in close and wreak havoc, then move to a safe distance while their foes bleed out.

Some warriors speak of the bloodlust that sweeps over them while using such weapons, an alien force that drives them to acts of great cruelty.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51943_ShortDesc", "A light axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51943_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> And it was suspicious. It lifted its head, its eyes glowing like balls of fire, and growled low in its throat. And at that instant Conan hurled the axe. </> - Beyond the Black River

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51947_ShortDesc", "A sword with an eye attached to it")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51947_LongDesc", "This sword was pillaged from the corpse of the Man on the Wall. It is a curious item that feels warm to the touch.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51950_ShortDesc", "A sword fashioned out of pure black ice and infused with blood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51950_LongDesc", "Infused with the blood of thousands of victims, this blade has been blessed by Tsathoggua.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51951_ShortDesc", "A pair of primitive stone-bladed knives")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51951_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Conan went with it, bruised, battered, invincible, hanging on like a bulldog to the hilt of his saber which he could not withdraw, tearing and ripping at the shuddering bulk with the poniard in his left hand, goring it to ribbons.</> - The Slithering Shadow

Sharpened stones serving as primitive daggers with limited ranged for fast, stabbing attacks.

Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Even the most primitive weapons can mean the difference between life and death for an Exile.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51952_ShortDesc", "A pair of vicious short-bladed knives")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51952_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As he went he fingered the poniard he had captured - a murderous weapon with a broad, double-edged blade nineteen inches long.</> - Rogues in the House

Crafted of iron, these poniards taper quickly to a sharp point that can be used to puncture holes in armor and flesh.

A thin groove in the center of the poniard can be filled with venom harvested from various creatures of the Exiled Lands. Venoms cause excruciating pain before death but are particularly effective for incapacitating large animals.

This poniard does not bear any markers of origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51953_ShortDesc", "A pair of sharp-bladed off-hand daggers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51953_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Conan did not reply; he merely stood and glared at her with his burning eyes, testing the edge of his poniard with a callused thumb.</> - Rogues in the House

While all poniards are capable of fast stabbing attacks with their venom coated blades, the extra strength of a steel poniard means that it can also be used to parry the attacks of enemies.

Using a poniard to parry requires more skill than a shield, but if successful such a parry will leave the enemy open for counter attack. Poniards are the off-hand weapon of choice in Zingaran duels for exactly this reason.")

column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51957_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers crafted from the eye of the Abysmal Remnant")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51957_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He saw and knew the ancient and evil serpent which swayed there, its wedge-shaped head, huge as that of a horse, as high as a tall man's head, and its palely gleaming barrel rippling out behind it. A forked tongue darted in and out, and the firelight glittered on bared fangs.</> - Beyond the Black River

As far as trophies go, these dagger are amongst the most bizarre. Made with the hypnotic eye of the Abysmal Remnant embedded in the blade, it has a fearsome aspect but does not seem to have any specific powers beyond that. 

Perhaps in time, certain powers will reveal themselves.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51958_ShortDesc", "A sword crafted from the eye of Abysmal Remnant")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51958_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He saw and knew the ancient and evil serpent which swayed there, its wedge-shaped head, huge as that of a horse, as high as a tall man's head, and its palely gleaming barrel rippling out behind it. A forked tongue darted in and out, and the firelight glittered on bared fangs.</> - Beyond the Black River

Staring long enough into the eye of the Abysmal Remnant, embedded in this sword, fills the mind with bizarre images.

Once, the Priestking made a pact with a demon from the outer void to inhabit some formed flesh that he was crafting. This was to be a weapon, used in the war against the human city in the north.

The experiment failed, the creature was born limbless and the experiment was abandoned. An acolyte of the Priestking tossed it into the sewer system, to drown in The Dregs.

But the creature did not die, and the demon was not freed. It found a pool where it could excrete the acid that it needed to survive. And then it reached out with its mind, looking for food.

Over time, it grew and the rats and other vermin in the sewers were no long enough to sustain it...")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51959_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers with a hardened steel blade of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51959_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He grunted with satisfaction. The feel of the hilt cheered him and gave him a glow of confidence. Whatever webs of conspiracy were drawn about him, whatever trickery and treachery ensnared him, this knife was real. The great muscles of his right arm swelled in anticipation of murderous blows.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These razor-sharp daggers are made of hardened steel and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.
This weapon has limited ranged for its fast, stabbing attacks. Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51961_ShortDesc", "A twisted rope strong enough to drag a captive a short distance")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51961_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">How long Conan lay senseless he never knew. His first sensation of returning consciousness was that of being dragged by one arm over rough and stony ground, and through dense underbrush. Then he was thrown carelessly down, and perhaps the jolt brought back his senses.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Ropes have dozens of uses, but the most common in the Exiled Lands is the binding and capture of slaves. Once an enemy is rendered unconscious, their ankles are bound with rope and they are dragged into captivity.

Ropes abrade on sharp stones and unravel often. The stronger the material of the rope, the further the captive can be dragged.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51962_ShortDesc", "Bindings strong enough to constrain a captive for a while")
column4:

NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51963_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">How long Conan lay senseless he never knew. His first sensation of returning consciousness was that of being dragged by one arm over rough and stony ground, and through dense underbrush. Then he was thrown carelessly down, and perhaps the jolt brought back his senses.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Ropes have dozens of uses, but the most common in the Exiled Lands is the binding and capture of slaves. Once an enemy is rendered unconscious, their ankles are bound with rope and they are dragged into captivity.

Ropes abrade on sharp stones and unravel often. The stronger the material of the rope, the further the captive can be dragged.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51964_ShortDesc", "Bindings strong enough to constrain a captive for a very long time")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51964_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">In one of these chariots lay Conan, king of Aquilonia, weighted with chains, the tang of defeat in his mouth, the blind fury of a trapped tiger in his soul.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Created of intricate links of iron and steel, this chain is strong enough to drag many times the weight of a man.

Chains have dozens of uses, but the most common in the Exiled Lands is the binding and capture of slaves. Once an enemy is rendered unconscious, their ankles are bound with chain and they are dragged into captivity.

Chains are vulnerable in their links which chip on stones and break occasionally. The stronger the chain links, the further the captive can be dragged.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51965_ShortDesc", "A rope made from the essence of the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51965_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">How long Conan lay senseless he never knew. His first sensation of returning consciousness was that of being dragged by one arm over rough and stony ground, and through dense underbrush. Then he was thrown carelessly down, and perhaps the jolt brought back his senses.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Ropes have dozens of uses, but the most common in the Exiled Lands is the binding and capture of slaves. Once an enemy is rendered unconscious, their ankles are bound with rope and they are dragged into captivity.

Ropes abrade on sharp stones and unravel often. This rope, however, will last for a very long time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51966_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers with a hardened steel blade of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51966_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He grunted with satisfaction. The feel of the hilt cheered him and gave him a glow of confidence. Whatever webs of conspiracy were drawn about him, whatever trickery and treachery ensnared him, this knife was real. The great muscles of his right arm swelled in anticipation of murderous blows.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These razor-sharp daggers are made of hardened steel and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.
This weapon has limited ranged for its fast, stabbing attacks. Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51967_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51967_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">When I was a fighting-man, the kettle-drums they beat; The people scattered gold-dust before my horse's feet; But now I am a great king, the people hound my track; With poison in my wine-cup, and daggers at my back.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

These impossibly sharp daggers are made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.
This weapon has limited ranged for its fast, stabbing attacks. Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51970_ShortDesc", "A sickle made in the Acheronian style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51970_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The blade glinted in the starlight, and blood spurted.</> - The Man-Eaters of Zamboula\n\nSickles are one-handed tools sporting a crescent-shaped blade. Made for harvesting crops, such a tool can just as easily sheer flesh and bone and reap a bloody bounty.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51971_ShortDesc", "A glass orb that shimmers with fire")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51971_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'His hand dipped into his robe and came out with something shining-a glistening sphere. This he threw suddenly at Conan. The Cimmerian contemptuously struck it aside with his sword-at the instant of contact there was a sharp explosion, a flare of white, blinding flame, and Conan pitched senseless to the ground.'</> - The Hour of the Dragon

While there are always rumors of sorcerers who summon fire from the skies and cause the earth to revolt against their foes, this orb is simply a concoction created from mixing fluids together.

To the credulous and superstitious, it appears to be sorcery. But to the educated it is simply an alchemical curiosity, able to set a burning fire on whatever surface it impacts.

It can also be used in combination with grease to create a larger fire effect.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51972_ShortDesc", "A glass orb filled with a greasy substance")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51972_LongDesc", "An orb filled with treated tar that leaves the tar slick and greasey. Upon application to a surface, this reduces friction and sudden changes of direction become impossible.\n\nThe grease can also be set alight by fire, or used to enhance the heat of a fire already burning.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51973_ShortDesc", "A glass orb filled with water")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51973_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'There is a crystal jar on that ivory table,\' he answered. \'Fill it with water and tie a strip of that torn hanging about its neck for a handle while I rip up this tapestry.\'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk\n\nThis is simply a glass flask filled with water. It can be used to douse fires and to settle particles from the air. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51974_ShortDesc", "A glass orb filled with green gas")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51974_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'With sudden suspicion he thrust his head over the threshold, into the bluish mist that filled the inner cavern. And he screamed, chokingly: 'There is death in the smoke!'</> - The Black Stranger

This orb, filled with the spores of the pufferball mushroom, explodes into a cloud of green mist when thrown.

While the spores of the mushroom are not as potent as the pollen of the lotus or dust from Stygian tombs, they still cause significant damage to those unlucky enough to inhale them.

When combined with water, the spores also form a thick viscous substance that acts like grease. When a cloud of spores is met with fire, the resulting explosion rocks the very heavens.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51975_ShortDesc", "A sword fashioned out of pure black ice")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51975_LongDesc", "The blade of this weapon is warm to the touch, despite it being made out of pure black ice. Beneath the shimmering surface of the blade, shadows seem to move.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51976_ShortDesc", "A broadsword fashioned out of pure black ice")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51976_LongDesc", "The blade of this weapon is warm to the touch, despite it being made out of pure black ice. Beneath the shimmering surface of the blade, shadows seem to move.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51977_ShortDesc", "A pickaxe fashioned out of pure black ice")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51977_LongDesc", "This pickaxe is warm to the touch, despite it being made out of pure black ice. Beneath the shimmering surface of the blade, shadows seem to move.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51978_ShortDesc", "A pickaxe made in the Acheronian style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51978_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I know him not,' he answered. 'He is mad to say I hired him. Let him take his just desserts. He has a strong back and the toil in the mines will be well for him.'</> - The God in the Bowl

The pick is one of the simplest tools known to man. Used extensively in mines across Hyboria to split rocks and, if necessary, split heads.
Created in the fires at the burning heart of the forge and wrought in ornate patterns as it cooled, this pick is strong and durable. It almost seems a shame to waste it on rocks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51979_ShortDesc", "A vicious sword made in the Acheronian style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51979_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> They stopped short. Conan faced them, not a naked man roused mazed and unarmed out of deep sleep to be butchered like a sheep, but a barbarian wide-awake and at bay, partly armored, and with his long sword in his hand.</>
The Phoenix on the Sword

Longsword has become a catch-all phrase for the mongrel swords of a thousand different makes that don't align easily with one simple classification.

This weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian style bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that once ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51982_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The horde had formed into a huge wedge, of which the tip was the Stygians and the body, the mailed asshuri, flanked by the nomads. In close formation, shields lifted, they rolled onward, while behind them a tall figure in a motionless chariot lifted wide-robed arms in grisly invocation.</> - Black Colossus\n\nThis weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian style bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that once ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51988_ShortDesc", "A shield made from an Acheronian design")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51988_LongDesc", "Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.\n\nThis shield is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian style bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that once ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51991_ShortDesc", "A shield made from an Acheronian design")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51991_LongDesc", "Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.

Through the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.

The sad reality of dragons was that they could not fly, they did not breathe fire or acid, and they were not particularly intelligent. They were simply gigantic predators that lived centuries ago.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51995_ShortDesc", "A formal headdress worn by Jhebbal Sag priests")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51995_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Balthus saw a lean figure of middle height, almost hidden in ostrich plumes set on a harness of leather and copper. From amidst the plumes peered a hideous and malevolent face. The plumes puzzled Balthus. He knew their source lay half the width of a world to the south. They fluttered and rustled evilly as the shaman leaped and cavorted.</> - Beyond the Black River

The worship of Jhebbal Sag has long been forgotten by the civilized Hyborians, but his priests in the Black Kingdoms and Pictish wilderness still spread his religion through fear and violence.

A large part of this is the ceremonial garb that priests don for their rituals. Ornate headdresses decorated with ostrich feathers are common - even among the Picts who trade for feathers with Zingaran pirates who carry them up from the south.

Despite offering no protection, the intimidation that comes from wearing such a headdress should not be underestimated.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51996_ShortDesc", "A headpiece worn by Acolytes of Derketo")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51996_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">That's what the black people of Kush call the Apples of Derketa. Derketa is the Queen of the Dead. Drink a little of that juice, or spill it on your flesh, and you'd be dead before you could tumble to the foot of this crag.</> - Red Nails

Derketo was originally worshipped in Shem, but was quickly adopted in Stygia and the Black Kingdoms further south.

The dual nature of Derketo is death and fertility, and as such she is often paired with the most powerful deity of the kingdom she is associated with. Derketo is the consort of Set in Stygia, but the companion of Dagon in Zembabwei. In Kush she is Derketa, Queen of the Dead, and there, she walks alone.

This ceremonial armor is designed to awe and seduce in equal measure.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52001_ShortDesc", "A simple turban of hide and fiber")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52001_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the fierce sun beating down on the unprotected head can cause extreme delirium in a short amount of time.
Apart from protection from the sun, this turban offers a small amount of protection from attacks on the head.
Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.
Created from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52002_ShortDesc", "A light chestpiece of hide and fiber")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52002_LongDesc", "Designed to keep the wearer cool, this armor emphasizes movement and agility in combat over straight up protection.\nThe blow that misses is always better than the one that lands. In this case, the one that lands will cause a significant amount of damage due to the simple construction of this armor.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52003_ShortDesc", "A pair of flexible hide gauntlets")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52003_LongDesc", "Hide pieces bound to a soft underbody of cloth keep these gauntlets as flexible as possible while offering some protection from attacks.\nBlows to the hand can cause crippling injuries, particularly to archers who need to have all of their fingers intact if they are to draw a bow.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52004_ShortDesc", "A loose fitting cloth wrap, bound to the waist with rawhide thongs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52004_LongDesc", "This wrap allows the legs to move freely, giving full range of motion. This is particularly useful to the adventurer just beginning their journey, as it allows them to make the all-important decision of fight or flight.\nLight armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52005_ShortDesc", "A pair of sturdy boots made from cloth and hide")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52005_LongDesc", "These boots of cloth wrapped and laced in hide, provide protection and warmth for the feet.\nThere are many dangers in the Exiled Lands and the small scorpions, spiders and snakes that can strike without warning are reason enough to keep legs and feet well covered.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52006_ShortDesc", "A robe of thick, dark material")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52006_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

They dress in black robes which serve to protect them against the searing heat of the volcano where they make their home.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52007_ShortDesc", "A hood of thick, dark material")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52007_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

This hood covers the head and conceals the face, allowing the wearer to proceed with dark deeds in complete anonymity.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52008_ShortDesc", "Handwraps made of a thick, dark material")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52008_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

These handwraps provide coverage against the warmth of the volcano, while allowing the hands to remain nimble enough to work the volcanic soil that clings to the caldera.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52009_ShortDesc", "A pair of thick leather sandals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52009_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

These sandals offer good grip on the rough stone that covers the inside of the volcano. While they are not designed to withstand the extremes of the lava flows that run along the volcano floor, they still provide some protection against the scorching heat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52010_ShortDesc", "A skirt of thick, dark material")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52010_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

This skirt is often worn by cultists who work the volcanic soil to grow crops. The additional mobility provided by the skirt is useful for those who spend their days bending and crouching.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52011_ShortDesc", "A riveted leather cap with a facemask")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52011_LongDesc", "This leather helmet includes large cheek  and neck protectors and a facemask for filtering the sand and dust from the air.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52012_ShortDesc", "Leather spaulders riveted to articulated rerebraces")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52012_LongDesc", "The fastest way to a man\'s heart, is through his armpits\' is a common expression amongst the gladiators of Argos. Every human is already born with some natural protection over their hearts namely their ribcage and breastbone.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52015_ShortDesc", "Calf-length riveted leather boots")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52016_ShortDesc", "A helmet made of thick reptile leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52016_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then for the first time humans appeared: dark-skinned, hawk-faced men in copper and leather harness, bearing bows - the warriors of pre-historic Stygia.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

The overlapping scales that offer natural protection to reptiles are an excellent source of protection for humans as well. The problem is that very few reptiles give up their skins willingly, and the most fearsome crocodiles are more than a match for a poorly armed hunter.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates a balance of protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

This style of armor is common in the Black Kingdoms.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52021_ShortDesc", "A horned steel helmet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52021_LongDesc", "This helmet, ornamented with a pair of horns, is designed to ward off powerful blows to the head and keep the wearer's brains on the inside of their skull.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52022_ShortDesc", "A heavy vest that offers significant protection")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52022_LongDesc", "Designed with defence in mind, this heavy pauldron is reinforced with overlapping steel plates on the main hand. This offers optimal protection and stability mid-swing, while allowing the wearer room to breathe and remain cool.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52023_ShortDesc", "Steel-plated gauntlets")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52023_LongDesc", "These gauntlets are adorned with overlapping plates of steel, which keeps the main hand protected while allowing full flexibility and mobility in the off-hand. 
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52024_ShortDesc", "A steel-plated skirt for protecting the upper thighs")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52024_LongDesc", "Sewn together with riveted leather and adjoined steel plates, this skirt allows free movement of the legs while in battle, while protecting the waist and upper thighs from damage.
The wide belt that encircles the waist also has the practical purpose of protecting vital organs with a thick layer of tempered metal.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52025_ShortDesc", "Steel-plated heavy-toed boots")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52025_LongDesc", "The upper sides of these boots are covered with a layer of steel to protect against any attacks made at that vulnerable area. The feet are often overlooked as an element of protection, but as King Namedides of Aquilonia once remarked "The enemy can't run without legs!".
His infantry were well known across the world for removing the largest toes of any prisoners of war 
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52046_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52046_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52047_ShortDesc", "An ornate necklace of teeth over human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52047_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
This chestpiece is soft and supple, which allows for great flexibility. The teeth used in the necklace appear to be crocodile teeth, taken from the great beasts that roam the Exiled Lands.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52048_ShortDesc", "Bracers of blood-dyed leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52048_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These bracers are the color of blood and made of a soft leather wrapped with cloth. A close look reveals human molars dangling from the bindings on the gauntlets.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52061_ShortDesc", "A headdress popular among Stygian nobility")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52061_LongDesc", "It is rumoured that the noble class that rules Stygia are the results of intermingling between the ancient, pre-human race that ruled Stygia and the savage humans who overthrew them. Occasionally, there are throwbacks to this ancient bloodline born among the nobles, and these half-human creatures are forced into service in the temples of Set, kept beneath the earth and away from prying eyes.

The fashions and designs of Stygia are unique amongst the races, again a side-effect of human culture crossed over with something alien.

This clothing is the type that would be worn by Stygian nobles to a feast, a festival or an orgy.")

The feet are often overlooked as an element of protection, but as King Namedides of Aquilonia once remarked "The enemy can't run without legs!".
His infantry were well known across the world for removing the largest toes of any prisoners of war 
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52071_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52071_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52072_ShortDesc", "An ornate necklace of teeth over human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52072_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
This chestpiece is soft and supple, which allows for great flexibility. The teeth used in the necklace appear to be crocodile teeth, taken from the great beasts that roam the Exiled Lands.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52073_ShortDesc", "Bracers of blood-dyed leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52073_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These bracers are the color of blood and made of a soft leather wrapped with cloth. A close look reveals human molars dangling from the bindings on the gauntlets.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52076_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52076_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the speaker mask is said to allow the wearer to communicate with the dead.\nDarfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.\nBut in the southern deserts, darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can command the dead and communicate with Yog directly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52080_ShortDesc", "For strong necks only")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52080_LongDesc", "Many a bearer have met their untimely demise by not having their hands free. One could argue that this contraption is not an improvement, since just as many have snapped their necks by simply moving their heads too quickly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52081_ShortDesc", "A mask that filters out the sandstorm debris")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52081_LongDesc", "When the sandstorm wails across the Exiled Lands, the choices are to take cover from the scouring sands, or be blinded and eventually, killed.
This breather mask, crafted with very small slits for the eyes that keep out most of the debris while allowing visibility and a cloth mouthpiece that filters the air, allows free movement within the sandstorm.
What lies at the heart of the storm is one of the many mysteries of the Exiled Lands.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52092_ShortDesc", "A simple cloth binding that protects the upper body")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52092_LongDesc", "A cloth binding that has been wound around the upper body to keep everything in its place.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52094_ShortDesc", "A simple cloth wrapping that protects the groin")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52094_LongDesc", "A cloth binding that winds between the legs to keep everything in its place.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52100_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by the Witch Queen of Lemuria")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52100_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Many Lemurians escaped to the eastern coast of the Thurian Continent, which was comparatively untouched. There they were enslaved by the ancient race which already dwelt there, and their history, for thousands of years, is a history of brutal servitude.</> - The Hyborian Age

This mask was used by the Witch Queens of Lemuria to communicate with their primary deity, Dagon, before their kingdom sank into the ocean during the cataclysm.

When the Lemurians crossed into the land of the Giant-kings, they negotiated for somewhere to settle. The Witch Queen, weary of the forced exile of her people, helped the Giant-kings to forge the bracelets, originally to facilitate communication between the two races.

Later, this mask possessed the exile Razma, controlling her thoughts and forcing her to start rebuilding the palace at the heart of Xel-ha.
This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52101_ShortDesc", "A headress favored by Zamorian temple dancers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52101_LongDesc", "Zamorians are known far and wide for the depth of their wickedness and thievery, but very few speak of the prowess of the temple dancers.
It is whispered that the temple girls of Yezud wear clothing such as this when they dance before the black stone spider that is their god.

For ceremonial usage, this headdress offers very little protection against sword or fang, but offers slight relief from cold, heat and stinging sand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52102_ShortDesc", "A blouse favored by Zamorian temple dancers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52102_LongDesc", "Zamorians are known far and wide for the depth of their wickedness and thievery, but very few speak of the prowess of the temple dancers.
The steps of the dance are unknown, but it is clear that it eases the black madness that whispers to those who find themselves in the vicinity of the awful presence of Zath, spider-god of Yezud.

For ceremonial usage, this blouse offers very little protection against sword or fang, but offers slight relief from cold, heat and stinging sand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52111_ShortDesc", "A headdress worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52111_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Trained in the temples of Luxur, the dancers of Derketo are renowned for their skill in the arts of pleasure. Thought the more stringent of the Setite priests frown upon the religion of the goddess, the wisest among them know that the deity represents the dual aspects of fertility and death.

In Stygia this manifests in the bizarre pairing of the dancers and the ritualistic killings of the cult of Set.

This headdress signifies the status of the wearer as a dancer in the service of Derketo.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52112_ShortDesc", "A blouse worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52112_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Trained in the temples of Luxur, the dancers of Derketo are renowned for their skill in the arts of pleasure. Thought the more stringent of the Setite priests frown upon the religion of the goddess, the wisest among them know that the deity represents the dual aspects of fertility and death.

In Stygia this manifests in the bizarre pairing of the dancers and the ritualistic killings of the cult of Set.

This loose-fitting blouse is designed to accentuate rather than conceal, to titillate rather than reveal. Dancers of Derketo are aware that lust, like fear, is one of the most powerful motivators of human kind.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52113_ShortDesc", "Bracelets worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52113_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

These bracelets jingle with every movement of the wearer - every provocative chest shake and sinuous coil of the wrist produces a golden note.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52114_ShortDesc", "A skirt worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52114_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Trained in the temples of Luxur, the dancers of Derketo are renowned for their skill in the arts of pleasure. Thought the more stringent of the Setite priests frown upon the religion of the goddess, the wisest among them know that the deity represents the dual aspects of fertility and death.

In Stygia this manifests in the bizarre pairing of the dancers and the ritualistic killings of the cult of Set.

Half-transparent, this skirt presents those who watch the dancers of Derketo with shadowy outlines of the flesh that lies beneath. A stirring in the blood that sets the heart to racing - and matches the step of the dancers in full flight.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52202_ShortDesc", "A tunic woven from fibrous plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52202_LongDesc", "When the sand whips and swirls in the wind, abrading everything in its path, even the smallest amount of protection is appreciated.\nThis tunic provides little protection from sword or fang, but it does provide slight relief from cold, heat and stinging sand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52203_ShortDesc", "Handwraps woven from fibrous plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52203_LongDesc", "Digging in the gritty soil of the Exiled Lands and tearing up plants by their roots without protection is dirty, infection-prone work. \nThese handwraps provide some protection from the elements and physical attacks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52204_ShortDesc", "Leggings woven from fibrous plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52204_LongDesc", "In the Hyborian age, nudity is a part of life. In warm climates, men and women go bare chested and wear flimsy clothing, slaves are clothed in whatever tatters they can find and children run naked in the streets.\nClothing, however, is a practical bulwark against the elements. And these leggings, coarse as they may be, can protect some very sensitive areas from the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52205_ShortDesc", "Footwraps woven from fibrous plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52205_LongDesc", "The soles of these footwraps offer very poor protection from the sharp-edged stones that litter the ground of the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52212_ShortDesc", "A leather apron for smithing")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52212_LongDesc", "Across the Hyborian kingdoms and beyond, in every village in every province, the smith is a necessity in daily life. From blades to ploughsnares, blacksmiths craft the tools and weapons to feed and arm the population.\nIn every village or town, the Blacksmith is recognized by their uniform - this simple leather apron. Offering protection from errant sparks and pockets for storing small tools, this apron is as much a badge of craft as the smiths hammer or the forge itself.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52213_ShortDesc", "Thick leather gloves offering crafting protection")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52213_LongDesc", "These gloves are made of thick leather molded over a padded inside. Made to protect the hands from damage while working with dangerous crafting elements, they offer a small amount of protection in combat.\nAs a secondary usage, the heavy gloves can be donned and worn during brawls to avoid damaging the hands in combat.\nOne famous sailor, known only as Dorgan of the Python, makes a large sum of gold by fighting his way across the Vilayet sea and betting on his own fights. He claims that the gloves keep his prize possessions safe.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52221_ShortDesc", "Shemitish turban commonly worn in the meadowland cities")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52221_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. Due to their access to these caravans, the Shemitish people often have access to the first pick of goods coming from the east - including fine silks from Khitai and brightly dyed cloth from Turan. This bounty of cloth is reflected in the loose fitting, comfortable clothing woven by the tailors of Shem.\nThis clothing is a practical bulwark against the elements but won\'t be enough to stop a blade.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52222_ShortDesc", "Shemitish tunic commonly worn in the meadowland cities")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52222_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52225_ShortDesc", "Shemitish pointy-toed shoes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52225_LongDesc", "While these shoes are impractical for the desert, they are incredibly comfortable.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52226_ShortDesc", "A pair of Shemitish gloves")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52226_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. Due to their access to these caravans, the Shemitish people often have access to the first pick of goods coming from the east - including fine silks from Khitai and brightly dyed cloth from Turan. column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52293_ShortDesc", "Rough gloves suited for climbing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52293_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">His groping hands and feet found niches and knobs, precarious holds at best, and sometimes he virtually hung by his finger nails. Yet upward he went, clawing, squirming, fighting for every foot.</> - Jewels of Gwahlur

As civilization sweeps across the barbaric nations of the world it brings comfort, security and occasionally, peace. But in such times, men forget the skills that they once had.

The ability to climb, for example, to find purchase on the steepest slopes and cling by the fingernails to the smallest of outcrops. To traverse the world using no more than the power of muscle and grit.

The barbaric Cimmerians and tribes of Afghul are known among the civilized nations for their near miraculous climbing ability. As any inhabitant of the Exiled Lands will tell you, there is no miracle here. Just the iron will to survive.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52295_ShortDesc", "Studded boots for climbing")
column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52301_ShortDesc", "A simple turban of hide and fiber")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52301_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the fierce sun beating down on the unprotected head can cause extreme delirium in a short amount of time.
Apart from protection from the sun, this turban offers a small amount of protection from attacks on the head.
Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.
Created from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52302_ShortDesc", "A light chestpiece of hide and fiber")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52302_LongDesc", "Designed to keep the wearer cool, this armor emphasizes movement and agility in combat over straight up protection.\nThe blow that misses is always better than the one that lands. In this case, the one that lands will cause a significant amount of damage due to the simple construction of this armor.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52303_ShortDesc", "A pair of flexible hide gauntlets")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52303_LongDesc", "Hide pieces bound to a soft underbody of cloth keep these gauntlets as flexible as possible while offering some protection from attacks.\nBlows to the hand can cause crippling injuries, particularly to archers who need to have all of their fingers intact if they are to draw a bow.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52304_ShortDesc", "A loose fitting cloth wrap, bound to the waist with rawhide thongs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52304_LongDesc", "This wrap allows the legs to move freely, giving full range of motion. This is particularly useful to the adventurer just beginning their journey, as it allows them to make the all-important decision of fight or flight.\nLight armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52305_ShortDesc", "A pair of sturdy boots made from cloth and hide")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52305_LongDesc", "These boots of cloth wrapped and laced in hide, provide protection and warmth for the feet.\nThere are many dangers in the Exiled Lands and the small scorpions, spiders and snakes that can strike without warning are reason enough to keep legs and feet well covered.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52306_ShortDesc", "The formal helm of a Stygian officer")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52306_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

This ornamented helm is commonly worn by officers of higher rank to make them more easily recognizable on the battlefield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52307_ShortDesc", "A shirt of Stygian scale mail")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52307_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

Scale mail used to be reserved for the nobility, but as the kingdoms surrounding Stygia began to use more sophisticated weaponry, it was decided that the Stygian soldiers required more protection. Now scale mail has become the standard.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52308_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Stygian soldiers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52308_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

These bronze bracers protect the lower arm in the clash of shields, while allowing the wearer the flexibility of wrist and hand to thrust into the gaps above and below the shield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52310_ShortDesc", "Sandals worn by Stygian soldiers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52310_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

The Stygian pike men are sometimes called hoppers by their enemies. Their insistence in wearing open soled sandals into battle means that in the clash of shield walls, enemies will often target their feet.

Stygian officers, however, consider this a boon as an enemy focused on looking down is less likely to see the pike that pierces their helmet.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

This ornamented helm is commonly worn by officers of higher rank to make them more easily recognizable on the battlefield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")
