column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52401_ShortDesc", "A simple turban of hide and fiber")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52401_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the fierce sun beating down on the unprotected head can cause extreme delirium in a short amount of time.
Apart from protection from the sun, this turban offers a small amount of protection from attacks on the head.
Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.
Created from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52402_ShortDesc", "A light chestpiece of hide and fiber")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52402_LongDesc", "Designed to keep the wearer cool, this armor emphasizes movement and agility in combat over straight up protection.\nThe blow that misses is always better than the one that lands. In this case, the one that lands will cause a significant amount of damage due to the simple construction of this armor.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52403_ShortDesc", "A pair of flexible hide gauntlets")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52403_LongDesc", "Hide pieces bound to a soft underbody of cloth keep these gauntlets as flexible as possible while offering some protection from attacks.\nBlows to the hand can cause crippling injuries, particularly to archers who need to have all of their fingers intact if they are to draw a bow.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52404_ShortDesc", "A loose fitting cloth wrap, bound to the waist with rawhide thongs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52404_LongDesc", "This wrap allows the legs to move freely, giving full range of motion. This is particularly useful to the adventurer just beginning their journey, as it allows them to make the all-important decision of fight or flight.\nLight armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52405_ShortDesc", "A pair of sturdy boots made from cloth and hide")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52405_LongDesc", "These boots of cloth wrapped and laced in hide, provide protection and warmth for the feet.\nThere are many dangers in the Exiled Lands and the small scorpions, spiders and snakes that can strike without warning are reason enough to keep legs and feet well covered.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52406_ShortDesc", "A helm commonly worn by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52406_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">About them and among them, like the drift of a storm, were strewn slashed and trampled bodies in steel caps and leather jerkins - archers and pikemen.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This leather helm provides significant protection against blows to the head.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52407_ShortDesc", "A chest piece favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52407_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This style of armor was reportedly created by a band of raiders who call themselves the Wolves of the Steppes. Led by the fearsome, Bhangi Khan, they have often been spotted on raids deep in the eastern empire of Khitai.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52408_ShortDesc", "Leather gauntlets favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52408_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

These leather gloves protect the hands in battle, while offering enough flexibility for shooting the horse-bows of the Hyrkania.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52421_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52421_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

Perhaps this is why the raiders wear masks such as this. To keep their identity hidden.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52422_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52422_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

This chestpiece offers excellent protection for the neck, shoulders and belly, while still being open enough to keep the wearer cool in the hot deserts of Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52423_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4:

These bracers protect the forearm and can be used to deflect superficial blows, thus keeping the wearer swinging and fighting just a little longer.")

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

These bracers protect the forearm and can be used to deflect superficial blows, thus keeping the wearer swinging and fighting just a little longer.")

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

These greaves protect the front of the legs from attack, while remaining open at the rear to keep the wearer cool in the scorching Stygian sun.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52436_ShortDesc", "A horned helm worn by the Shamans of Kambuja")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52436_LongDesc", "The jungle-locked kingdom of Kambuja is mysterious to the inhabitants of the dreaming west. Unlike neighboring Vendhya, the locals do not welcome foreign trade and it is said that any merchant who sets themselves on the paths that lead into the jungle will never return.

This armor, then, is a rarity, made from a half-remembered glimpse of a Kambujan Shaman captured by the Vendhyans and put on display in the nations of the west.

The helm is more intimidating than protective, modelled on the blasphemous shapes of a heinous demonic entity. Known as Tim.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52451_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52451_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThe mask can be used to hide the face of the wearer, as they plunder an enemy in the open ocean.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52452_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52452_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThe chestpiece is designed to allow freedom of movement for swimming. It\'s not as light as some other armors, but it is not going to drag a warrior down into the depths. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52453_ShortDesc", "Gauntlets worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52453_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThese gauntlets are designed to protect the hands and lower arms, but the hands are freed to take up the work of the sailor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52454_ShortDesc", "A tasset worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52454_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.

This tasset is designed to be quickly kicked off if a warrior falls into water, freeing the warrior from its protection and weight before they are sucked into the depths.

The metal discs sewn on to this garment depict Dagon, the god of the Lemurians.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52455_ShortDesc", "Boots worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52455_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThese boots protect the lower part of the leg and foot, while offering a simple mechanism for quick release in the event that the warrior needs to be barefoot in a hurry.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52466_ShortDesc", "Ornate jewelry designed for Lemurian royalty")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52466_LongDesc", "The rulers of ancient Lemuria were, without exception, women. They worshipped Dagon and any male heirs to the throne were given in sacrifice to the Demon of the Depths.\n\nThe royal garments are therefore designed to be worn by their Witch Queens. Which explains their femininity, if not exactly why some men insist on wearing them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52467_ShortDesc", "An ornate gown designed for Lemurian royalty")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52467_LongDesc", "The rulers of ancient Lemuria were, without exception, women. They worshipped Dagon and any male heirs to the throne were given in sacrifice to the Demon of the Depths.

The royal garments are therefore designed to be worn by their Witch Queens. Which explains their femininity, if not exactly why some men insist on wearing them.

It is clear that the designers of the royal Lemurian clothing were also responsible for the design of the bracelet that imprisons people in the Exiled Lands. Another mystery.")

They worshipped Dagon and any male heirs to the throne were given in sacrifice to the Demon of the Depths.\n\nThe royal garments are therefore designed to be worn by their Witch Queens. Which explains their femininity, if not exactly why some men insist on wearing them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52494_ShortDesc", "A replacement prosthetic for a hand")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52494_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\n\nWho needs dual-wielding anyway?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52495_ShortDesc", "A wooden prosthetic leg")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52495_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\n\nSomehow, this peg leg allows the temporary removal of your own - where it is stored is anyones guess.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52496_ShortDesc", "A pair of earrings worn by buccaneers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52496_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\n\nThese earrings are crude, cobbled together from base metals. But among pirates, keeping up a certain appearance is all the matters. Like the Black Hand, however, it seems to work.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52499_ShortDesc", "A heavily stitched pair of boots")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52499_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.

These boots are a reflection of their attitude, a patchwork of sloppy stitching and flung together pieces. Like the Black Hand, however, it seems to work.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements that balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52500_ShortDesc", "A crudely-fashioned eye patch")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52500_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52501_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by devotees of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52501_LongDesc", "The dispassionate features of the serpent have been modeled and refined in this mask. It distorts the features of the wearer and brings them closer to the cold beauty of the serpents so beloved of their god.\nUsed primarily in rituals within the temple of Set, this mask nevertheless offers a certain level of protection for the face of the wearer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52502_ShortDesc", "A choker worn by devotees of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52502_LongDesc", "Crafted from the finest golds, this garment is light and supple. It molds pleasingly to the form and accentuates the chest. The mysteries of Set are not all blood and death - the ritual that depicts the coupling of Set with his mistress, Derketo, has been described by Mitrean scholars as \"a blasphemous orgy of wine and blood.\" Though they always take the opportunity to vist any temple of Derketo during such rites. For the purposes of research, of course.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52504_ShortDesc", "A shendyt worn by devotees of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52504_LongDesc", "Woven silk edged with golden trim has been used to shape this ornamental shendyt. Worn by devotees of Set during their rituals, these shendyts are often stained in the blood of sacrifice.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52505_ShortDesc", "A pair of sandals worn by devotees of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52505_LongDesc", "These ceremonial sandals were not designed for the harsh environment of the desert, but rather the stone floors of the temple. Runnng in sand wearing these is an uncomfortable experience and fighting in them is almost impossible due to poor balance.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52509_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Yoggite warriors")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52509_LongDesc", "Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, Darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52510_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Yoggite warriors")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52510_LongDesc", "Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, Darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52511_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Yoggite shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52511_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, Darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52512_ShortDesc", "An ornate necklace of teeth over human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52512_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
This chestpiece is soft and supple, which allows for great flexibility. The teeth used in the necklace appear to be crocodile teeth, taken from the great beasts that roam the Exiled Lands.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52513_ShortDesc", "Bracers of blood-dyed leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52513_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These bracers are the color of blood and made of a soft leather wrapped with cloth. A close look reveals human molars dangling from the bindings on the gauntlets.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52514_ShortDesc", "Skirt of human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52514_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These skirt is simple and adorned with a belt of small beads and human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52515_ShortDesc", "Ankle wraps of soft leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52515_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These leather wraps, generously called greaves, are supple leather adorned with human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52516_ShortDesc", "A helmet crafted from the skull of Hyena")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52516_LongDesc", "The Dogs of the Desert are a mysterious clan who inhabit the northern reaches of the desert. Their obsession with capturing and taming Hyenas and their fanatical worship of the god known as Jhebbal Sag keeps them aloof from the other factions in the region.\nThe fact that they wear uncured furs and unclean bones probably doesn\'t help.\nSome might question wearing fur in the warmth of the desert, but nights can be brutally cold and the slopes of the mountain are not that far to the north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52522_ShortDesc", "A simple tunic")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52522_LongDesc", "Followers of Mitra commit to a life of simplicty and dignity. They prefer knowledge to ritual and the calm of meditation to the storm of battle.\nThis tunic reflects the simple principles of the Mitraen devout.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52526_ShortDesc", "A turban designed to protect the head from the elements")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52526_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

This turban has been refined in the time that they have spent in the Exiled Lands, offering comfort against the warm weather of the region and limited protection against the scouring sands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52527_ShortDesc", "A loose shirt favoured by relic hunters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52527_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

Still scavengers at heart, this shirt is paired with a small leather sack for storing any treasure that a relic hunter might stumble across while exploring the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52528_ShortDesc", "A set of sturdy gloves for handling relics")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52528_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

Too many foolish souls have lost life, limb and sanity to the effects of handling the relics of the ancient world. These gloves were created with to deal with that specific problem of adventuring.

Sturdy enough to protect the wrists and hands against hidden needles or snakebites, durable enough to protect the skin against corrosive magics and sudden fires and comfortable enough to wear while jamming a hand into a sarcophagus.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52529_ShortDesc", "Practical canvas pants for exploring")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52529_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

These pants, made of sturdy canvas, will keep the legs protected against stinging sands while allowing full freedom to leap over traps, canyons and short enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52530_ShortDesc", "A set of boots design for exploring ruins")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52530_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

When the Relic Hunters first arrived in the Exiled Lands, they were given sandals and flat-soled shoes. It is not known how many Relic Hunters died with their toes wedged into a gap between flagstones while an ancient horror bore down upon their prone body.

Since those early days, the Relic Hunters have moved to a style of boot favoured in Shem - curled toes to avoid catching on cracks when sprinting, supple leather to allow maximum freedom of movement and high cuffs to tuck into pants and prevent the accumulation of sand.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52532_ShortDesc", "A patchwork vest of leather, rope and cloth")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52532_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.

This garment, favored by the sailors of the Black Hand looks as though it has been mended so many times that none of the original material is left. Still due to the age of the garment and the many layers it exhibits more durability than it's frail appearance would indicate. 

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements that balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column4:

Their obsession with capturing and taming Hyenas and their fanatical worship of the god known as Jhebbal Sag keeps them aloof from the other factions in the region.\nThe fact that they wear uncured furs and unclean bones probably doesn\'t help.\nSome might question wearing fur in the warmth of the desert, but nights can be brutally cold and the slopes of the mountain are not that far to the north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52556_ShortDesc", "A helmet forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52556_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Free my hands and I'll varnish this floor with your brains!</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This heavy helmet is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52557_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52557_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then, as the white stars glimmered through the blue velvet dusk, making her whirling body a blur of ivory fire, with a wild cry she threw herself at Conan's feet, and the blind flood of the Cimmerian's desire swept all else away as he crushed her panting form against the black plates of his corseleted breast.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

This impossibly hard pauldron is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column4:

column4:

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52561_ShortDesc", "A helmet of hardened steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52561_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The plain swam to Conan's gaze, the sunlight was a thick red haze and he reeled in his saddle, grasping the flowing mane with his hand. Blood rained on his mail, but grimly he urged the stallion on.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This heavy helmet is wrought from hardened steel, the work of an advanced smith.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52566_ShortDesc", "A riveted fur cap")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52566_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

A medium cap of fur and rivets to keep one safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

These impossibly hard gauntlets are made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52591_ShortDesc", "A helmet of hardened steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52591_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The plain swam to Conan's gaze, the sunlight was a thick red haze and he reeled in his saddle, grasping the flowing mane with his hand. Blood rained on his mail, but grimly he urged the stallion on.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This heavy helmet is wrought from hardened steel, the work of an advanced smith.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52596_ShortDesc", "A riveted fur cap")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52596_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

A medium cap of fur and rivets to keep one safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52601_ShortDesc", "A steel helmet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52601_LongDesc", "This helmet is designed to ward off powerful blows to the head and keep the wearer's brains on the inside of their skull.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52602_ShortDesc", "A horned steel helmet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52602_LongDesc", "This helmet, ornamented with a pair of horns, is designed to ward off powerful blows to the head and keep the wearer's brains on the inside of their skull.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52603_ShortDesc", "An ancient helmet with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52603_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It is sorcery - grisly black magic from the grim youth of the world. An awful shape has risen out of the shades of the Past, and none can stand before it.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This eldritch helm bears markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the names Deathbringer, Kinscourge, and Maimer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52604_ShortDesc", "An ancient chestpiece with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52604_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I have lain in your arms, panting with the violence of our love; you have held and crushed and conquered me, drawing my soul to your lips with the fierceness of your bruising kisses. My heart is welded to your heart, my soul is part of your soul! Were I still in death and you fighting for life, I would come back to the abyss to aid you--aye, whether my spirit floated with the purple sails on the crystal sea of paradise, or writhed in the molten flames of hell! I am yours, and all the gods and all their eternities shall not sever us!</> - Queen of the Black Coast

This eldritch chest armor bears markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the names Tyros and Telith.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52605_ShortDesc", "Ancient gauntlets with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52605_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Those eyes grew and became gigantic, and in them the Cimmerian glimpsed the reality of all the abysmal and blasphemous horrors that lurk in the outer darkness of formless voids and nighted gulfs.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

These eldritch gauntlets bear markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper of the hybrid half-child of the humans and the Giant-kings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52606_ShortDesc", "Ancient leg armor with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52606_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Wits and swords are as straws against the wisdom of the Darkness...</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

This eldritch leg armor bears markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the names Klael the Warmaker, The Archivist, and the Priestking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52607_ShortDesc", "Ancient plated boots with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52607_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">By Crom, I do not like this place, where dead men rise, and sleeping men vanish into the bellies of shadows!</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

These eldritch boots bear markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the name of the Witch Queen.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52608_ShortDesc", "A heavy leather helmet")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52608_LongDesc", "This helmet is designed to ward off powerful blows to the head and keep the wearer\'s brains on the inside of their skull.\n\nThis heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52610_ShortDesc", "A coronal radiating winter\'s chill")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52610_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The glowing snow lay empty and bare; high above his head the witch-lights flashed and played in a frosty sky gone mad, and among the distant blue mountains there sounded a rolling thunder as of a gigantic war-chariot rushing behind steeds whose frantic hoofs struck lightning from the snows and echoes from the skies.</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nThis headpiece marks one as devout to Ymir, Father of Giants, Lord of Storm and War.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52611_ShortDesc", "This chest piece protects one with a frost giant\'s might")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52611_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And in that instant she flung her arms toward the lights that glowed in the skies above her and cried out in a voice that rang in Conan\'s ears for ever after: \'Ymir! Oh, my father, save me!\' </> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nThis frigid armor of adamantine strength marks one as devout to Ymir, Father of Giants, Lord of Storm and War.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52612_ShortDesc", "Gauntlets that give an icy touch")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52612_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Not so!\' cried an older man, whose eyes were wild and weird. \'It was Atali, the daughter of Ymir, the frost-giant! To fields of the dead she comes, and shows herself to the dying... She lures men from stricken fields into the wastelands to be slain by her brothers, the ice-giants, who lay men\'s red hearts smoking on Ymir\'s board.\'</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nThese gauntlets of ice and steel mark one as devout to Ymir, Father of Giants, Lord of Storm and War.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52613_ShortDesc", "Leggings marked by Ymir\'s runes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52613_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Swear not so often by Ymir,\' uneasily muttered a warrior, glancing at the distant mountains.</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nThese leggings, of a material both frosty and otherworldly, mark one as devout to Ymir, Father of Giants, Lord of Storm and War.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52614_ShortDesc", "Boots that crunch like snow with every step")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52614_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Above him the skies glowed and crackled with strange lights and gleams. The snow shone weirdly, now frosty blue, now icy crimson, now cold silver. Through a shimmering icy realm of enchantment Conan plunged doggedly onward, in a crystalline maze where the only reality was the white body dancing across the glittering snow beyond his reach - ever beyond his reach.</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nThese boots of winter weirdness mark one as devout to Ymir, Father of Giants, Lord of Storm and War.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52615_ShortDesc", "A riveted fur cap of Vanir make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52615_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

A medium cap of fur and rivets to keep one safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52935_ShortDesc", "A hood for those who work in the shadows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52935_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

Designed with the principle that the best fight is a fight avoided, this outfit allows the wearer to blend into the shadows and remain unseen in the deep shadows of the Zamorian cities. 
Whether it is as effective in the lands beyond Zamoria is another question.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52936_ShortDesc", "A leather chestpiece for those who work in the shadows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52936_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

Designed with the principle that the best fight is a fight avoided, this outfit allows the wearer to blend into the shadows and remain unseen in the deep shadows of the Zamorian cities. 

It has been wrapped tightly to dampen any noise caused by loose straps and buckles. Whether it is as effective in the lands beyond Zamoria is another question.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52937_ShortDesc", "Fingerless gloves for those who need dextrous hands")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52937_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

A thief's fingers must be free to do nimble work - manipulating lockpicks, snatching purses and slitting throats. These gloves are designed to protect the hand and forearm while freeing the fingers to do their worst.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52938_ShortDesc", "Leather leggings with a belt of useful pouches")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52938_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These leggings are designed to help, not hinder, the burgeoning burglar in their trade. Accompanied by a handy belt, full of small pouches for storing the various tools of the thieving profession, these skin tight leather pants also offer excellent protection.
 Zamorian cutthroats swear by them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52939_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots of supple leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52939_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These boots are designed to allow cutthroats easy access to their victims, damping their footsteps as they approach from behind. 
They're also surprisingly durable when fleeing the city watch.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52940_ShortDesc", "A hood for those who work in the shadows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52940_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

Designed with the principle that the best fight is a fight avoided, this outfit allows the wearer to blend into the shadows and remain unseen in the deep shadows of the Zamorian cities. 
Whether it is as effective in the lands beyond Zamoria is another question.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52941_ShortDesc", "A leather chestpiece for those who work in the shadows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52941_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

Designed with the principle that the best fight is a fight avoided, this outfit allows the wearer to blend into the shadows and remain unseen in the deep shadows of the Zamorian cities. 

It has been wrapped tightly to dampen any noise caused by loose straps and buckles. Whether it is as effective in the lands beyond Zamoria is another question.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52942_ShortDesc", "Fingerless gloves for those who need dextrous hands")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52942_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

A thief's fingers must be free to do nimble work - manipulating lockpicks, snatching purses and slitting throats. These gloves are designed to protect the hand and forearm while freeing the fingers to do their worst.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52943_ShortDesc", "Leather leggings with a belt of useful pouches")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52943_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These leggings are designed to help, not hinder, the burgeoning burglar in their trade. Accompanied by a handy belt, full of small pouches for storing the various tools of the thieving profession, these skin tight leather pants also offer excellent protection.
 Zamorian cutthroats swear by them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52944_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots of supple leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52944_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These boots are designed to allow cutthroats easy access to their victims, damping their footsteps as they approach from behind. 
They're also surprisingly durable when fleeing the city watch.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52950_ShortDesc", "A waistguard designed to intimidate")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52950_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

It is considered a challenge among Hyperborean slavers to go bare-chested on their raids, wearing nothing more than this waistguard. While it offers less protection than steel leggings and a breastplate, it intimidates newly caught slaves into submission.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52951_ShortDesc", "A set of sturdy bracers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52951_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

Hyperborean slavers wear this armor to intimidate their enemies and cow their slaves.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52956_ShortDesc", "A loincloth worn beneath by Hyperborean slavers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52956_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

Primarily worn beneath the more armored waistguard, this loincloth is designed to keep the vitals of a slaver warm and protected when on long raids in the northern lands of Asgard and Vanaheim.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52957_ShortDesc", "A helmet designed to intimidate")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52957_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

The helmets of Hyperboreans are designed to protect them from magical threats, as well as mundane. The witch-men of Hyperborea do not want anybody controlling their servants.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52958_ShortDesc", "Sturdy boots worn by Hyperborean slavers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52958_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

These boots are designed to be sturdy enough to last long trips and to grip well on rough terrain. It might be coincidental, but the additional grip makes it that much harder for a chained slave to pull a slaver off their feet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52965_ShortDesc", "Shemitish turban commonly worn in the meadowland cities")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52965_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. Due to their access to these caravans, the Shemitish people often have access to the first pick of goods coming from the east - including fine silks from Khitai and brightly dyed cloth from Turan. This bounty of cloth is reflected in the loose fitting, comfortable clothing woven by the tailors of Shem.\nThis clothing is a practical bulwark against the elements but won\'t be enough to stop a blade.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52975_ShortDesc", "A pair of bone earrings often worn by Vanir commoners")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52975_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These earrings provide no significant protection, but they are marked with clan symbols - so that if a dead settler is found, their possessions can be returned to the clan. Jokingly referred to by the Aesir as Vanearrings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52976_ShortDesc", "A fur-lined vest worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52976_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

This vest is designed to keep the settler warm, while freeing their hands for working with tools. It offers some basic protection against attacks due to its thickness, but is not as effective as true armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52977_ShortDesc", "A set of fur gloves worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52977_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These gloves are perfect for keeping the hands warm while working frozen soil.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52978_ShortDesc", "A furry breechclout worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52978_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

This breechclout  keeps the settler warm, but has an unfortunate tendency to attract fleas and lice. Vanir women are well known for their habit of bathing in freezing streams in the midst of winter, Vanir men are known for being lice-infested bastards.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52979_ShortDesc", "A pair of furry boots worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52981_ShortDesc", "A fur-lined vest worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52981_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

This vest is designed to keep the settler warm, while freeing their hands for working with tools. It offers some basic protection against attacks due to its thickness, but is not as effective as true armor.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52990_LongDesc", "Crafted from scraps of metal and leather torn from the Champion of the Warmaker, this armor still retains some of it\'s potential. It could be further improved given enough time and magical infusions. It withstands an enormous amount of punishment. The magical energies that surge through this helmet grant additional Grit.")

The magical energies that surge through these leggings grant additional Encumbrance and repairs the equipped weapon for a slight amount when the wearer takes damage.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53001_ShortDesc", "Extract of the aloe plant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53001_LongDesc", "Stygian traditions of healing hold that the aloe plant contains many desirable properties. In Luxur, the aloe is harvested for use in the temples of Derketo to cleanse blemishes from the skin of the priestesses. It is often used to sooth oozing wounds and those who ingest it claim that they feel a burst of wellbeing. Whether these effects are of the body or the mind is irrelevant - ingesting aloe extract seems to give the imbiber a regenerative health effect.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53011_ShortDesc", "A brilliant purple potion that cures everything")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53011_LongDesc", "Extracted from the venom of various poisonous snakes, this violet potion seems to purge the system of all poisons upon use. Commonly used by street performers in Vendhya to shrug off the effects of cobra bites, more fools have died trying to harvest the ingredients for the curative than would have died if the curative did not exist at all. This concoction also has the added benefit - and drawback - of making the user experience an effect no unlike that of drinking alcohol.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53101_ShortDesc", "A potion that causes hallucinations and visions")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53101_LongDesc", "The yellow lotus is used by sorcerers to provide visions and trances, with a strong hallucinogenic effect. It is said that those who survive the visions are given a deeper insight into the world, able to communicate with the inner world in a way that rewrites their very physique. In reality, the effect of the potion blanks the mind, freeing one to focus on a new set of skills at the cost of forgetting all previous abilities and skills.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53102_ShortDesc", "A glowing potion that improves underwater breathing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53102_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">She waded out until the low waves were lapping about her waist; then she struck out strongly, swimming with a vigor that promised unusual enurance.</> - The Devil in Iron

The Dregs have always been a dangerous place. When the Giant-kings would send slaves to clean out the sewers, they would often lose valuable servants to the creatures which dwelt in the sewers, not to mention those that drowned when a chamber suddenly flooded.

For the latter, at least, they could craft a solution. Using a combination of the strange glowing plants and heat, they created a potion that would allow those caught in water to be able to buy a few more minutes of precious breathing time.

Slaves still disappeared from time to time, but the scrutiny of the Giant-kings seemed to cause a great reduction in these incidents.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53201_ShortDesc", "A poison that can be applied to daggers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53201_LongDesc", "The toxin gland of the Sand Reapers is difficult to obtain due to the ferocious nature of the creatures. When properly prepared, it becomes a poison that can be applied to certain weapons, such as daggers, and then used to debilitate foes. In Vendhya, assassins often use poison to kill their targets - the current king has weathered no less than five attempts on his life thus far, though the five skulls bleaching on the Tower of the Kites are evidence of their failure.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53203_ShortDesc", "A poison that can be applied to daggers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53203_LongDesc", "When properly prepared, it becomes a poison that can be applied to certain weapons, such as daggers, and then used to debilitate foes. In Vendhya, assassins often use poison to kill their targets - the current king has weathered no less than five attempts on his life thus far, though the five skulls bleaching on the Tower of the Kites are evidence of their failure.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53501_ShortDesc", "Flesh that has been ritually purified")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53501_LongDesc", "Devotees of Yog have purified this flesh in the firepits of sacrifice. It can be eaten to gain the favour of Yog.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53502_ShortDesc", "A dish purported to be blessed by the gods")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53502_LongDesc", "Worshippers of Mitra often bring sacrifices of fruit or grain to lay upon his altar, in return for his blessing. And occasionally his blessing is very formidable indeed, taking the form of Ambrosia. This bizarre substance, considered a food of the gods, has healing properties that the Priests of Mitra use to bring strength and vitality to the poor. How it is made is pure conjecture, as it seems to congeal within empty vessels left out on the altar with no physical intervention from priest or penitent.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53503_ShortDesc", "A potent antidote to poison")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53503_LongDesc", "Set commands that his followers revere serpents above all creatures, even requiring that his devotees allow themselves to be devoured by the giant temple snakes if the creatures so desire. This reverence means that many priests are bitten by the venemous serpents that roam the stone temples. Rather than simply accept their fate at the hands of a petulant snake, the priests often keep a supply of this antidote handy. Created during the rituals of sacrifice from the hearts of humans, it is a literal trade of a life for a life and Set does not seem to hold any grudges against followers who spare themselves in this manner.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53511_ShortDesc", "Crossbow bolts with flint heads")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53511_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Arus the watchman grasped his crossbow with shaky hands, and he felt beads of clammy perspiration on his skin as he stared at the unlovely corpse sprawling on the polished floor before him. It is not pleasant to come upon Death in a lonely place at midnight.</> - The God in the Bowl\n\nWithout bolts, a crossbow is just a really poorly shaped club.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53548_ShortDesc", "A mixture for removing warpaints")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53548_LongDesc", "Some part alcohol, some part water, this fluid is used to remove warpaints in times of peace and quiet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53549_ShortDesc", "A brush for copying warpaint designs.")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53549_LongDesc", "The application of symbols and paints to the body during war is a time honored tradition of the Nordheimers. In days past, tattoos were traditional, but the ever-shifting tides of battle and alliance between those war-like tribes made it difficult to be certain who would be friend or foe in the future.

One well known tale tells of a chieftain's son, married off to a neighboring tribe to seal a hasty alliance. When he brought his new bride to the bedchamber and eagerly removed her dress, he was shocked to discover a picture of his father and the words "limp-pricked whore monger" tattooed across her back. The alliance did not last very long.

Since that time, inks have been popular. Less durable, yes, but also less chance of making a permanent mistake. Through the use of this brush, warpaints can quickly be copied and used again.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53611_ShortDesc", "Arrows with flint heads")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53611_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53615_ShortDesc", "Arrows that release a healing cloud")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53615_LongDesc", "Made somewhat unwieldy by the bag of ground aloe attached to them, these arrows will release a small cloud of healing gas wherever they strike.

This doesn't seem like a practical way to deliver healing in battle, as there is just as much chance of healing foes. But... some people like exotic solutions.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53616_ShortDesc", "An arrow of evil and ancient design")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53616_LongDesc", "Who knows what sorcery is etched upon the head of this ancient arrow? All that is know is that every shot with it weakens an enemy, corrupting their soul and leaving them gasping for relief.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53617_ShortDesc", "An arrow that explodes on impact")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53617_LongDesc", "Only a madman would willingly carry arrows like this into battle. The chance of hitting friends when trying to damage foes, the chance of accidentally ricocheting an arrow back into oneself, and the chance that the arrows will explode in the quiver...
A madman or a berserker, perhaps.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53618_ShortDesc", "An arrow treated with a glowing substance")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53618_LongDesc", "The head of this arrow has been treated with a glowing substance, causing it to glow. This is useful for marking points in dark caverns and seeing how deep those bottomless wells really are.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53619_ShortDesc", "A hollowed out arrow filled with a poisonous powder")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53619_LongDesc", "This arrowhead has been hollowed out and filled with a poisonous powder. Designed to split upon impact, the arrow releases a cloud of poisonous spores into the air, damaging any standing within.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53620_ShortDesc", "An arrow containing an oily solution")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53620_LongDesc", "The hollow arrow is filled with a pair of special reactants that mix together on contact with the ground and form an oily pool.\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53621_ShortDesc", "An arrow treated with witchfire")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53621_LongDesc", "The head of this arrow has been treated with witchfire and black blood. This substance sticks to targets and burns them constantly causing a bleeding effect. Due to the rather strange shape of the arrow, it is not possible to fit as many of these as other arrows in a quiver.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53622_ShortDesc", "A hollowed out arrow filled with a noxious acid")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53622_LongDesc", "This arrowhead has been hollowed out and filled with a potent acid. Designed to split upon impact, the arrow releases a cloud of acidic smoke into the air, damaging any standing within as well as their armor.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53623_ShortDesc", "A hollowed out arrow filled with smoke")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53623_LongDesc", "The hollow arrow is filled with a pair of special reactants that mix together on contact with the ground and form a cloud of smoke.\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53651_ShortDesc", "Venomous snakes transformed into deadly arrows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53651_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53652_ShortDesc", "Arrows made with an Abysmal Fang")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53652_LongDesc", "The fangs of the Abysmal Remnant are made of a hardened substance that can withstand strong acid. They are also razor sharp.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53653_ShortDesc", "Bolts made with an Abysmal Fang")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53653_LongDesc", "The fangs of the Abysmal Remnant are made of a hardened substance that can withstand strong acid. They are also razor sharp. \n\nBolts can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53654_ShortDesc", "Arrows with hardened steel heads of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53654_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds. Cimmerians use this fine metal to create arrowheads that will put holes straight through the fine and pretty armor of their civilized foes.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53655_ShortDesc", "Crossbow bolts with hardened steel heads of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53655_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Arus the watchman grasped his crossbow with shaky hands, and he felt beads of clammy perspiration on his skin as he stared at the unlovely corpse sprawling on the polished floor before him. It is not pleasant to come upon Death in a lonely place at midnight.</> - The God in the Bowl

Without bolts, a crossbow is just a really poorly shaped club.

Cimmerian bolts are made from hardened steel and penetrate deeply into armor, though one needs a supply of such finely made metal.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53656_ShortDesc", "Arrows with heads forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53656_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Now arrows fly between the hosts like stinging clouds that hide the sun.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

There is very little that can defend a target from such an exquisitely made arrow. But star metal is precious and rare, and not always available.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53657_ShortDesc", "Crossbow bolts with heads forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53657_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan bounded back from the waving bills and his leap carried him outside the ring of his foes, to where Arus stood fumbling at his crossbow. A savage kick in the belly dropped him, green faced and gagging, and Conan's sandalled heel crunched square in the watchman's mouth.</> - The God in the Bowl

Without bolts, a crossbow is just a really poorly shaped club.

Bolts of start metal pass through armor like a heated knife through tallow.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53658_ShortDesc", "Arrows crafted from shards of ice infused with the power of Ymir")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53658_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")
