column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53659_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Arus the watchman grasped his crossbow with shaky hands, and he felt beads of clammy perspiration on his skin as he stared at the unlovely corpse sprawling on the polished floor before him. It is not pleasant to come upon Death in a lonely place at midnight.</> - The God in the Bowl\n\nWithout bolts, a crossbow is just a really poorly shaped club.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53712_ShortDesc", "A severed human arm")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53712_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan rose, still smiling, as if to reach into a near-by cooking pot; then quick as a cat he struck Aja a terrible blow with the heavy bone. The Bakalah war-chief slumped over, his skull crushed in, and instantly a frightful yell rent the skies as the Bamulas went into action like blood-mad panthers.</> - The Vale of Lost Women

Once, this limb belonged to a dangerous criminal, but now he can be considered 'armless. It looks like a left arm though, so he is all right. He can stump his enemies by pretending to surrender. Still, this entire incident has made him half as handy as he used to be. 
At least from now on you'll be well armed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53713_ShortDesc", "A severed human leg")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53713_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan brained him with the beef bone, took his poniard and his keys, and made a leisurely departure.</> - Rogues in the House

This leg, severed from the corpse of an enemy, is bloodless and stiff. Carrying it around might not be a good way to make friends, but then again it might help to make a different kind of friend.
The important thing is that it can be used as a weapon. And beating someone to death with a limb is an itch that rarely gets scratched in civilized society.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53735_ShortDesc", "A light axe balanced for throwing")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53735_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails\n\nThrough the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53997_LongDesc", "These daggers are old but very sharp. The bones that these daggers have been crafted from do not come from any of the animals that walks these lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54006_ShortDesc", "Wrested from the undead hands of the Executioner")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54006_LongDesc", "A creature known only as the Executioner once wielded this. It is unknown how many eyes have glanced on the blade of this weapon before it has sunk its teeth into them but the indentions and grooves of the blade are caked with age-old blood.\n\nThis weapon will instantly destroy any opponent that has suffered significant enough damage.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54007_LongDesc", "A creature known only as the Executioner once wielded this. It is unknown how many eyes have glanced on the blade of this weapon before it has sunk its teeth into them but the indentions and grooves of the blade are caked with age-old blood.\n\nThis weapon will instantly destroy any opponent that has suffered significant enough damage.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_55001_ShortDesc", "Use to invoke the Avatar of Set")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_55001_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Some gods are strong to harm, others, to aid; at least so say their priests.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Learning true names is a study that sorcerers use to contact the demons of the Outer Void. Such sorcerers have volumes full of the names of their familiars and allies.

The true name of a god, however, burns brightly in the mind when spoken, then flares and fades into nothingness. Once spoken, such a name is forgotten immediately.

This name then, carved in stone, is a priceless gift. For a short period, the gaze of a god will be upon the speaker and they will be lifted to heights of power undreamed of. But men were not built to live as gods, so the power is fleeting.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_55100_ShortDesc", "A spiritual residue left on religious altars")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_55100_LongDesc", "Over time, a place that is used for religious ceremonies takes on a certain significance. Not simply in the minds of the followers of that religion, but also in others who pass through an area.\nIn the oldest groves and shrines of the world, the presence of those ancient, gloomy gods can still be felt. In the shining altars of Mitra or the bloody slabs of Set, the manifestation of this spiritual presence is palpable.\nWhen a shrine is defiled, this effect leeches slowly away, but if the defilers are of an opposing religion, they actually absorb the power that they have stolen. Thus altars are a precious commodity in the Exiled Lands and worship brings great bounties to those who pursue it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_60001_ShortDesc", "Imp Idol Eye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_60001_LongDesc", "Imp Idol Eye")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_70001_ShortDesc", "A small idol depicting Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_70001_LongDesc", "Worshippers of Set are aware that displeasing their god can mean an altar and a blood drenched knife in their future. In order to keep the dictates of Set constantly on their minds, devotees place small statues around their dwellings to remind them of the precepts of the Old Serpent.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80101_ShortDesc", "A comfortable wooden bed")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80101_LongDesc", "Few of the inhabitants of the Exiled Lands are lucky enough to sleep in a bed at night. Some disdain the comfort of a full bed, imagining that the softness of the mattress will cause a softening of their bodies and minds.\nBut some see the bed as a place of lovemaking, sleeping and dreaming. They consider it an important part of civilization and sneer at those who sleep on the ground as uncouth savages.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80102_ShortDesc", "A folding bed that takes up little space")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80102_LongDesc", "This bed made of leather stretched over a folding frame, take up less space than a conventional bed.\nCommonly used in barracks, cheap inns and mercenary headquarters, this bed is valued mostly for its ability to be stacked and stored whenever it isn\'t being used.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point until it is destroyed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80103_ShortDesc", "A low divan made in the Stygian style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80103_LongDesc", "Both couch and bed, the divan probably originated in Vendhya or Turan, but it rapidly became popular in the kingdom of Stygia. The most elaborate of divans are made of silk and gold inlaid ebony, but they can also be made from simple materials.\nStygian nobles are often portrayed as indolent and decadent and imagery of them lounging on divans, eating and drinking, has contributed to this portrayal. In practicality, during the hottest hours of the day all Stygians retire to their houses for leisure time and these rumors are probably spread by foreign merchants frustrated with a culture that doesn\'t follow their schedule.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point until it is destroyed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80104_ShortDesc", "A comfortable, double sized bed")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80104_LongDesc", "Few of the inhabitants of the Exiled Lands are lucky enough to sleep in a bed at night. Some disdain the comfort of a full bed, imagining that the softness of the mattress will cause a softening of their bodies and minds.\nBut some see the bed as a place of lovemaking, sleeping and dreaming. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point.")

Using a bed will set it as your spawn point.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80111_ShortDesc", "A rawhide bedroll for sleeping on the ground.")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80111_LongDesc", "Roughly sewn together from the hides of animals, this bedroll offers warmth and some small protection from sharp rocks and twigs on the grounds.

The price, of course, is the sharp smell of untreated leather and the occasional unwanted attentions of passing animals.

When somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Placing a bedroll will set it as your spawn point, until you place a new one or it is destroyed. Placing a new bedroll will destroy the old one.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80112_ShortDesc", "A mattress of leaves, twigs and grass.")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80112_LongDesc", "A hastily gathered bundle of fibers stripped from the plants and vegetation that dot the Exiled Lands, this bedroll offers very little in the way warmth or protection.

It's probably better than lying on the hard ground though. Slightly.

When somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Placing a bedroll will set it as your spawn point, until you place a new one or it is destroyed. Placing a new bedroll will destroy the old one.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80131_ShortDesc", "A well that fills slowly over time")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80131_LongDesc", "Made from rough stones and wood, this well manages to capture a small amount of water.\nWater is an essential element for survival and this is doubly the case in the desert environments of the Exiled Lands. Any permanent settlement near water will inevitable be contested by others who also seek access to this life affirming resource.\nThe convenience of a well allows building in areas that would otherwise be unsustainable. Wells fill with water over time and can be used to quench thirst, replenish waterskins and perform the dozens of other activities that require the presence of water.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80132_ShortDesc", "A large well that fills slowly over time")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80132_LongDesc", "Made from well-fitted, tight stonework, this well captures a generous amount of water.\nWater is an essential element for survival and this is doubly the case in the desert environments of the Exiled Lands. Any permanent settlement near water will inevitable be contested by others who also seek access to this life affirming resource.\nThe convenience of a well allows building in areas that would otherwise be unsustainable. Wells fill with water over time and can be used to quench thirst, replenish waterskins and perform the dozens of other activities that require the presence of water.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80151_ShortDesc", "A training dummy for practising combat techniques")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80151_LongDesc", "Made of stuffed straw and rough cloth, this dummy is a stand in for the horrendous creatures of the Exiled Lands.\nThe ability to guage hit locations from the markings on the dummy is a great way for warriors to increase their abilities.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80152_ShortDesc", "A target for refining ranged techniques")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80152_LongDesc", "Bows require a lifetime of discipline to master and those who do not practise regularly will find themselves losing the edge.\nThis target provides a perfect opportunity to practise with bows, crossbows and thrown weapons without the inevitable conflict that comes from shooting somebody full of arrows.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80171_ShortDesc", "This spike can be decorated with various skulls")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80171_LongDesc", "This sharpened wooden spike, once placed, waits patiently for something to be impaled upon it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80201_ShortDesc", "A rectangular wooden table")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80201_LongDesc", "Tables vary in shape and size, materials and decoration based on the culture and craftsmanship of their maker.\nThis one is a wooden rectangle.\nThe artisan was probably hoping to decorate the table with dozens of interesting objects and thereby distract from the lack of imagination in the creation of the table itself.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80202_ShortDesc", "A round wooden table")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80202_LongDesc", "Tables vary in shape and size, materials and decoration based on the culture and craftsmanship of their maker.\nThis one is a wooden circle.\nThe artisan was probably hoping to decorate the table with dozens of interesting objects and thereby distract from the lack of imagination in the creation of the table itself.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80203_ShortDesc", "A slab of rock")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80203_LongDesc", "This rock slab serves the dual purpose of being both a place to sit and eat and a sacrificial altar. Entirely depending on the purpose to which it has been put, those stains on the surface are either bloodstains or gravy stains.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80204_ShortDesc", "A rectangular wooden table")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80204_LongDesc", "Tables vary in shape and size, materials and decoration based on the culture and craftsmanship of their maker.\nThis one is a wooden rectangle.\nThe artisan was probably hoping to decorate the table with dozens of interesting objects and thereby distract from the lack of imagination in the creation of the table itself.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80205_ShortDesc", "A low wooden table")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80205_LongDesc", "Tables vary in shape and size, materials and decoration based on the culture and craftsmanship of their maker.\nThis one is a low wooden circle.\nThe artisan was probably hoping to decorate the table with dozens of interesting objects and thereby distract from the lack of imagination in the creation of the table itself.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80208_ShortDesc", "A wooden crate for storage")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80208_LongDesc", "A box made out of wood, as found in many a market. Crates allow large quantities of storage but being made solely out of wood, are much weaker than their strongbox and chest counterparts.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80209_ShortDesc", "A wooden crate for storage")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80209_LongDesc", "A box made out of wood, as found in many a market. Crates allow large quantities of storage but being made solely out of wood, are much weaker than their strongbox and chest counterparts.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80210_ShortDesc", "A bundle of sharpened stakes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80210_LongDesc", "These makeshift bundles of sharpened wooden stakes are usually placed around mercenary camps and other temporary fortifications.\nNo sane soldier wants to charge an enemy who has ringed their camp with barricades such as these.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80211_ShortDesc", "A barricade of high sharpened stakes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80211_LongDesc", "Designed as a foil to cavalry charges, the stakes on these barricades were originally about chest high to a horse. Over time it was discovered that the closer the spikes were to eye height on a horse, the less chance that the beast could be coerced into charging them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80212_ShortDesc", "A wooden crate for storage")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80212_LongDesc", "A box made out of wood, as found in many a market. Crates allow large quantities of storage but being made solely out of wood, are much weaker than their strongbox and chest counterparts.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80213_ShortDesc", "A crude cage made out of branches")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80213_LongDesc", "A makeshift cage, suitable as a place to keep ones more unruly... possessions.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80214_ShortDesc", "A crude cage made out of branches")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80214_LongDesc", "A makeshift cage, suitable as a place to keep ones more unruly... possessions.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80215_ShortDesc", "A crude cage made out of branches")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80215_LongDesc", "A makeshift cage, suitable as a place to keep ones more unruly... possessions.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80216_ShortDesc", "A plate made in the Stygian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80216_LongDesc", "A simple plate for holding or preparing food.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80217_ShortDesc", "A crude wooden fence")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80217_LongDesc", "A collection of crude wooden planks and branches, bound together with rope, these wooden fences offer little protection from intruders but are useful to encircle ones encampment.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80218_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier made in the Acheronian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80218_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80219_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier made in the Acheronian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80219_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80251_ShortDesc", "A simple wooden stool")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80251_LongDesc", "Sometimes after a day of killing and slaying, all an Exile wants to do is sit down and relax.\nStools are often used as makeshift weapons in tavern brawls across Hyboria, usually hurled at an opponent in between curses.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80252_ShortDesc", "A round wooden stool")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80252_LongDesc", "Useful for sitting and hurling at enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80253_ShortDesc", "A woven wooden stool")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80253_LongDesc", "Crafted by weaving thin bands of hard wood into a strong yet pliable surface, this stool is comfortable to sit on and very lightweight.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80261_ShortDesc", "A wooden chair")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80261_LongDesc", "Commonly found only in the houses of the wealthy or noble, chairs with armrests and backs are considered a mark of refinement.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80262_ShortDesc", "Wooden chair with backrest")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80262_LongDesc", "Commonly found only in the houses of the wealthy or noble, chairs with armrests and backs are considered a mark of refinement.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80263_ShortDesc", "Wooden chair with backrest and armrests")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80263_LongDesc", "Commonly found only in the houses of the wealthy or noble, chairs with armrests and backs are considered a mark of refinement.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80271_ShortDesc", "A crude log bench")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80271_LongDesc", "Benches like this are common in the taverns and alehouses of the world. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80272_ShortDesc", "A crude wooden bench")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80272_LongDesc", "Benches like this are common in the taverns and alehouses of the world. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80281_ShortDesc", "A throne made of stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80281_LongDesc", "Unlike other chairs, a throne gives the one who sits in it authority above and beyond that of an ordinary man.\nBattles have always been fought for this kind of power, and they always will be.\nSitting on a throne of any kind will increase confidence and prowess for a period.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80301_ShortDesc", "A wooden signpost")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80301_LongDesc", "In the Western kingdoms of Aquilonia and Nemedia, the practise of using wooden signs to provide warning and information for travellers and merchants has been established for centuries.\nOnce a signpost is placed, it can be used to write a custom message for any travellers to read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80302_ShortDesc", "A wall sign")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80302_LongDesc", "Designed to be placed on walls and provide information about the location, these signs are a mark of civilization beyond what most people would expect to find in the Exiled Lands.\nOnce a signpost is placed, it can be used to write a custom message for any travellers to read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80303_ShortDesc", "A proud and erect battle-standard")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80303_LongDesc", "Placing a battle standard makes the surrounding area of the standard a PvP combat area.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80311_ShortDesc", "A scroll made from flattened reed stalks")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80311_LongDesc", "Made from the pith of flattened reeds, papyrus scrolls are commonly used in Stygia for holding the words of sacred texts.\nThe material used is too brittle to be very good for the creation of long-form texts, but for simple messages a papyrus scroll is cheap and easy to produce.\nThis scroll can be filled in, and then shared with others. If they can read, of course. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80312_ShortDesc", "A finely woven bowl")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80312_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'A shell-shaped bowl of gold on a black altar in a deep cavern,\' Conan muttered, frowning as he sought to capture the illusive image.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nBowls are no rare thing among the tools of man - made from clay and metal and carved wood. Some bowls are given a more decorative touch, made from finer materials with artistic flourishes - a show of an artisan\'s skill, the indulgence of the wealthy, or the reverence of a sorcerer or priest who puts the receptacle to mystical purpose.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80313_LongDesc", "Made from the pith of flattened reeds, papyrus scrolls are commonly used in Stygia for holding the words of sacred texts.\nThe material used is too brittle to be very good for the creation of long-form texts, but for simple messages a papyrus scroll is cheap and easy to produce.\nThis scroll can be filled in, and then shared with others. column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80501_ShortDesc", "A tall torch that can be placed in the ground")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80501_LongDesc", "A large torch that can be placed in the ground to create light in an area. Some use these as beacons, to light their way home on the darkest of nights.\nIn the Exiled Lands, the torches of the Darfari Cannibals are prominent in the darkness. In their camps, the cannibals dance madly to the throbbing of skin-covered drums and their frenzy amongst the flickering light of torch and cookfire seems oddly appropriate.\nThese torches can be lit and unlit without fuel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80502_ShortDesc", "An upgraded torch that can be placed in the ground")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80502_LongDesc", "A large torch that can be placed in the ground to create light in an area. Some use these as beacons, to light their way home on the darkest of nights.\nIn the Exiled Lands, the torches of the Darfari Cannibals are prominent in the darkness. In their camps, the cannibals dance madly to the throbbing of skin-covered drums and their frenzy amongst the flickering light of torch and cookfire seems oddly appropriate.\nThese torches can be lit and unlit without fuel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80503_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier made in the Stygian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80503_LongDesc", "This small brazier, made of bronze worked into the shape of a serpent, is commonly found in Stygian temples of Set. \nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80504_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier made in the Stygian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80504_LongDesc", "This small brazier, made of bronze worked into the shape of a serpent, is commonly found in Stygian temples of Set. \nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon. ")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80505_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80506_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80507_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80508_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80508_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80509_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80509_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80511_ShortDesc", "An iron bracketed torch that can be attached to a wall")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80511_LongDesc", "Defending a fortification during a night assault is made infinitely simpler by the ability to see where the enemy is coming from.\nAttaching torches to the walls of a building can free hands to grip a blade or pike and cast a light upon the activities of enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80515_ShortDesc", "An iron-sheathed lantern that can be attached to a wall")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80515_LongDesc", "This ornate lantern bears patterning that seems to indicate that it is of Turanian origin. It is well known that the rich quarter of Agrapur has street lanterns placed at regular intervals to discourage thieves.\nLanterns have a steadier light than torches, and they remain lit for longer. However, the soft glow of a lantern fails to evoke the same primal urges as the naked flame.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80521_ShortDesc", "The melted, half-used stub of a candle")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80521_LongDesc", "Used primarily indoors, candles are the cheapest light source available. In royal castles, great candelabras with hundreds of candles light great ballrooms and throne rooms, while in the huts of peasants a single candle burns in the night to illuminate those simple tasks that are performed once the sun has dropped below the horizon.\nMade from beeswax shaped around a treated wick, this candle has been used extensively in the past.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80522_ShortDesc", "A white, beeswax candle")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80522_LongDesc", "Used primarily indoors, candles are the cheapest light source available. In royal castles, great candelabras with hundreds of candles light great ballrooms and throne rooms, while in the huts of peasants a single candle burns in the night to illuminate those simple tasks that are performed once the sun has dropped below the horizon.\nWhite candles are often burned in the temples of Mitra representing the purity of thought and knowledge that Mitra brings to his followers.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80523_ShortDesc", "A black, beeswax candle")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80523_LongDesc", "Used primarily indoors, candles are the cheapest light source available. In royal castles, great candelabras with hundreds of candles light great ballrooms and throne rooms, while in the huts of peasants a single candle burns in the night to illuminate those simple tasks that are performed once the sun has dropped below the horizon.\nBlack candles are sought after by sorcerers for use in their rituals. The vilest of men purportedly create candles from the blood of demons for communicating with presences that circle in the Outer Void.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80524_ShortDesc", "A black wax candle")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80524_LongDesc", "Used primarily indoors, candles are the cheapest light source available. In royal castles, great candelabras with hundreds of candles light great ballrooms and throne rooms, while in the huts of peasants a single candle burns in the night to illuminate those simple tasks that are performed once the sun has dropped below the horizon.\nBlack candles are sought after by sorcerers for use in their rituals. The vilest of men purportedly create candles from the blood of demons for communicating with presences that circle in the Outer Void.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80525_ShortDesc", "A metal candleholder")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80525_LongDesc", "Mostly used for decoration and to prevent the ever-present danger of candlewax burns, this candleholder is nondescript and could be found in any Hyborian Kingdom.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80531_ShortDesc", "An odd gem that glows when rubbed")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80531_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'They are jewels, fused with radium. You rub them with your thumb to make them glow, and rub them again, the opposite way, to extinguish them.\'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk\n\nThe product of a science long vanished in the ancient past, these gems seem to glow indefinitely when activated. There is a cost, however, as those who use the Radium Gems seem to slowly lose their grip on sanity, whispering to themselves of green stoned cities and the nameless horrors that stalk them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80532_ShortDesc", "A bag of witchfire powder")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80532_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">For an instant a dimming witchfire glimmered in those dusky depths; then it disappeared, and Conan lay staring down into the blackness of the ultimate abyss from which no sound came.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Witchfire is an alchemical component, created by ancient scientists as a waste product on their ultimate path to radium gems.

Witchfire powder is created by combining glowing plants and brimstone. 

The powder can be used in the crafting of heatless, blue torches.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80533_ShortDesc", "An ornate standing torch topped with radium")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80533_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They are jewels, fused with radium. You rub them with your thumb to make them glow, and rub them again, the opposite way, to extinguish them.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

The product of a science long vanished in the ancient past, these gems seem to glow indefinitely when activated. There is a cost, however, as those who use the Radium Gems seem to slowly lose their grip on sanity, whispering to themselves of green stoned cities and the nameless horrors that stalk them.

This standing torch can be placed in the ground to light an area or show the path home. Adding dye to the radium torch, will change the color of its glow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80534_ShortDesc", "A hanging torch-holder containing an odd gem")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80534_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'They are jewels, fused with radium. You rub them with your thumb to make them glow, and rub them again, the opposite way, to extinguish them.\'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk\n\nThe product of a science long vanished in the ancient past, these gems seem to glow indefinitely when activated. There is a cost, however, as those who use the Radium Gems seem to slowly lose their grip on sanity, whispering to themselves of green stoned cities and the nameless horrors that stalk them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80535_ShortDesc", "An ornate wall torch topped with radium")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80535_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They are jewels, fused with radium. You rub them with your thumb to make them glow, and rub them again, the opposite way, to extinguish them.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

The product of a science long vanished in the ancient past, these gems seem to glow indefinitely when activated. There is a cost, however, as those who use the Radium Gems seem to slowly lose their grip on sanity, whispering to themselves of green stoned cities and the nameless horrors that stalk them.

This wall torch can be attached to a building. Adding dye to the radium torch will change the color of its glow.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80536_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">For an instant a dimming witchfire glimmered in those dusky depths; then it disappeared, and Conan lay staring down into the blackness of the ultimate abyss from which no sound came.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Witchfire is an alchemical component, created by ancient scientists as a waste product on their ultimate patch to radium gems.

Witchfire powder is created from the combination of strange glowing plants and brimstone. 

This wall torch burns blue and gives off no heat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80539_ShortDesc", "A standing torch made from glowing plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80539_LongDesc", "Scholars and adventurers have long known of the properties of certain glowing plants that can be found in subterranean caves and hollows. Though some barbaric tribes swear that such places are demon-tainted and ghost-haunted and avoid them at all costs, others swear that they provide healing or other medicinal properties.\n\nThis is a smokeless torch, created from the bones of some unfortunate creature and a bundle of glowing plants.")

Though some barbaric tribes swear that such places are demon-tainted and ghost-haunted and avoid them at all costs, others swear that they provide healing or other medicinal properties.\n\nThis is a smokeless torch, created from the bones of some unfortunate creature and a bundle of glowing plants.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80551_ShortDesc", "A patterned tapestry in earthen colors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80551_LongDesc", "Tapestries such as this travel the Lotus road between Khitai and the Kingdoms of the West daily. Woven of plant fibers or silk, they vary in quality and quantity based entirely on the skill of the weaver and the materials used. \nThat these can be made in the Exiled Lands, without a loom, is impressive.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80553_ShortDesc", "A decorative grindstone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80553_LongDesc", "Grindstones are usually fashioned out of sandstone. This grindstone, however, is not, and as such is only functional as a decorative item.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80571_ShortDesc", "A small awning of orange cloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80571_LongDesc", "Among the great bazaars of Khemi, merchants use awnings such as this to protect their wares from the harsh Stygian sun.\nBy their nature, these awnings are made to be taken up and down quickly. They are not particularly robust, but they do offer shade when needed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80601_ShortDesc", "A red, patterned, Stygian carpet")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80601_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this carpet is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80621_ShortDesc", "A rug made from rawhide")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80621_LongDesc", "In the gloomy hills of Cimmeria and the snow capped ranges of Vanaheim and Asgard, animal hides and furs are considered a necessity. Hide rugs are a common floor ornament considered doubly practical if the fur is left attached.\nThey also have a distinctive fragrance.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80631_LongDesc", "Pillows can be anything from a sack stuffed with rags to a masterwoven spider silk. They can be found from hovels to palaces and anywhere in between. Even the hardiest of warriors like to have somewhere to lay their head at night.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80643_LongDesc", "Shaped of clay and fired in a kiln, jugs are used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80644_ShortDesc", "A small jar")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80644_LongDesc", "These jars are sought after by merchants for their light weight and compact size. They usually contain rare ingredients such as lotus honey.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80645_LongDesc", "This crude bowl could have been made in any land, by any maker. It bears no distinguishing markers beyond its ability to hold liquid.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80646_ShortDesc", "A wooden bowl")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80646_LongDesc", "A simple wooden bowl for holding or preparing food.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80647_ShortDesc", "A vessel for holding questionable liquids")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80647_LongDesc", "Hammered wood, banded with iron, this flagon is indistiguishable from thousands of the same found in dives and watering holes across Hyboria. A friend to cling to in dark times, a lover to kiss when lonely and a weapon to swing when the action starts, the humble flagon has seen and been everywhere.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80673_ShortDesc", "A keg for storing ale")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80673_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He remembered great horns of foaming ale, jacks of sparkling wine gulped carelessly or spilled on the tavern floor.</> - A Witch Shall be Born

Ale is the choice drink of fighting men, especially in taverns where the wine is sour. Served in foaming tankards from large oaken kegs, ale is usually served at room temperature and has a rich fruit flavor.

This keg bears no specific maker's mark, but that won't stop anybody from drinking it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80695_ShortDesc", "A shelf for displaying objects")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80695_LongDesc", "This simple shelf can be placed against almost any wall and used to display small objects.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80697_ShortDesc", "A statuette depicting the Warmaker")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80697_LongDesc", "This statuette has grooves along the bottom edges, as if it has frequently scraped against metal holder.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80701_LongDesc", "Moth eaten and ragged, this flag is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.\nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80740_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with common Darfari patterns.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80741_ShortDesc", "A decorative skeleton piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80741_LongDesc", "While tastes in interior design may vary, few visitors would complain about skeletal decoration pieces such as this. Mostly out of fear of being added to the owners bone collection.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80742_ShortDesc", "A crackling place of warmth and welcoming")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80742_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Logs flamed in the wide fireplace, for there was a frosty edge to the air, and a great meat pasty in a stone platter stood smoking on a broad mahogany board.\'</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nFew things warm the body and the soul, as a proper fireplace and the welcoming spirit of the hearth. How civilized.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80743_ShortDesc", "A shelved piece of furniture")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80743_LongDesc", "Often made of wood and featuring shelves and doors, cupboards are places to stow dishware or even display certain ornaments or property.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80744_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier made in the Stygian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80744_LongDesc", "This small brazier is commonly found in Stygian temples of Set.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80745_ShortDesc", "A heavy iron cauldron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80745_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the ivory throne-seat Tascela lolled. Bronze bowls of incense rolled their spirals about her; the wisps of smoke curled about her naked limbs like caressing fingers.</> - Red Nails

The humble cauldron is conventionally used by chefs to create meals.  However, the versatility of the cauldron means that it is also sought after by alchemists and sorcerers who concoct strange experiments.

This cauldron, however, has seen better days and now only serves a purpose as an ornamental piece.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80746_ShortDesc", "A decorative tea pot")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80746_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He was a magician from far Khitai, returning to his native kingdom after a journey to Stygia. He took me with him to purple-towered Paikang, its minarets rising amid the vine-festooned jungles of bamboo, and there I grew to womanhood under his teaching.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nThis tea pot is purely decorative.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80747_ShortDesc", "A piece of Stygian earthenware")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80747_LongDesc", "These jars are sought after by merchants for their light weight and compact size. They usually contain rare ingredients such as lotus honey.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80748_ShortDesc", "A Stygian metal jug")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80748_LongDesc", "These jars are sought after by merchants for their light weight and compact size. They usually contain rare ingredients such as lotus honey.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80749_ShortDesc", "A stygian instrument")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80749_LongDesc", "Typically found on board Stygian slave ships, the designs for these drums have seemingly made it into the sweltering desert.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80750_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier made in the Stygian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80750_LongDesc", "This small brazier is commonly found in Stygian temples of Set.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80751_ShortDesc", "A bronze gong mounted on a wooden frame")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80751_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Startingly, shockingly in the slumberous stillness, there had boomed the deep strident clangor of a great gong!</> - Jewels of Gwahlur

The clamor of gongs ringing from the temples of a hundred different deities rouses the common folk of Hyboria from sleep each morning. 
Gongs are used mainly for ceremony in temples while noblemen use gongs to summon servants to obey their whims.

It is rumored that in far Khitai, gongs are used to summon the spirits of the ancestors, or drive them forth into the night.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80752_ShortDesc", "A huge warhorn mounted on a wooden frame")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80752_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">So she lay without conscious thought or motion, while outside the drums bellowed, the horns clamored, and barbaric voices lifted hideous chants, keeping time to naked feet slapping the hard earth and open palms smiting one another softly.</> - The Vale of Lost Women

The call to battle is often sounded on small horns carried by cavalry. During a battle these horns are used to communicate and rally the troops.

This horn however, is enormous, and can only be used with defense in mind. The one who winds this horn is sending an intimidating message to their enemies - I am here, come and take me if you can.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80753_ShortDesc", "Wind chimes crafted of human bones")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80753_LongDesc", "The cannibal tribes of Darfar have developed a unique mechanism to warn them against the sandstorms that occasionally sweep through their lands. These wind chimes, made from the bones of humans, begin to chime when the wind picks up. If a sandstorm is coming, the noise of the chimes becomes impossible to ignore.\nWhen the wind moves sluggishly through the Darfari camps, however, the chimes create an eerie, ghostly music. Perhaps this unsettling tune contributes to the unsettling reputation of the Darfari.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80754_ShortDesc", "A drum crafted in Darfari style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80754_LongDesc", "When the throbbing of the drums begins in the darkness that covers the Exiled Lands, men and women hide in terror. Around their firepits, the devotees of Yog are preparing for a hunt.\nThe cannibalistic rituals of the Darfari are always accompanied by the beating of these skin-covered drums. A wise man does not look too closely at the pale leather that covers the drums, nor question where it was obtained. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80755_ShortDesc", "Wind chimes crafted of human bones")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80755_LongDesc", "The cannibal tribes of Darfar have developed a unique mechanism to warn them against the sandstorms that occasionally sweep through their lands. These wind chimes, made from the bones of humans, begin to chime when the wind picks up. If a sandstorm is coming, the noise of the chimes becomes impossible to ignore.\nWhen the wind moves sluggishly through the Darfari camps, however, the chimes create an eerie, ghostly music. Perhaps this unsettling tune contributes to the unsettling reputation of the Darfari.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80756_ShortDesc", "A low divan made in the Stygian style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80756_LongDesc", "Both couch and bed, the divan probably originated in Vendhya or Turan, but it rapidly became popular in the kingdom of Stygia. The most elaborate of divans are made of silk and gold inlaid ebony, but they can also be made from simple materials.\nStygian nobles are often portrayed as indolent and decadent and imagery of them lounging on divans, eating and drinking, has contributed to this portrayal. In practicality, during the hottest hours of the day all Stygians retire to their houses for leisure time and these rumors are probably spread by foreign merchants frustrated with a culture that doesn\'t follow their schedule.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point until it is destroyed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80757_ShortDesc", "A carved statue to Ymir")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80757_LongDesc", "While individual Nordheimer clans may worship different minor deities, Ymir is considered the chief of all gods. The god of Storm and War is said to send his daughter Atali to fetch the souls of dead and dying warriors to fill the halls of Valhalla.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80758_ShortDesc", "A huge warhorn mounted on a wooden frame")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80758_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">So she lay without conscious thought or motion, while outside the drums bellowed, the horns clamored, and barbaric voices lifted hideous chants, keeping time to naked feet slapping the hard earth and open palms smiting one another softly.</> - The Vale of Lost Women

The call to battle is often sounded on small horns carried by cavalry. During a battle these horns are used to communicate and rally the troops.
This horn however, is enormous, and can only be used with defence in mind. The one who winds this horn is sending an intimidating message to their enemies I am here, come and take me if you can.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80759_ShortDesc", "A stick of incense that burns to sweeten the air")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80759_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Smoke and exotic scent of incense floated up from a brazier on a golden tripod, and behind it sat an idol on a sort of marble couch.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Incense is often associated with religious ceremonies. It is burned to honor the memory of brave spirits, to create a miasma of mystery in the shrines of the gods and to cleanse the scent of the dead upon a funeral pyre.

Good tavern keepers will keep a supply near the latrine, to keep the smell from ruining the appetite of their guests. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80760_ShortDesc", "A decorative drinking horn")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80760_LongDesc", "Usually drinking horns are hollowed out and filled with liquid, but the crafter of this particular horn was lazy, so it is just for show. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80761_ShortDesc", "A decorative drinking horn")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80761_LongDesc", "Usually drinking horns are hollowed out and filled with liquid, but the crafter of this particular horn was lazy, so it is just for show. They did take the time to polish the ivory though.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80762_ShortDesc", "A huge ivory warhorn mounted on a wooden frame")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80762_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">So she lay without conscious thought or motion, while outside the drums bellowed, the horns clamored, and barbaric voices lifted hideous chants, keeping time to naked feet slapping the hard earth and open palms smiting one another softly.</> - The Vale of Lost Women

The call to battle is often sounded on small horns carried by cavalry. During a battle these horns are used to communicate and rally the troops.

This horn however, is enormous, and can only be used with defense in mind. The one who winds this horn is sending an intimidating message to their enemies - I am here, come and take me if you can.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80763_ShortDesc", "A rack for displaying crossed weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80763_LongDesc", "Boastful warriors and craftsman alike enjoy adorning their strongholds with the weapons of their conquered foes.\n\nHumbler heroes still find such display racks useful, not least for being able to store weapons in places where they would otherwise seem out of place.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80764_ShortDesc", "A pedestal for displaying a single weapon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80764_LongDesc", "Boastful warriors and craftsman alike enjoy adorning their strongholds with the weapons of their conquered foes.\n\nHumbler heroes still find such pedestals useful, not least for being able to store weapons in places where they would otherwise seem out of place.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80765_ShortDesc", "A simple tent")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80765_LongDesc", "The Zuagir, a tribe of shemite nomads who roam the sands from Zamora to Zamboula, created these tents as a rather novel way to ride out the sandstorms which sweep the deserts of Hyboria.

Made of woven camel-hair, these tents are deployed quickly and with little fuss and are actually quite a comfortable place to ride out a sandstorm.

Sandstorms in the Exiled Lands contain more than just wind-blown sand and flying fragments. There are darker terrors against which woven camelhair may not prove particularly effective.

Once a tent is placed, gaining shelter is a simple as crouching inside it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80766_ShortDesc", "A sailcloth tent made in the Black Hand style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80766_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand may be aggressive, disgusting, pirates, but like all good sailors they know their way around a needle and thread.\n\nDuring their time in the Exiled Lands, they have devised several different designs for their tents using little more than sailcloth, sturdy branches and a few lengths of stout rope.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80767_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand may be aggressive, disgusting, pirates, but like all good sailors they know their way around a needle and thread.\n\nDuring their time in the Exiled Lands, they have devised several different designs for their tents using little more than sailcloth, sturdy branches and a few lengths of stout rope.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80770_ShortDesc", "A large, shabby shadecloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80770_LongDesc", "This motheaten shadecloth has seen better days. But shade is shade.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80771_ShortDesc", "A small, shabby shadecloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80771_LongDesc", "This motheaten shadecloth has seen better days. But shade is shade.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80772_ShortDesc", "A small awning of blue cloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80772_LongDesc", "Among the great bazaars of Khemi, merchants use awnings such as this to protect their wares from the harsh Stygian sun.\nBy their nature, these awnings are made to be taken up and down quickly. They are not particularly robust, but they do offer shade when needed.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80773_LongDesc", "Among the great bazaars of Khemi, merchants use awnings such as this to protect their wares from the harsh Stygian sun.\nBy their nature, these awnings are made to be taken up and down quickly. They are not particularly robust, but they do offer shade when needed.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80774_LongDesc", "Among the great bazaars of Khemi, merchants use awnings such as this to protect their wares from the harsh Stygian sun.\nBy their nature, these awnings are made to be taken up and down quickly. They are not particularly robust, but they do offer shade when needed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80811_ShortDesc", "A simple wooden ladder")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80811_LongDesc", "Somewhere, far from the Exiled Lands, a scholar sits writing frantically. His master has given him the task of writing hundreds of descriptions of mundane items, from swords and armor, to plant fiber and stones. He glances at the next item on his list. Ladder. 

He stops, sets his quill down and looks at his reflection in a nearby mirror. He is a man grown old before his time, a slave in all but name to his masters. 

'What am I doing', he wonders. His life is a series of decisions that he almost didn't recognize that he was making.  As his thoughts spiral into the past and as he traces that inevitable trajectory backwards he realizes that there was no single point, no decision that brought him to this point. It was an accumulation of decisions across his entire lifespan, building around him like sand in the desert that leaves him living a life of quiet desperation, drowning slowly as the quicksand fills his throat.

As the realization hits him, he feels a vast sadness, an aching in his soul that he could have been so much more than simply this. A single, crystalline tear seeps from his eye and drips down onto the parchment he is working on, blurring the ink.

Resolving to make more of this life, the man stands, pushing aside his parchment, and moving to the door.

Which bursts open and, before the surprised scribe can even gasp, he is run through by a wild-eyed thief who has crept into the mansion in search of valuables.

The thief wipes his knife on the dead scholar's clothing, and glances around the room. His gaze wanders across the parchment on the table, filled with a list of items and descriptions written in the neat hand of the deceased scholar. He grins, and reaches for the quill.

Later, when the guards find the dead scholar, lying facefirst in a mingled pool of blood and ink, they will be briefly distracted by the bizarre message scratched into the parchment beside the word ladder. It simply reads: "Something you climb, idiot".

The guards shrug. Nobody really cares about the text anyway.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80851_ShortDesc", "A wooden box for storing items")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80851_LongDesc", "Somewhere to place excess items and materials, this box is made from simple materials. It can be locked against strangers, but a determined thief will be able to smash it open and take what they please.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80852_ShortDesc", "A large chest for storing items")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80852_LongDesc", "Somewhere to place excess items and materials, this chest is made from sturdy materials. It can be locked against strangers, and all but the most determined thief will be deterred. No system is perfect, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80853_ShortDesc", "A vault for storing valuable items")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80853_LongDesc", "This vault, made from steel and iron, represents the most secure location to store excess items and materials. Breaking into this vault will require a heroic effort.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80901_ShortDesc", "A ceramic vase of explosive powder")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80901_LongDesc", "Originally created in Khitai for use in fireworks, enterprising warriors and merchants soon saw the value of using this explosive powder in warfare.\nThe jars are prepared, filled with the powder and carefully sealed against the air. The very touch of air is enough to ignite the powder yet each jar comes with a fuse that can be lit for a delayed detonation.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80911_ShortDesc", "An iron trap for capturing medium sized animals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80911_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The jaws of an iron trap had closed on his leg, with teeth that sank deep and held. Only the ridged muscles of his calf saved the bone from being splintered.</> - Red Nails

These traps were originally conceived by noblemen in Zingara to prevent human poachers from trespassing on their estate. The effectiveness of the traps was legendary and it wasn't very long until the traps were being used by hunters across the western kingdoms to capture animals.

When the jaws close on the hapless creature, it is stuck fast, unable to move until it is freed from the trap. Iron and steel traps are in special demand due to the ability to reuse them almost immediately.

This trap is only effective on medium sized animals and humanoids.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80912_ShortDesc", "A pressure sensitive floor panel that releases sharpened spikes")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80912_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Not the Grey Lotus, this time, but something just as effective. Nearly every chamber in my house is a trap.</> - Rogues in the House

Honest people defend their homes with stout walls and strength of arms. But devious people know that once a wall is breached, their enemy will be off guard. There are many traps that can be concealed within the walls and floor of a keep and thieves and conquerors alike would do well to keep their wits about them.

Nabonidus, the Red Priest, is rumoured to have filled his mansion with traps to kill the assassins and thieves which came to rob him of life and loot respectively. Ultimately they proved ineffective, as he was found murdered in his own mansion one morning, just inches from the trigger to one of his own traps.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80913_ShortDesc", "A wooden trap for capturing small animals")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80913_LongDesc", "This small trap is useful for capturing game and other small animals. It is not strong enough to keep anything larger than a rabbit pinned for very long.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80914_ShortDesc", "A trap that releases a damaging vapor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80914_LongDesc", "Filled with a viscous, clinging vapor that eats the lungs and makes breathing impossible, this deadly trap is used by merchants in Zamora to discourage thieves. It is even proof against the sandstorm masks commonly crafted by desert tribesman to keep out sand particles - evidently the gas is able to seep into the masks regardless.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80915_ShortDesc", "An exploding jar that can be buried")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80915_LongDesc", "Originally created in Khitai for use in fireworks, enterprising warriors and merchants soon saw the value of using this explosive powder in warfare.\nOne enterprising Nemedian merchant thought that surrounding his mansion with a ring of explosive jars buried in the earth, their lids rigged with a special trigger, would deter would-be thieves from stealing over his walls. When his favorite hunting hound triggered the trap and knocked down half of the wall around his mansion, the merchant sold the details of the trigger mechanism to a blacksmith and left the estate behind.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80945_ShortDesc", "A pleasure temple dedicated to the goddess Derketo")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80945_LongDesc", "Derketo is a fertility goddess and she is worshipped for her ability to grant bounteous crops and good calving seasons. Her rituals, however, involved deviant orgies that can last for weeks and include necrophilia and bestiality.\n\nHer places of worship are therefore chosen for comfort, style, and the freeing of inhibitions. They are places where life and death intertwine like a pair of lovers. Those who visit the pleasure places of Derketo are reminded what it is to live and die - and how pleasurable both can be.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80948_ShortDesc", "A place for worshipping Jhebbal Sag")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80948_LongDesc", "Though the Lord of Beasts prefers natural locations for his sacred groves, it is understood that men no longer live in the deep wilds of the world. Thus, the altars of Jhebbal Sag tend to be built of crude stone and hacked into a basic likeness. Too much polish would be reminiscent of man without the component of the beast. Too little polish would alienate mankind.\n\nThough Jhebbal Sag rarely visits such altars, he will receive sacrifices made here and eventually provide the power to manifest his avatar.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80951_ShortDesc", "A shrine to Set, the Old Serpent")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80951_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Ships did not put unasked into this port, where dusky sorcerers wove awful spells in the murk of sacrificial smoke mounting eternally from blood-stained altars where naked women screamed, and where Set, the Old Serpent, arch-demon of the Hyborians but god of the Stygians, was said to writhe his shining coils among his worshippers.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Created as a focal point for the worship of Set, this pristine shrine will not remain so for long. 

The hunger of Set requires human sacrifice and the altars of Set regularly run with blood.

Altars can also be used to perform rituals of creation - placing certain items on the altar can invoke the blessings of the gods.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80952_ShortDesc", "An altar to Set, the Old Serpent")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80952_LongDesc", "Created as a focal point for the worship of Set, this pristine altar will not remain so for long. \nThe hunger of Set requires human sacrifice and the altars of Set regularly run with blood.\nAltars can also be used to perform rituals of creation - placing certain items on the altar can invoke the blessings of the gods.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80961_ShortDesc", "A sacrifice pit made for the glory of Yog")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80961_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Somewhere near by had been the pit, dark and awful, wherein screaming victims were fed to a nameless amorphic monstrosity which came up out of a deeper, more hellish cavern.</> - Black Colossus

The altars of Yog are crude sacrifice pits, lined with spikes and stones. Victims are hauled up to a rough stone platform and then uncerimonously booted into the pit. 

When the victim has finished shrieking, the worshippers of Yog gather and partake of the purified flesh.

It is said that the blessing of Yog falls upon anything within the pit. It is not uncommon to meet Yoggites who have smeared themselves with ashes from their sacrifice pits and decorated themselves with the bones of their victims.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80962_ShortDesc", "A sacrifice pit made for the glory of Yog")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80962_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">At the edge of the desert, beyond the houses, there is a clump of palm trees, and within that grove there is a pit. And within that pit have been found human bones, charred and blackened. Not once, but many times!</> - Shadows in Zamboula

The altars of Yog are crude sacrifice pits, lined with spikes and stones. Victims are hauled up to a rough stone platform and then uncerimonously booted into the pit. 

When the victim has finished shrieking, the worshippers of Yog gather and partake of the purified flesh.

It is said that the blessing of Yog falls upon anything within the pit. It is not uncommon to meet Yoggites who have smeared themselves with ashes from their sacrifice pits and decorated themselves with the bones of their victims.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80963_ShortDesc", "A sacrifice pit made for the glory of Yog")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80963_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He understood now the mystery of the strangers who had disappeared from the house of Aram Baksh; the riddle of the black drum thrumming out there beyond the palm groves, and of that pit of charred bones - that pit where strange meat might be roasted under the stars, while black beasts squatted about to glut a hideous hunger.</> - Shadows in Zamboula

The altars of Yog are crude sacrifice pits, lined with spikes and stones. Victims are hauled up to a rough stone platform and then uncerimonously booted into the pit. 

When the victim has finished shrieking, the worshippers of Yog gather and partake of the purified flesh.

It is said that the blessing of Yog falls upon anything within the pit. It is not uncommon to meet Yoggites who have smeared themselves with ashes from their sacrifice pits and decorated themselves with the bones of their victims.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80971_ShortDesc", "A holy shrine dedicated to the worship of Mitra")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80971_LongDesc", "Considered a good god, Mitra is worshipped throughout the Hyborian kings, replacing the worship of Bori from which those primitive tribes took their name.

Mitra's symbol is that of the phoenix, but when he is depicted it is in the form of a well built, bearded man. He abhors the bloody rituals of other religions and prefers for his followers to perform dignified, purification rituals.

Mitra's priests preach a monotheistic doctrine and as such their followers tend to persecute the members of other nearby religions. Due to this tendency, Chapels to Mitra cannot be built within a very long range of shrines to other gods.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80974_ShortDesc", "A place of sacrifice to Ymir, the Frost Giant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80974_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The clangor of the swords had died away, the shouting of the slaughter was hushed; silence lay on the red-stained snow. The bleak pale sun that glittered so blindingly from the ice-fields and the snow-covered plains struck sheens of silver from rent corselet and broken blade, where the dead lay as they had fallen. The nerveless hand yet gripped the broken hilt; helmeted heads back-drawn in the death-throes, tilted red beards and golden beards grimly upward, as if in last invocation to Ymir the frost-giant, god of a warrior-race...</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nIt is said that the battlefield is truly Ymir\'s altar. The war god does not want murdered sacrifices so much as beautiful deaths during the din of glorious combat. Yet those most devoted to the Lord of Storm and War still find themselves constructing places where they can directly commune with their god through the medium of spilt blood. On the cold winds of deadly winter, one might hear the grinding whisper of the Father of Giants saying, \'You get what you give.\'")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80975_ShortDesc", "A statue in the image of Mitra that pours forth water")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80975_LongDesc", "Through the mysteries of Mitra it is possible to call water to well forth eternally. This affirmation of Mitra\'s power is marred somewhat by those who claim that the worshippers of Mitra only build these over pre-existing streams.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80976_ShortDesc", "A statue in the image of Mitra that radiates holy light")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80976_LongDesc", "It is said that the lights on these statues will burn eternally as long as Mitra has a single faithful follower. It can be argued, of course, that a single faithful follower of Mitra would also keep the light burning to perpetuate the mysteries of Mitra and therefore create a paradox which has theologians everywhere going to sleep each night with a sore head.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80986_ShortDesc", "A cooked, rare fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80986_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">It takes an Argossean merchant to wring wealth out of a little waterfront shop that stank of rotten fish and cheap wine.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe bounty of the rivers and seas are a major food source for many peoples in Hyboria. Such fare may be prepared by roasting, boiling, and many other methods besides.")

Such fare may be prepared by roasting, boiling, and many other methods besides.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80991_ShortDesc", "A rare fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80991_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is harvested from small fish not known for being good eating. It is not particularly filling or flavorful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80996_ShortDesc", "A dried and stuffed fish mounted on a wooden plack")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80996_LongDesc", "Fishermen often keep their most memorable catch as a trophy. Some are kept for the memories, others to impress, and yet others are kept for the sole reason of having something on the wall. Looking at this piece, you cannot help but wonder what reason could possibly be behind this one.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81019_ShortDesc", "An extremely long and ancient polearm")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81019_LongDesc", "When this weapon was recovered from the body of the King Below, it had adjusted in size to fit human hands. Clearly magical in nature, the haft of the polearm is engraved with the runes that give it the name, Kingslayer.

The oddly shaped blade makes it more like a long-handled sword than a spear, yet it is balanced perfectly in the hands, as if eager to seek blood.

Whatever the story of this weapon, it will be an asset to those who wish to rule the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81020_ShortDesc", "An extremely sharp pair of ancient daggers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81020_LongDesc", "When these weapon were recovered from the body of the King Below, they had adjusted in size to fit human hands. Clearly magical in nature, the handle of the dagger is engraved with the runes that give it the name, Kingslayer.\n\nWhatever the story of this weapon, it will be an asset to those who wish to rule the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_83007_ShortDesc", "A furnace for smelting metals and stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_83007_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Logs flamed in the wide fireplace, for there was a frosty edge to the air, and a great meat pasty in a stone platter stood smoking on a broad mahogany board.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nDesigned to heat ore to incredibly high temperatures in order to extract pure metals, furnaces require fuels such as coal or wood and ores for processing and catalysts such as Steelfire for strengthening. Intense heat can also be used to harden certain types of stone and a furnace can be used in conjunction with other concoctions to create hardened stone bricks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88884_ShortDesc", "A pile of bones")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88884_LongDesc", "There is something disconcerting about these bones.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88885_ShortDesc", "A pile of bones")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88885_LongDesc", "There is something disconcerting about these bones.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88887_ShortDesc", "A skull impaled on a stake")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88887_LongDesc", "There is something disconcerting about the grinning skull attached to this stake. Though the eye sockets are hollow and the skin and flesh have been long since scoured from the bones, it still appears to be watchful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88890_ShortDesc", "This is a skull taken from a dead enemy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88890_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the dead rise to fight once again. Perhaps they rise due to the long forgotten command of a necromancer. Perhaps they rise to the singing of a song that the living cannot hear. \nWhatever wakes them, they must still be put to sleep once more.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88891_ShortDesc", "The shell from a Shaleback Hatchling")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88891_LongDesc", "This shell, taken from a Shaleback Hatchling, is brittle and easily chipped. It cannot be used to make weapons or armor nor is it useful for potions or food. Essentially a baby Shaleback was killed for no reason. Way to go.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88892_ShortDesc", "A warning sign as good as any.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88892_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the dead rise to fight once again. Perhaps they rise due to the long forgotten command of a necromancer. Perhaps they rise to the singing of a song that the living cannot hear. \nWhatever wakes them, they must still be put to sleep once more.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88893_ShortDesc", "A totem of Vanir design")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88893_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\"> \'Who are you to swear by Ymir?\' she mocked. \'What know you of the gods of ice and snow, you who have come up from the south to adventure among an alien people?\'</> - Gods of the North\n\nWhile individual Nordheimer clans may worship different minor deities, Ymir is considered the chief of all gods. The god of Storm and War is said to send his daughter Atali to fetch the souls of dead and dying warriors to fill the halls of Valhalla.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88897_LongDesc", "Shaped of clay and fired in a kiln, jugs are used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88898_LongDesc", "Shaped of clay and fired in a kiln, jugs are used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88899_ShortDesc", "A placeable divider for the easily embarrased")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88899_LongDesc", "While noone would claim Stygians are easily embarrased, some  visitors to the brothels in Khem may wish for some privacy. While the folding screens do not muffle the screams of what goes on behind them, they do obscure the line of sight.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88900_ShortDesc", "A wooden table of Stygian design")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88900_LongDesc", "Tables vary in shape and size, materials and decoration based on the culture and craftsmanship of their maker.\nThis one is a wooden circle.\nThe artisan was probably hoping to decorate the table with dozens of interesting objects and thereby distract from the lack of imagination in the creation of the table itself.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88901_ShortDesc", "A round wooden table")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88901_LongDesc", "Tables vary in shape and size, materials and decoration based on the culture and craftsmanship of their maker.\nThis one is a wooden circle.\nThe artisan was probably hoping to decorate the table with dozens of interesting objects and thereby distract from the lack of imagination in the creation of the table itself.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88902_ShortDesc", "A rack for displaying weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88902_LongDesc", "Boastful warriors and craftsman alike enjoy adorning their strongholds with the weapons of their conquered foes.\n\nHumbler heroes still find such display racks useful, not least for being able to store weapons in places where they would otherwise seem out of place.")
