column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88904_LongDesc", "Boastful warriors and craftsman alike enjoy adorning their strongholds with the weapons of their conquered foes.\n\nHumbler heroes still find such display racks useful, not least for being able to store weapons in places where they would otherwise seem out of place.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89001_ShortDesc", "A small campfire for cooking and keeping warm")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89001_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Lie here.' He indicated a clean-swept space close to a small flickering fire. He saw no incongruity in a princess lying down on the naked ground beside a campfire, wrapped in a warrior's cloak.</> - Black Colossus

The campfire is an adventurers best friend when the nights turn cold and the darkness presses in all around. Made from simple branches and twigs, the campfire is an excellent source of light and heat.

Campfires can be used to cook meat which is important given the number of parasites that infect the wild animals of the Exiled Lands. Better to eat some burned meat, than be poisoned for days.

With the light of a campfire, however, comes visibility. Wary travelers would do well to hide their fires, lest they be ambushed in the night by men with unsavory intentions.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89010_ShortDesc", "A large bonfire")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89010_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">They camped that night on the northern slopes of those hills, and hook-nosed, fiery-eyed men of the hill tribes came in scores to squat about the fires and repeat news that had come up out of the mysterious desert. </>- Black Colossus\n\nBuilt of large pieces of wood, the bonfire is a blazing beacon in the night. Bonfires give off more light and heat than their lesser relative, the campfire, which can be an advantage if the priority is to remain warm, or a disadvantage if the priority is to remain hidden.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89011_ShortDesc", "A  large campfire for cooking and keeping warm")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89011_LongDesc", "The campfire is an adventurers best friend when the nights turn cold and the darkness presses in all around.\nCampfires can be used to cook meat - which is important given the number of parasites that infect the wild animals of the Exiled Lands. Better to eat some burned meat, than be poisoned for days.\nWith the light of a campfire, however, comes visibility.  A fire this large is very difficult to hide.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89101_ShortDesc", "A furnace for smelting metals and stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89101_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Logs flamed in the wide fireplace, for there was a frosty edge to the air, and a great meat pasty in a stone platter stood smoking on a broad mahogany board.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nDesigned to heat ore to incredibly high temperatures in order to extract pure metals, furnaces require fuels such as coal or wood and ores for processing and catalysts such as Steelfire for strengthening. Intense heat can also be used to harden certain types of stone and a furnace can be used in conjunction with other concoctions to create hardened stone bricks.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89102_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Logs flamed in the wide fireplace, for there was a frosty edge to the air, and a great meat pasty in a stone platter stood smoking on a broad mahogany board.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nDesigned to heat ore to incredibly high temperatures in order to extract pure metals, furnaces require fuels such as coal or wood and ores for processing and catalysts such as Steelfire for strengthening. Intense heat can also be used to harden certain types of stone and a furnace can be used in conjunction with other concoctions to create hardened stone bricks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89103_ShortDesc", "A cauldron for mixing concoctions")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89103_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the ivory throne-seat Tascela lolled. Bronze bowls of incense rolled their spirals about her; the wisps of smoke curled about her naked limbs like caressing fingers.</> - Red Nails

The humble cauldron is conventionally used by chefs to create meals.  However, the versatility of the cauldron means that it is also sought after by alchemists and sorcerers who concoct strange experiments.

Smelting catalysts such as Steelfire, can only be created by an alchemist who knows the particular combination of ingredients.

This particular type of cauldron was first used commonly in Vendhya.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89104_ShortDesc", "A tannery for processing hides into leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89104_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were young men, but hard and sinewy, with a bearing that comes only to men rendered desperate by adversity. They were clad in mail shirts and worn leather; swords hung at their girdles.</> - A Witch Shall be Born

The stench of the tannery is easily identifiable in the major cities of the world and tanners are often relegated to the outskirts of cities or villages, preferably downstream. 

Bark is the most common form of tannin used to convert hide into leather. During the process it breaks down into Tar, which is a useful catalyst for alchemists.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89201_ShortDesc", "A bench covered in tools for crafting armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89201_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">With the firelight glinting from his blue steel armor, he seemed like an image of steel - dynamic power for the moment quiescent; not resting, but motionless for the instant, awaiting the signal to plunge again into terrific action.</> - Black Colossus\n\nCreating armor, particularly metal armor, requires a large number of exotic tools. This armormaking bench can be used to create anything from the lightest leather armor to hardened steel armor. Provided that the raw materials are available, of course.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89301_ShortDesc", "A bench covered in tools for shaping metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89301_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">That is to say, they had learned to work crudely in copper and tin, which were found scantily in their country, and for which latter metal they raided into the mountains of Zingara, or traded hides, whale's teeth, walrus tusks and such few things as savages have to trade.</>- The Hyborian Age

Smithing is a well-known and oft-used profession in the Hyborian kingdoms. In the larger cities and towns, smiths are forced to join guilds that offer them a certain amount of political protection, while enforcing a rigorous set of standards of work and tools.

This bench contains many of the tools that smiths need, but in the Exiled Lands, there are no standards to be enforced.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89302_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">That is to say, they had learned to work crudely in copper and tin, which were found scantily in their country, and for which latter metal they raided into the mountains of Zingara, or traded hides, whale's teeth, walrus tusks and such few things as savages have to trade.</>- The Hyborian Age

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89401_ShortDesc", "A bench covered in tools for carpentry")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89401_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Our merciful sovereign offers you one more chance, Countess,\" said the tallest of the three, and he spoke Aquilonian without an accent. \"He bids me say that if you soften your proud, rebellious spirit, he will still open his arms to you. If not-\' he gestured toward a grim wooden block in the center of the cell. It was blackly stained, and showed many deep nicks as if a keen edge, cutting through some yielding substance, had sunk into the wood.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe ability to work wood is a useful skill for anybody interested in creating buildings and furniture. This bench is covered with all of the implements that one needs to create anything from houses to chairs.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89801_ShortDesc", "A foundation for building siege equipment")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89801_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He had sent his light riders, his spahis, inland to ravage the country, and had reared up his siege engines in the plain.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This foundation is designed to be a reinforced base for building siege engines that require stability as they are fired.

Siege engines require immense amounts of labor to craft and maintain. They are expensive to transport, and the working parts break often, requiring constant supervision.

It is undoubted, however, that beneath the gods themselves, they are one of the most powerful weapons available to any army.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89811_ShortDesc", "A rotating base for a trebuchet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89811_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the landward side mangonels rained boulders and tree-trunks among the defenders, shattering through roofs and crushing humans like beetles; rams pounded incessantly at the stones; sappers burrowed like moles in the earth, sinking their mines beneath the towers.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This base piece of the trebuchet, once placed on a siege foundation, can be upgraded with a  frame to reach full functionality.

In the so-called civilized kingdoms of Hyboria, nobles build great palaces with walls of mighty stone to protect themselves from their enemies at court and abroad. 

The solution to sturdy walls and cowardly nobility is the steadfast trebuchet. A machine of immense power, the trebuchet can be used to fling stones, corpses and even specially designed explosives.

Their weakness is their immobility, they cannot be easily moved once placed and finding the correct range and angle requires time and patience. With repeated use, it is almost certain that some or all of the pieces of the trebuchet will degrade and need to be replaced.")

column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89852_ShortDesc", "Ammunition for the trebuchet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89852_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They pushed on grimly, over soil charred and blackened, where the naked rock had in places been turned to lava by the explosion of those diabolical bombs.</> - People of the Black Circle

Using similar ingredients to those found in Kothic Demon-fire, this explosive barrage is designed to melt the very stones that it explodes upon, slowly burning all caught in its wrath.

It is expensive to create, however, and those who use it in battle earn a reputation for ruthlessness and unusual cruelty.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89911_ShortDesc", "A wheel that strengthens the body as it breaks the mind")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89911_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He did not care anymore. Life and death... the same.</> - Conan the Barbarian \n\nThis wheel is based on a design that originally comes from the mountains and valleys of Vanaheim. It is unclear whether it serves any purpose other than to keep prisoners passive and exhausted until they can be used for more productive tasks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90000_ShortDesc", "A map showing the ancient kingdom of the Giant-kings")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90000_LongDesc", "This room is a copy of the maproom that exists beneath the Unnamed City. In times past, the Giant-kings used sorcery to quickly move their slaves around their kingdom, attuning their bracelets to different areas and then using the map room to get there.

While the terrain is slightly different, owing to the eons that have passed since the creation of the original map, this map room still retains the ability to quickly send anybody with a bracelet to one of the attuned obelisks.

It is speculated that in the dim past, the obelisks served as a form of permission for slaves - the more trusted the slave, the more access to obelisks. Now, it is simply a matter of finding them, wherever they are.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90001_ShortDesc", "A square foundation piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90001_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting sandstone buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90002_ShortDesc", "A square wall piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90002_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90003_ShortDesc", "A square ceiling piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90003_LongDesc", "It is said that nobody is truly home until they have a roof over their head. Across the civilizations of Hyboria, rooves are made from a diverse number of materials from clay-fired tiles warmed in the kilns of Agarapar to the roughly thatched rooves of the Nordheimers. 
In the Exiled Lands, however, materials are limited. Something to keep the sandstorms at bay and the bat demons from swooping down and snatching people while they sleep is probably good enough.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90004_ShortDesc", "A doorframe made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90004_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.
A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.
The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90005_ShortDesc", "Stairs of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90005_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90006_ShortDesc", "A wedge shaped piece of sandstone ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90006_LongDesc", "Wedge shaped building pieces allow greater flexibility in the shapes available to builders.\nCobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.\nDespite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90007_ShortDesc", "A sandstone wall with space for a window")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90007_LongDesc", "Windows provide great vantage points for archers without forcing them to leave the safety of stout walls.\nCobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.\nDespite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90008_ShortDesc", "A simple wooden door")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90008_LongDesc", "Created from the most basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this simple wooden door offers access to friends and denies it to foes.\nThe wood has aged in the desert sun and will not be strong enough to hold out determined foes, but it will keep the weather outside.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90009_ShortDesc", "A pillar made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90009_LongDesc", "Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90010_ShortDesc", "A fence piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90010_LongDesc", "Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. 
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90024_ShortDesc", "A sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90024_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90069_ShortDesc", "Stairs of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90069_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90070_ShortDesc", "Stairs made of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90070_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90071_ShortDesc", "A staircase made of reinforced stone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90071_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Reinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90101_ShortDesc", "A square-shaped Stonebrick foundation")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90101_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90102_ShortDesc", "A wall of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90102_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90103_ShortDesc", "A ceiling piece of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90103_LongDesc", "It is said that nobody is truly home until they have a roof over their head. Across the civilizations of Hyboria, rooves are made from a diverse number of materials - from clay-fired tiles warmed in the kilns of Agarapar to the roughly thatched rooves of the Nordheimers. 
In the Exiled Lands, however, materials are limited. Something to keep the sandstorms at bay and the bat demons from swooping down and snatching people while they sleep is probably good enough.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90104_ShortDesc", "A doorframe of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90104_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.
A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.
The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90106_ShortDesc", "A wedge shaped piece of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90106_LongDesc", "Wedges are used to expand the possibilities of a building.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90107_ShortDesc", "A frame made of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90107_LongDesc", "This is a wall with some stones removed to create space for a window. Useful for letting in natural light and keeping an eye on the surroundings.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90108_ShortDesc", "A door of reinforced wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90108_LongDesc", "Shaped wooden planks reinforced with iron bands are used to create this solid door. While providing access, this door also provides significant protection against intruders.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90109_ShortDesc", "A pillar made of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90109_LongDesc", "Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90110_ShortDesc", "A low fence of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90110_LongDesc", "This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. \nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90111_LongDesc", "Wedge foundations allow unique shapes to be created when building.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90120_LongDesc", "Fence foundations can be placed in locations where fences and walls are needed, but the larger foundations of a building do not need to be placed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90121_ShortDesc", "Framework for a large gate")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90121_LongDesc", "The best battle, as they say, is the one you never have to fight. With formidable enough gates, the enemies will think twice about attacking any fortress. Not simply because the scale of the gates has them concerned about getting inside, but because large gates imply large inhabitants and armies get nervous when they think they might be outnumbered.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90122_ShortDesc", "Sturdy doors to keep enemies at bay")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90122_LongDesc", "These large doors are designed to allow access for large groups of people in and out of safe areas. Raiders and bandits make walls a must have in the Exiled Lands and the protection afforded by gates such as these should not be taken for granted.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90201_ShortDesc", "A square foundation piece made of reinforced stone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90201_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Reinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90202_ShortDesc", "A wall made of reinforced stone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90202_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Reinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90203_ShortDesc", "A ceiling made of reinforced stone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90203_LongDesc", "It is said that nobody is truly home until they have a roof over their head. Across the civilizations of Hyboria, rooves are made from a diverse number of materials - from clay-fired tiles warmned in the kilns of Agarapar to the roughly thatched rooves of the Nordheimers. 
In the Exiled Lands, however, materials are limited. Something to keep the sandstorms at bay and the bat demons from swooping down and snatching people while they sleep is probably good enough.
Reinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90204_ShortDesc", "A doorframe made of reinforced stone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90204_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.
A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.
The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.
Reinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90205_ShortDesc", "A staircase made of reinforced stone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90205_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Reinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90206_LongDesc", "Wedges are used to expand the possibilities of a building.\nReinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90207_ShortDesc", "A frame made of reinforced stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90207_LongDesc", "This is a wall with some stones removed to create space for a window. Useful for letting in natural light and keeping an eye on the surroundings.\nReinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90208_ShortDesc", "A heavy door, reinforced with metal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90208_LongDesc", "One of the strongest doors that can be crafted, the heavy door offers protection against everything but the most powerful of enemy tricks.\nRaging hordes have been kept at bay by such doors and with a simple locking mechanism they become proof against incursions into structures.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90209_ShortDesc", "A pillar made of reinforced stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90209_LongDesc", "Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.\nReinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90210_ShortDesc", "A low fence made of reinforced stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90210_LongDesc", "This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. \nReinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90223_ShortDesc", "Crenelated walls for placing siege cauldrons and archers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90223_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Under the walls the mailed figures swarmed, battering at the gates, rearing up scaling-ladders, pushing storming-towers, thronged with spearmen, against the turrets.'</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The strength of walls during a siege is determined by two things - the strength of building itself and the ability of defenders to cleanly shoot enemies that are attacking.

These crenelated walls are a common design, effective at giving archers a clear space for firing on enemies as well as providing a niche for placing siege cauldrons and other defensive mechanisms.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90224_ShortDesc", "A mechanism that allows or denies access to a gate")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90224_LongDesc", "Connected to a gate, the drawbridge is designed as a defensive measure, denying approaching enemies easy access to the gate. The drawbridge is operated by a lever.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90225_ShortDesc", "A mechanism that allows vertical travel without climbing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90225_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Then, looping the loose end of his silk rope about Natala's hips, and cautioning her to hold on with both hands, he lifted her through the window and lowered her the thirty-odd feet to the earth.'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

The mechanics of creating such a machine - involving counter-weights, pulleys and other fine details - are considered sorcery by the ignorant and wisdom by the enlightened.

The practical benefits of such a machine cannot be denied, but civilized peoples who grow too reliant upon them will find that a climbing horde of barbarians can be just as effective, and infinitely more deadly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90226_ShortDesc", "A mechanism that allows horizontal travel")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90226_LongDesc", "The mechanics of creating such a machine - involving counter-weights, pulleys and other fine details - are considered sorcery by the ignorant and wisdom by the enlightened.\n\nThe practical benefits of such a machine cannot be denied, but civilized peoples who grow too reliant upon them will find that a horde of barbarians following a rope hand over hand can be just as effective, and infinitely more deadly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90227_ShortDesc", "A cauldron attached to a simple lever")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90227_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Take your plots to hell with you!' he roared, and like a sack of salt, he hurled the prince of Pellia far out, to fall through empty space for a hundred and fifty feet. The people gave back as the body came hurtling down, to smash on the marble pave, spattering blood and brains, and lie crushed in its splintered armor, like a mangled beetle.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Crafting fortifications is the beginning of a coherent siege strategy but it is the least interesting and least creative part of the equation. A good fortification includes structures that are built for a specific purpose - such as murder holes created to lure enemies through a gauntlet of deadly traps.

These siege cauldrons, filled with boiling tar, are simply another tool in the arsenal of a siege engineer. They can be used to discourage eager climbers or to wreak havoc on enemies trapped in a murder hole.")

Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Black Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90268_ShortDesc", "A wedge made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90268_LongDesc", "Wedges are used to expand the possibilities of a building.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90269_ShortDesc", "A frame made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90269_LongDesc", "This is a wall with some stones removed to create space for a window. Useful for letting in natural light and keeping an eye on the surroundings.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90270_ShortDesc", "A heavy door, reinforced with metal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90270_LongDesc", "One of the strongest doors that can be crafted, the heavy door offers protection against everything but the most powerful of enemy tricks.\nRaging hordes have been kept at bay by such doors and with a simple locking mechanism they become proof against incursions into structures.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90271_ShortDesc", "A pillar made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90271_LongDesc", "Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90272_LongDesc", "This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. \nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90280_ShortDesc", "A fence foundation of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90280_LongDesc", "Fence foundations can be placed in locations where fences and walls are needed, but the larger foundations of a building do not need to be placed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90281_ShortDesc", "Framework for a large gate")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90281_LongDesc", "The best battle, they say, is the one you never have to fight. With formidable enough gates, the enemies will think twice about attacking any fortress. Not simply because the scale of the gates has them concerned about getting inside, but because large gates imply large inhabitants and armies get nervous when they think they might be outnumbered.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90282_ShortDesc", "Sturdy doors to keep enemies at bay")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90282_LongDesc", "These large doors are designed to allow access for large groups of people in and out of safe areas. Raiders and bandits make walls a must have in the Exiled Lands and the protection afforded by gates such as these should not be taken for granted.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90283_ShortDesc", "Crenelated walls for placing siege cauldrons and archers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90283_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Under the walls the mailed figures swarmed, battering at the gates, rearing up scaling-ladders, pushing storming-towers, thronged with spearmen, against the turrets.'</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The strength of walls during a siege is determined by two things - the strength of building itself and the ability of defenders to cleanly shoot enemies that are attacking.

These crenelated walls are a common design, effective at giving archers a clear space for firing on enemies as well as providing a niche for placing siege cauldrons and other defensive mechanisms.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90284_ShortDesc", "A hatch frame made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90284_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.

A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.

The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90289_ShortDesc", "A door made to fit a hatch frame")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90289_LongDesc", "Created from the most basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this simple wooden door offers access to friends and denies it to foes.\nThe wood has aged in the desert sun and will not be strong enough to hold out determined foes, but it will keep the weather outside.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90290_ShortDesc", "A door made to fit a hatch frame")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90290_LongDesc", "Shaped wooden planks reinforced with iron bands are used to create this solid door. While providing access, this door also provides significant protection against intruders.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90294_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90294_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90295_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90295_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90323_ShortDesc", "A square-shaped Insulated Wood foundation")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90323_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Built of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90988_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90988_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well - perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn\'t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91000_ShortDesc", "A simple turban of hide and fiber")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91000_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the fierce sun beating down on the unprotected head can cause extreme delirium in a short amount of time.
Apart from protection from the sun, this turban offers a small amount of protection from attacks on the head.
Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.
Created from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91001_ShortDesc", "A light chestpiece of hide and fiber")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91001_LongDesc", "Designed to keep the wearer cool, this armor emphasizes movement and agility in combat over straight up protection.\nThe blow that misses is always better than the one that lands. In this case, the one that lands will cause a significant amount of damage due to the simple construction of this armor.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91002_ShortDesc", "A pair of flexible hide gauntlets")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91002_LongDesc", "Hide pieces bound to a soft underbody of cloth keep these gauntlets as flexible as possible while offering some protection from attacks.\nBlows to the hand can cause crippling injuries, particularly to archers who need to have all of their fingers intact if they are to draw a bow.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91003_ShortDesc", "A loose fitting cloth wrap, bound to the waist with rawhide thongs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91003_LongDesc", "This wrap allows the legs to move freely, giving full range of motion. This is particularly useful to the adventurer just beginning their journey, as it allows them to make the all-important decision of fight or flight.\nLight armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91004_ShortDesc", "A pair of sturdy boots made from cloth and hide")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91004_LongDesc", "These boots of cloth wrapped and laced in hide, provide protection and warmth for the feet.\nThere are many dangers in the Exiled Lands and the small scorpions, spiders and snakes that can strike without warning are reason enough to keep legs and feet well covered.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91005_ShortDesc", "A riveted leather cap with a facemask")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91005_LongDesc", "This leather helmet includes large cheek  and neck protectors and a facemask for filtering the sand and dust from the air.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91006_ShortDesc", "Leather spaulders riveted to articulated rerebraces")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91006_LongDesc", "The fastest way to a man\'s heart, is through his armpits\' is a common expression amongst the gladiators of Argos. Chest protection is often reinforced on the upper arms and the vulnerable areas around the armpits, rather than the central chest. Every human is already born with some natural protection over their hearts namely their ribcage and breastbone.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91007_ShortDesc", "Elbow length gauntlets of riveted leather")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91007_LongDesc", "Protecting the forearms and fingers is the primary purpose of gauntlets. The loss of a hand will cripple a warrior and the loss of fingers will cripple an archer.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91008_ShortDesc", "A leather skirt that protects the upper thighs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91008_LongDesc", "This long leather skirt is designed to protect the upper thighs from attacks while providing mobility.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91009_ShortDesc", "Calf-length riveted leather boots")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91009_LongDesc", "These boots offer good protection for the calves and feet and their sturdy construction means that they tolerate the harsh conditions for a long time.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91015_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91015_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91016_ShortDesc", "An ornate necklace of teeth over human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91016_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
This chestpiece is soft and supple, which allows for great flexibility. The teeth used in the necklace appear to be crocodile teeth, taken from the great beasts that roam the Exiled Lands.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91017_ShortDesc", "Bracers of blood-dyed leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91017_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These bracers are the color of blood and made of a soft leather wrapped with cloth. A close look reveals human molars dangling from the bindings on the gauntlets.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91018_ShortDesc", "Skirt of human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91018_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These skirt is simple and adorned with a belt of small beads and human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91019_ShortDesc", "Ankle wraps of soft leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91019_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These greaves are simple and adorned with small beads and human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91020_ShortDesc", "Shemitish turban commonly worn in the meadowland cities")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91020_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. Due to their access to these caravans, the Shemitish people often have access to the first pick of goods coming from the east - including fine silks from Khitai and brightly dyed cloth from Turan. This bounty of cloth is reflected in the loose fitting, comfortable clothing woven by the tailors of Shem.\nThis clothing is a practical bulwark against the elements but won\'t be enough to stop a blade.\n")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91021_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91024_ShortDesc", "Shemitish pointy-toed shoes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91024_LongDesc", "While these shoes are impractical for the desert, they are incredibly comfortable.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91025_ShortDesc", "A pair of bone earrings often worn by Vanir commoners")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91025_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These earrings provide no significant protection, but they are marked with clan symbols - so that if a dead settler is found, their possessions can be returned to the clan. Jokingly referred to by the Aesir as Vanearrings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91026_ShortDesc", "A fur-lined vest worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91026_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

This vest is designed to keep the settler warm, while freeing their hands for working with tools. It offers some basic protection against attacks due to its thickness, but is not as effective as true armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91027_ShortDesc", "A set of fur gloves worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91027_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These gloves are perfect for keeping the hands warm while working frozen soil.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91028_ShortDesc", "A furry breechclout worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91028_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

This breechclout  keeps the settler warm, but has an unfortunate tendency to attract fleas and lice. Vanir women are well known for their habit of bathing in freezing streams in the midst of winter, Vanir men are known for being lice-infested bastards.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91029_ShortDesc", "A pair of furry boots worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91029_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These boots keep the feet warm while stumbling through banks and drifts of snow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91030_ShortDesc", "A hood for those who work in the shadows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91030_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

Designed with the principle that the best fight is a fight avoided, this outfit allows the wearer to blend into the shadows and remain unseen in the deep shadows of the Zamorian cities. 
Whether it is as effective in the lands beyond Zamoria is another question.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91031_ShortDesc", "A leather chestpiece for those who work in the shadows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91031_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

Designed with the principle that the best fight is a fight avoided, this outfit allows the wearer to blend into the shadows and remain unseen in the deep shadows of the Zamorian cities. 

It has been wrapped tightly to dampen any noise caused by loose straps and buckles. Whether it is as effective in the lands beyond Zamoria is another question.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91032_ShortDesc", "Fingerless gloves for those who need dextrous hands")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91032_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

A thief's fingers must be free to do nimble work - manipulating lockpicks, snatching purses and slitting throats. These gloves are designed to protect the hand and forearm while freeing the fingers to do their worst.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91033_ShortDesc", "Leather leggings with a belt of useful pouches")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91033_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These leggings are designed to help, not hinder, the burgeoning burglar in their trade. Accompanied by a handy belt, full of small pouches for storing the various tools of the thieving profession, these skin tight leather pants also offer excellent protection.
 Zamorian cutthroats swear by them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91034_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots of supple leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91034_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These boots are designed to allow cutthroats easy access to their victims, damping their footsteps as they approach from behind. 
They're also surprisingly durable when fleeing the city watch.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91035_ShortDesc", "A headscarf popular among Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91035_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Freebooters attire themselves in all manner of flamboyant outfits, but the headscarf is cheap, popular and practical.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91036_ShortDesc", "A vest worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91036_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

The sturdy leather vest is designed to turn the sharp edges of a saber but will offer little protection against a well-placed thrust. Still, it is practical for those who spend their lives on ships, and never needs to be scoured for rust.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91037_ShortDesc", "A pair of gloves worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91037_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Leather gloves are practical onboard a ship - for preventing blisters, rope-burn and the occasional knife wound as well.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91038_ShortDesc", "A pair of pants worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91038_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

The sturdy leather pants offer the freedom to scamper along lines, while still being stiff enough to turn the sharp edge of a dagger. They also never need to be scoured for rust.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91039_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91039_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Leather boots are practical onboard a ship - for preventing splinters and broken toes, but also for kicking unfortunate prisoners over the side.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91040_ShortDesc", "A turban designed to protect the head from the elements")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91040_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

This turban has been refined in the time that they have spent in the Exiled Lands, offering comfort against the warm weather of the region and limited protection against the scouring sands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91041_ShortDesc", "A loose shirt favoured by relic hunters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91041_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

Still scavengers at heart, this shirt is paired with a small leather sack for storing any treasure that a relic hunter might stumble across while exploring the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91042_ShortDesc", "A set of sturdy gloves for handling relics")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91042_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

Too many foolish souls have lost life, limb and sanity to the effects of handling the relics of the ancient world. These gloves were created with to deal with that specific problem of adventuring.

Sturdy enough to protect the wrists and hands against hidden needles or snakebites, durable enough to protect the skin against corrosive magics and sudden fires and comfortable enough to wear while jamming a hand into a sarcophagus.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91043_ShortDesc", "Practical canvas pants for exploring")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91043_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

These pants, made of sturdy canvas, will keep the legs protected against stinging sands while allowing full freedom to leap over traps, canyons and short enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91044_ShortDesc", "A set of boots design for exploring ruins")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91044_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

When the Relic Hunters first arrived in the Exiled Lands, they were given sandals and flat-soled shoes. It is not known how many Relic Hunters died with their toes wedged into a gap between flagstones while an ancient horror bore down upon their prone body.

Since those early days, the Relic Hunters have moved to a style of boot favoured in Shem - curled toes to avoid catching on cracks when sprinting, supple leather to allow maximum freedom of movement and high cuffs to tuck into pants and prevent the accumulation of sand.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91045_ShortDesc", "A horned helm worn by the Shamans of Kambuja")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91045_LongDesc", "The jungle-locked kingdom of Kambuja is mysterious to the inhabitants of the dreaming west. Unlike neighboring Vendhya, the locals do not welcome foreign trade and it is said that any merchant who sets themselves on the paths that lead into the jungle will never return.

This armor, then, is a rarity, made from a half-remembered glimpse of a Kambujan Shaman captured by the Vendhyans and put on display in the nations of the west.

The helm is more intimidating than protective, modelled on the blasphemous shapes of a heinous demonic entity. Known as Tim.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91050_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91050_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

Perhaps this is why the raiders wear masks such as this. To keep their identity hidden.")

This chestpiece offers excellent protection for the neck, shoulders and belly, while still being open enough to keep the wearer cool in the hot deserts of Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91055_ShortDesc", "A riveted fur cap of Vanir make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91055_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

A medium cap of fur and rivets to keep one safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")
