column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91060_ShortDesc", "A plumed helmet favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91060_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. The clearly recognizable plume of the helmet also serves to identify guardsmen on sight - a boon for which the pickpockets of Tarantia are eternally grateful.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

The large pauldron on the right shoulder is designed to protect the main arm during combat, while keeping the armor flexible and relatively light.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91070_ShortDesc", "A helmet designed to intimidate")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91070_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

The helmets of Hyperboreans are designed to protect them from magical threats, as well as mundane. The witch-men of Hyperborea do not want anybody controlling their servants.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91071_ShortDesc", "A waistguard designed to intimidate")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91071_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

It is considered a challenge among Hyperborean slavers to go bare-chested on their raids, wearing nothing more than this waistguard. While it offers less protection than steel leggings and a breastplate, it intimidates newly caught slaves into submission.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91072_ShortDesc", "A set of sturdy bracers")
column4:

Hyperborean slavers wear this armor to intimidate their enemies and cow their slaves.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91073_ShortDesc", "A loincloth worn beneath by Hyperborean slavers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91073_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

Primarily worn beneath the more armored waistguard, this loincloth is designed to keep the vitals of a slaver warm and protected when on long raids in the northern lands of Asgard and Vanaheim.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91074_ShortDesc", "Sturdy boots worn by Hyperborean slavers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91074_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

These boots are designed to be sturdy enough to last long trips and to grip well on rough terrain. It might be coincidental, but the additional grip makes it that much harder for a chained slave to pull a slaver off their feet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91075_ShortDesc", "A helm commonly worn by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91075_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">About them and among them, like the drift of a storm, were strewn slashed and trampled bodies in steel caps and leather jerkins - archers and pikemen.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This leather helm provides significant protection against blows to the head.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91076_ShortDesc", "A chest piece favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91076_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This style of armor was reportedly created by a band of raiders who call themselves the Wolves of the Steppes. Led by the fearsome, Bhangi Khan, they have often been spotted on raids deep in the eastern empire of Khitai.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91080_ShortDesc", "A helmet forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91080_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Free my hands and I'll varnish this floor with your brains!</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This heavy helmet is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91085_ShortDesc", "The formal helm of a Stygian officer")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91085_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

This ornamented helm is commonly worn by officers of higher rank to make them more easily recognizable on the battlefield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91086_ShortDesc", "A shirt of Stygian scale mail")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91086_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

Scale mail used to be reserved for the nobility, but as the kingdoms surrounding Stygia began to use more sophisticated weaponry, it was decided that the Stygian soldiers required more protection. Now scale mail has become the standard.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91087_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Stygian soldiers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91087_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

These bronze bracers protect the lower arm in the clash of shields, while allowing the wearer the flexibility of wrist and hand to thrust into the gaps above and below the shield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91088_ShortDesc", "A skirt of Stygian scale mail")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91088_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

Scale mail used to be reserved for the nobility, but as the kingdoms surrounding Stygia began to use more sophisticated weaponry, it was decided that the Stygian soldiers required more protection. Now scale mail has become the standard.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91089_ShortDesc", "Sandals worn by Stygian soldiers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91089_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

The Stygian pike men are sometimes called hoppers by their enemies. Their insistence in wearing open soled sandals into battle means that in the clash of shield walls, enemies will often target their feet.

Stygian officers, however, consider this a boon as an enemy focused on looking down is less likely to see the pike that pierces their helmet.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91095_ShortDesc", "A simple turban of hide and fiber")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91095_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the fierce sun beating down on the unprotected head can cause extreme delirium in a short amount of time.
Apart from protection from the sun, this turban offers a small amount of protection from attacks on the head.
Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.
Created from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91096_ShortDesc", "A light chestpiece of hide and fiber")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91096_LongDesc", "Designed to keep the wearer cool, this armor emphasizes movement and agility in combat over straight up protection.\nThe blow that misses is always better than the one that lands. In this case, the one that lands will cause a significant amount of damage due to the simple construction of this armor.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91097_ShortDesc", "A pair of flexible hide gauntlets")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91097_LongDesc", "Hide pieces bound to a soft underbody of cloth keep these gauntlets as flexible as possible while offering some protection from attacks.\nBlows to the hand can cause crippling injuries, particularly to archers who need to have all of their fingers intact if they are to draw a bow.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91098_ShortDesc", "A loose fitting cloth wrap, bound to the waist with rawhide thongs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91098_LongDesc", "This wrap allows the legs to move freely, giving full range of motion. This is particularly useful to the adventurer just beginning their journey, as it allows them to make the all-important decision of fight or flight.\nLight armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91099_ShortDesc", "A pair of sturdy boots made from cloth and hide")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91099_LongDesc", "These boots of cloth wrapped and laced in hide, provide protection and warmth for the feet.\nThere are many dangers in the Exiled Lands and the small scorpions, spiders and snakes that can strike without warning are reason enough to keep legs and feet well covered.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91100_ShortDesc", "A riveted leather cap with a facemask")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91100_LongDesc", "This leather helmet includes large cheek  and neck protectors and a facemask for filtering the sand and dust from the air.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91101_ShortDesc", "Leather spaulders riveted to articulated rerebraces")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91101_LongDesc", "The fastest way to a man\'s heart, is through his armpits\' is a common expression amongst the gladiators of Argos. Chest protection is often reinforced on the upper arms and the vulnerable areas around the armpits, rather than the central chest. Every human is already born with some natural protection over their hearts namely their ribcage and breastbone.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91102_ShortDesc", "Elbow length gauntlets of riveted leather")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91102_LongDesc", "Protecting the forearms and fingers is the primary purpose of gauntlets. The loss of a hand will cripple a warrior and the loss of fingers will cripple an archer.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91103_ShortDesc", "A leather skirt that protects the upper thighs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91103_LongDesc", "This long leather skirt is designed to protect the upper thighs from attacks while providing mobility.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91104_ShortDesc", "Calf-length riveted leather boots")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91104_LongDesc", "These boots offer good protection for the calves and feet and their sturdy construction means that they tolerate the harsh conditions for a long time.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91110_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91110_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91111_ShortDesc", "An ornate necklace of teeth over human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91111_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
This chestpiece is soft and supple, which allows for great flexibility. The teeth used in the necklace appear to be crocodile teeth, taken from the great beasts that roam the Exiled Lands.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91112_ShortDesc", "Bracers of blood-dyed leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91112_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These bracers are the color of blood and made of a soft leather wrapped with cloth. A close look reveals human molars dangling from the bindings on the gauntlets.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91113_ShortDesc", "Skirt of human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91113_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These skirt is simple and adorned with a belt of small beads and human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91114_ShortDesc", "Ankle wraps of soft leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91114_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These greaves are simple and adorned with small beads and human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91115_ShortDesc", "Shemitish turban commonly worn in the meadowland cities")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91115_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. Due to their access to these caravans, the Shemitish people often have access to the first pick of goods coming from the east - including fine silks from Khitai and brightly dyed cloth from Turan. This bounty of cloth is reflected in the loose fitting, comfortable clothing woven by the tailors of Shem.\nThis clothing is a practical bulwark against the elements but won\'t be enough to stop a blade.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91116_ShortDesc", "Shemitish tunic commonly worn in the meadowland cities")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91116_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91119_ShortDesc", "Shemitish pointy-toed shoes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91119_LongDesc", "While these shoes are impractical for the desert, they are incredibly comfortable.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91120_ShortDesc", "A pair of bone earrings often worn by Vanir commoners")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91120_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These earrings provide no significant protection, but they are marked with clan symbols - so that if a dead settler is found, their possessions can be returned to the clan. Jokingly referred to by the Aesir as Vanearrings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91121_ShortDesc", "A fur-lined vest worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91121_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

This vest is designed to keep the settler warm, while freeing their hands for working with tools. It offers some basic protection against attacks due to its thickness, but is not as effective as true armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91122_ShortDesc", "A set of fur gloves worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91122_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These gloves are perfect for keeping the hands warm while working frozen soil.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91123_ShortDesc", "A furry breechclout worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91123_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

This breechclout  keeps the settler warm, but has an unfortunate tendency to attract fleas and lice. Vanir women are well known for their habit of bathing in freezing streams in the midst of winter, Vanir men are known for being lice-infested bastards.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91124_ShortDesc", "A pair of furry boots worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91124_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These boots keep the feet warm while stumbling through banks and drifts of snow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91125_ShortDesc", "A hood for those who work in the shadows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91125_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

Designed with the principle that the best fight is a fight avoided, this outfit allows the wearer to blend into the shadows and remain unseen in the deep shadows of the Zamorian cities. 
Whether it is as effective in the lands beyond Zamoria is another question.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91126_ShortDesc", "A leather chestpiece for those who work in the shadows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91126_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

Designed with the principle that the best fight is a fight avoided, this outfit allows the wearer to blend into the shadows and remain unseen in the deep shadows of the Zamorian cities. 

It has been wrapped tightly to dampen any noise caused by loose straps and buckles. Whether it is as effective in the lands beyond Zamoria is another question.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91127_ShortDesc", "Fingerless gloves for those who need dextrous hands")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91127_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

A thief's fingers must be free to do nimble work - manipulating lockpicks, snatching purses and slitting throats. These gloves are designed to protect the hand and forearm while freeing the fingers to do their worst.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91128_ShortDesc", "Leather leggings with a belt of useful pouches")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91128_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These leggings are designed to help, not hinder, the burgeoning burglar in their trade. Accompanied by a handy belt, full of small pouches for storing the various tools of the thieving profession, these skin tight leather pants also offer excellent protection.
 Zamorian cutthroats swear by them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91129_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots of supple leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91129_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These boots are designed to allow cutthroats easy access to their victims, damping their footsteps as they approach from behind. 
They're also surprisingly durable when fleeing the city watch.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91130_ShortDesc", "A headscarf popular among Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91130_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Freebooters attire themselves in all manner of flamboyant outfits, but the headscarf is cheap, popular and practical.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91131_ShortDesc", "A vest worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91131_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

The sturdy leather vest is designed to turn the sharp edges of a saber but will offer little protection against a well-placed thrust. Still, it is practical for those who spend their lives on ships, and never needs to be scoured for rust.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91132_ShortDesc", "A pair of gloves worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91132_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Leather gloves are practical onboard a ship - for preventing blisters, rope-burn and the occasional knife wound as well.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91133_ShortDesc", "A pair of pants worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91133_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

The sturdy leather pants offer the freedom to scamper along lines, while still being stiff enough to turn the sharp edge of a dagger. They also never need to be scoured for rust.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91134_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91134_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Leather boots are practical onboard a ship - for preventing splinters and broken toes, but also for kicking unfortunate prisoners over the side.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91135_ShortDesc", "A turban designed to protect the head from the elements")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91135_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

This turban has been refined in the time that they have spent in the Exiled Lands, offering comfort against the warm weather of the region and limited protection against the scouring sands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91136_ShortDesc", "A loose shirt favoured by relic hunters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91136_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

Still scavengers at heart, this shirt is paired with a small leather sack for storing any treasure that a relic hunter might stumble across while exploring the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91137_ShortDesc", "A set of sturdy gloves for handling relics")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91137_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

Too many foolish souls have lost life, limb and sanity to the effects of handling the relics of the ancient world. These gloves were created with to deal with that specific problem of adventuring.

Sturdy enough to protect the wrists and hands against hidden needles or snakebites, durable enough to protect the skin against corrosive magics and sudden fires and comfortable enough to wear while jamming a hand into a sarcophagus.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91138_ShortDesc", "Practical canvas pants for exploring")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91138_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

These pants, made of sturdy canvas, will keep the legs protected against stinging sands while allowing full freedom to leap over traps, canyons and short enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91139_ShortDesc", "A set of boots design for exploring ruins")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91139_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

When the Relic Hunters first arrived in the Exiled Lands, they were given sandals and flat-soled shoes. It is not known how many Relic Hunters died with their toes wedged into a gap between flagstones while an ancient horror bore down upon their prone body.

Since those early days, the Relic Hunters have moved to a style of boot favoured in Shem - curled toes to avoid catching on cracks when sprinting, supple leather to allow maximum freedom of movement and high cuffs to tuck into pants and prevent the accumulation of sand.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91140_ShortDesc", "A horned helm worn by the Shamans of Kambuja")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91140_LongDesc", "The jungle-locked kingdom of Kambuja is mysterious to the inhabitants of the dreaming west. Unlike neighboring Vendhya, the locals do not welcome foreign trade and it is said that any merchant who sets themselves on the paths that lead into the jungle will never return.

This armor, then, is a rarity, made from a half-remembered glimpse of a Kambujan Shaman captured by the Vendhyans and put on display in the nations of the west.

The helm is more intimidating than protective, modelled on the blasphemous shapes of a heinous demonic entity. Known as Tim.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91145_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91145_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

Perhaps this is why the raiders wear masks such as this. To keep their identity hidden.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91146_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

This chestpiece offers excellent protection for the neck, shoulders and belly, while still being open enough to keep the wearer cool in the hot deserts of Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91150_ShortDesc", "A riveted fur cap of Vanir make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91150_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

A medium cap of fur and rivets to keep one safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91155_ShortDesc", "A plumed helmet favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91155_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. The clearly recognizable plume of the helmet also serves to identify guardsmen on sight - a boon for which the pickpockets of Tarantia are eternally grateful.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot.

The large pauldron on the right shoulder is designed to protect the main arm during combat, while keeping the armor flexible and relatively light.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

 The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. 

The left bracer is stiff leather to protect the freehand, while the right is a more flexible form of padding - allowing greater blade manoeuvrability during combat.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. 

Aquilonian guardsmen are often forced to chase down criminals or leap across rooftops in pursuit of fleeing foes. This short skirt is designed to allow them this freedom of movement, while still protecting their upper thighs.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91165_ShortDesc", "A helmet designed to intimidate")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91165_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

The helmets of Hyperboreans are designed to protect them from magical threats, as well as mundane. The witch-men of Hyperborea do not want anybody controlling their servants.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91166_ShortDesc", "A waistguard designed to intimidate")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91166_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

It is considered a challenge among Hyperborean slavers to go bare-chested on their raids, wearing nothing more than this waistguard. While it offers less protection than steel leggings and a breastplate, it intimidates newly caught slaves into submission.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91167_ShortDesc", "A set of sturdy bracers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91167_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

Hyperborean slavers wear this armor to intimidate their enemies and cow their slaves.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91168_ShortDesc", "A loincloth worn beneath by Hyperborean slavers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91168_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

Primarily worn beneath the more armored waistguard, this loincloth is designed to keep the vitals of a slaver warm and protected when on long raids in the northern lands of Asgard and Vanaheim.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91169_ShortDesc", "Sturdy boots worn by Hyperborean slavers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91169_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

These boots are designed to be sturdy enough to last long trips and to grip well on rough terrain. It might be coincidental, but the additional grip makes it that much harder for a chained slave to pull a slaver off their feet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91170_ShortDesc", "A helm commonly worn by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91170_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">About them and among them, like the drift of a storm, were strewn slashed and trampled bodies in steel caps and leather jerkins - archers and pikemen.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This leather helm provides significant protection against blows to the head.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91171_ShortDesc", "A chest piece favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91171_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This style of armor was reportedly created by a band of raiders who call themselves the Wolves of the Steppes. Led by the fearsome, Bhangi Khan, they have often been spotted on raids deep in the eastern empire of Khitai.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91172_ShortDesc", "Leather gauntlets favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

These leather gloves protect the hands in battle, while offering enough flexibility for shooting the horse-bows of the Hyrkania.")

column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91175_ShortDesc", "A helmet forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91175_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Free my hands and I'll varnish this floor with your brains!</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This heavy helmet is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91176_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91176_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then, as the white stars glimmered through the blue velvet dusk, making her whirling body a blur of ivory fire, with a wild cry she threw herself at Conan's feet, and the blind flood of the Cimmerian's desire swept all else away as he crushed her panting form against the black plates of his corseleted breast.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

This impossibly hard pauldron is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91180_ShortDesc", "The formal helm of a Stygian officer")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91180_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

This ornamented helm is commonly worn by officers of higher rank to make them more easily recognizable on the battlefield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91181_ShortDesc", "A shirt of Stygian scale mail")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91181_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

Scale mail used to be reserved for the nobility, but as the kingdoms surrounding Stygia began to use more sophisticated weaponry, it was decided that the Stygian soldiers required more protection. Now scale mail has become the standard.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91182_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Stygian soldiers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91182_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

These bronze bracers protect the lower arm in the clash of shields, while allowing the wearer the flexibility of wrist and hand to thrust into the gaps above and below the shield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91183_ShortDesc", "A skirt of Stygian scale mail")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91183_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

Scale mail used to be reserved for the nobility, but as the kingdoms surrounding Stygia began to use more sophisticated weaponry, it was decided that the Stygian soldiers required more protection. Now scale mail has become the standard.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91184_ShortDesc", "Sandals worn by Stygian soldiers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91184_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

The Stygian pike men are sometimes called hoppers by their enemies. Their insistence in wearing open soled sandals into battle means that in the clash of shield walls, enemies will often target their feet.

Stygian officers, however, consider this a boon as an enemy focused on looking down is less likely to see the pike that pierces their helmet.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91190_ShortDesc", "A simple turban of hide and fiber")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91190_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the fierce sun beating down on the unprotected head can cause extreme delirium in a short amount of time.
Apart from protection from the sun, this turban offers a small amount of protection from attacks on the head.
Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.
Created from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91191_ShortDesc", "A light chestpiece of hide and fiber")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91191_LongDesc", "Designed to keep the wearer cool, this armor emphasizes movement and agility in combat over straight up protection.\nThe blow that misses is always better than the one that lands. In this case, the one that lands will cause a significant amount of damage due to the simple construction of this armor.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91192_ShortDesc", "A pair of flexible hide gauntlets")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91192_LongDesc", "Hide pieces bound to a soft underbody of cloth keep these gauntlets as flexible as possible while offering some protection from attacks.\nBlows to the hand can cause crippling injuries, particularly to archers who need to have all of their fingers intact if they are to draw a bow.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91193_ShortDesc", "A loose fitting cloth wrap, bound to the waist with rawhide thongs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91193_LongDesc", "This wrap allows the legs to move freely, giving full range of motion. This is particularly useful to the adventurer just beginning their journey, as it allows them to make the all-important decision of fight or flight.\nLight armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91194_ShortDesc", "A pair of sturdy boots made from cloth and hide")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91194_LongDesc", "These boots of cloth wrapped and laced in hide, provide protection and warmth for the feet.\nThere are many dangers in the Exiled Lands and the small scorpions, spiders and snakes that can strike without warning are reason enough to keep legs and feet well covered.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91195_ShortDesc", "A riveted leather cap with a facemask")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91195_LongDesc", "This leather helmet includes large cheek  and neck protectors and a facemask for filtering the sand and dust from the air.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91196_ShortDesc", "Leather spaulders riveted to articulated rerebraces")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91196_LongDesc", "The fastest way to a man\'s heart, is through his armpits\' is a common expression amongst the gladiators of Argos. Chest protection is often reinforced on the upper arms and the vulnerable areas around the armpits, rather than the central chest. Every human is already born with some natural protection over their hearts namely their ribcage and breastbone.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91197_ShortDesc", "Elbow length gauntlets of riveted leather")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91197_LongDesc", "Protecting the forearms and fingers is the primary purpose of gauntlets. The loss of a hand will cripple a warrior and the loss of fingers will cripple an archer.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91198_ShortDesc", "A leather skirt that protects the upper thighs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91198_LongDesc", "This long leather skirt is designed to protect the upper thighs from attacks while providing mobility.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91199_ShortDesc", "Calf-length riveted leather boots")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91199_LongDesc", "These boots offer good protection for the calves and feet and their sturdy construction means that they tolerate the harsh conditions for a long time.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91205_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91205_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91206_ShortDesc", "An ornate necklace of teeth over human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91206_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
This chestpiece is soft and supple, which allows for great flexibility. The teeth used in the necklace appear to be crocodile teeth, taken from the great beasts that roam the Exiled Lands.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91207_ShortDesc", "Bracers of blood-dyed leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91207_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These bracers are the color of blood and made of a soft leather wrapped with cloth. A close look reveals human molars dangling from the bindings on the gauntlets.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91208_ShortDesc", "Skirt of human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91208_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These skirt is simple and adorned with a belt of small beads and human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91209_ShortDesc", "Ankle wraps of soft leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91209_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These greaves are simple and adorned with small beads and human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91210_ShortDesc", "Shemitish turban commonly worn in the meadowland cities")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91210_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. Due to their access to these caravans, the Shemitish people often have access to the first pick of goods coming from the east - including fine silks from Khitai and brightly dyed cloth from Turan. This bounty of cloth is reflected in the loose fitting, comfortable clothing woven by the tailors of Shem.\nThis clothing is a practical bulwark against the elements but won\'t be enough to stop a blade.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91211_ShortDesc", "Shemitish tunic commonly worn in the meadowland cities")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91211_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91214_ShortDesc", "Shemitish pointy-toed shoes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91214_LongDesc", "While these shoes are impractical for the desert, they are incredibly comfortable.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91215_ShortDesc", "A pair of bone earrings often worn by Vanir commoners")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91215_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These earrings provide no significant protection, but they are marked with clan symbols - so that if a dead settler is found, their possessions can be returned to the clan. Jokingly referred to by the Aesir as Vanearrings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91216_ShortDesc", "A fur-lined vest worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91216_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

This vest is designed to keep the settler warm, while freeing their hands for working with tools. It offers some basic protection against attacks due to its thickness, but is not as effective as true armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91217_ShortDesc", "A set of fur gloves worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91217_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These gloves are perfect for keeping the hands warm while working frozen soil.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91218_ShortDesc", "A furry breechclout worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91218_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

This breechclout  keeps the settler warm, but has an unfortunate tendency to attract fleas and lice. Vanir women are well known for their habit of bathing in freezing streams in the midst of winter, Vanir men are known for being lice-infested bastards.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91219_ShortDesc", "A pair of furry boots worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91219_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These boots keep the feet warm while stumbling through banks and drifts of snow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91220_ShortDesc", "A hood for those who work in the shadows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91220_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

Designed with the principle that the best fight is a fight avoided, this outfit allows the wearer to blend into the shadows and remain unseen in the deep shadows of the Zamorian cities. 
Whether it is as effective in the lands beyond Zamoria is another question.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91221_ShortDesc", "A leather chestpiece for those who work in the shadows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91221_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

Designed with the principle that the best fight is a fight avoided, this outfit allows the wearer to blend into the shadows and remain unseen in the deep shadows of the Zamorian cities. 

It has been wrapped tightly to dampen any noise caused by loose straps and buckles. Whether it is as effective in the lands beyond Zamoria is another question.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91222_ShortDesc", "Fingerless gloves for those who need dextrous hands")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91222_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

A thief's fingers must be free to do nimble work - manipulating lockpicks, snatching purses and slitting throats. These gloves are designed to protect the hand and forearm while freeing the fingers to do their worst.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91223_ShortDesc", "Leather leggings with a belt of useful pouches")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91223_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These leggings are designed to help, not hinder, the burgeoning burglar in their trade. Accompanied by a handy belt, full of small pouches for storing the various tools of the thieving profession, these skin tight leather pants also offer excellent protection.
 Zamorian cutthroats swear by them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91224_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots of supple leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91224_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These boots are designed to allow cutthroats easy access to their victims, damping their footsteps as they approach from behind. 
They're also surprisingly durable when fleeing the city watch.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91225_ShortDesc", "A headscarf popular among Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91225_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Freebooters attire themselves in all manner of flamboyant outfits, but the headscarf is cheap, popular and practical.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91226_ShortDesc", "A vest worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91226_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

The sturdy leather vest is designed to turn the sharp edges of a saber but will offer little protection against a well-placed thrust. Still, it is practical for those who spend their lives on ships, and never needs to be scoured for rust.")
