column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91230_ShortDesc", "A turban designed to protect the head from the elements")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91230_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

This turban has been refined in the time that they have spent in the Exiled Lands, offering comfort against the warm weather of the region and limited protection against the scouring sands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91231_ShortDesc", "A loose shirt favoured by relic hunters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91231_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

Still scavengers at heart, this shirt is paired with a small leather sack for storing any treasure that a relic hunter might stumble across while exploring the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91232_ShortDesc", "A set of sturdy gloves for handling relics")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91232_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

Too many foolish souls have lost life, limb and sanity to the effects of handling the relics of the ancient world. These gloves were created with to deal with that specific problem of adventuring.

Sturdy enough to protect the wrists and hands against hidden needles or snakebites, durable enough to protect the skin against corrosive magics and sudden fires and comfortable enough to wear while jamming a hand into a sarcophagus.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91233_ShortDesc", "Practical canvas pants for exploring")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91233_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

These pants, made of sturdy canvas, will keep the legs protected against stinging sands while allowing full freedom to leap over traps, canyons and short enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91234_ShortDesc", "A set of boots design for exploring ruins")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91234_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

When the Relic Hunters first arrived in the Exiled Lands, they were given sandals and flat-soled shoes. It is not known how many Relic Hunters died with their toes wedged into a gap between flagstones while an ancient horror bore down upon their prone body.

Since those early days, the Relic Hunters have moved to a style of boot favoured in Shem - curled toes to avoid catching on cracks when sprinting, supple leather to allow maximum freedom of movement and high cuffs to tuck into pants and prevent the accumulation of sand.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91235_ShortDesc", "A horned helm worn by the Shamans of Kambuja")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91235_LongDesc", "The jungle-locked kingdom of Kambuja is mysterious to the inhabitants of the dreaming west. Unlike neighboring Vendhya, the locals do not welcome foreign trade and it is said that any merchant who sets themselves on the paths that lead into the jungle will never return.

This armor, then, is a rarity, made from a half-remembered glimpse of a Kambujan Shaman captured by the Vendhyans and put on display in the nations of the west.

The helm is more intimidating than protective, modelled on the blasphemous shapes of a heinous demonic entity. Known as Tim.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91240_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91240_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

Perhaps this is why the raiders wear masks such as this. To keep their identity hidden.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91241_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91241_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

This chestpiece offers excellent protection for the neck, shoulders and belly, while still being open enough to keep the wearer cool in the hot deserts of Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91245_ShortDesc", "A riveted fur cap of Vanir make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91245_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

A medium cap of fur and rivets to keep one safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91250_ShortDesc", "A plumed helmet favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91250_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. The clearly recognizable plume of the helmet also serves to identify guardsmen on sight - a boon for which the pickpockets of Tarantia are eternally grateful.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column4:

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot.

The large pauldron on the right shoulder is designed to protect the main arm during combat, while keeping the armor flexible and relatively light.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column4:

 The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. 

The left bracer is stiff leather to protect the freehand, while the right is a more flexible form of padding - allowing greater blade manoeuvrability during combat.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91253_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. 

Aquilonian guardsmen are often forced to chase down criminals or leap across rooftops in pursuit of fleeing foes. This short skirt is designed to allow them this freedom of movement, while still protecting their upper thighs.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

The distinctive sound of these sandals slapping against the paving stones is a hallmark of Aquilonian cities. 

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91260_ShortDesc", "A helmet designed to intimidate")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91260_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

The helmets of Hyperboreans are designed to protect them from magical threats, as well as mundane. The witch-men of Hyperborea do not want anybody controlling their servants.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91261_ShortDesc", "A waistguard designed to intimidate")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91261_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

It is considered a challenge among Hyperborean slavers to go bare-chested on their raids, wearing nothing more than this waistguard. While it offers less protection than steel leggings and a breastplate, it intimidates newly caught slaves into submission.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91262_ShortDesc", "A set of sturdy bracers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91262_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

Hyperborean slavers wear this armor to intimidate their enemies and cow their slaves.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91263_ShortDesc", "A loincloth worn beneath by Hyperborean slavers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91263_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

Primarily worn beneath the more armored waistguard, this loincloth is designed to keep the vitals of a slaver warm and protected when on long raids in the northern lands of Asgard and Vanaheim.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91264_ShortDesc", "Sturdy boots worn by Hyperborean slavers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91264_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

These boots are designed to be sturdy enough to last long trips and to grip well on rough terrain. It might be coincidental, but the additional grip makes it that much harder for a chained slave to pull a slaver off their feet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91265_ShortDesc", "A helm commonly worn by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91265_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">About them and among them, like the drift of a storm, were strewn slashed and trampled bodies in steel caps and leather jerkins - archers and pikemen.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This leather helm provides significant protection against blows to the head.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91266_ShortDesc", "A chest piece favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91266_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This style of armor was reportedly created by a band of raiders who call themselves the Wolves of the Steppes. Led by the fearsome, Bhangi Khan, they have often been spotted on raids deep in the eastern empire of Khitai.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91267_ShortDesc", "Leather gauntlets favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91267_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

These leather gloves protect the hands in battle, while offering enough flexibility for shooting the horse-bows of the Hyrkania.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91268_ShortDesc", "Heavy britches favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91268_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This style of armor was reportedly created by a band of raiders who call themselves the Wolves of the Steppes. Led by the fearsome, Bhangi Khan, they have often been spotted on raids deep in the eastern empire of Khitai.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91269_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91269_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

These boots are designed to protect the feet from blows during combat from the back of a horse.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91270_ShortDesc", "A helmet forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91270_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Free my hands and I'll varnish this floor with your brains!</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This heavy helmet is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91271_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91271_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then, as the white stars glimmered through the blue velvet dusk, making her whirling body a blur of ivory fire, with a wild cry she threw herself at Conan's feet, and the blind flood of the Cimmerian's desire swept all else away as he crushed her panting form against the black plates of his corseleted breast.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

This impossibly hard pauldron is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column4:

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91273_ShortDesc", "Leg armor forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91274_ShortDesc", "Plated boots are forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91274_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They gave tongue like wolves and surged about the lone figure in the gray mail, and the clamor and din of steel drowned the cries of the circling raven.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These impossibly hard plated boots are made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91275_ShortDesc", "The formal helm of a Stygian officer")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91275_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

This ornamented helm is commonly worn by officers of higher rank to make them more easily recognizable on the battlefield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91276_ShortDesc", "A shirt of Stygian scale mail")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91276_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

Scale mail used to be reserved for the nobility, but as the kingdoms surrounding Stygia began to use more sophisticated weaponry, it was decided that the Stygian soldiers required more protection. Now scale mail has become the standard.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91277_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Stygian soldiers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91277_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

These bronze bracers protect the lower arm in the clash of shields, while allowing the wearer the flexibility of wrist and hand to thrust into the gaps above and below the shield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91278_ShortDesc", "A skirt of Stygian scale mail")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91278_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

Scale mail used to be reserved for the nobility, but as the kingdoms surrounding Stygia began to use more sophisticated weaponry, it was decided that the Stygian soldiers required more protection. Now scale mail has become the standard.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91279_ShortDesc", "Sandals worn by Stygian soldiers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91279_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

The Stygian pike men are sometimes called hoppers by their enemies. Their insistence in wearing open soled sandals into battle means that in the clash of shield walls, enemies will often target their feet.

Stygian officers, however, consider this a boon as an enemy focused on looking down is less likely to see the pike that pierces their helmet.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91280_ShortDesc", "A helmet made of thick reptile leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91280_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then for the first time humans appeared: dark-skinned, hawk-faced men in copper and leather harness, bearing bows - the warriors of pre-historic Stygia.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

The overlapping scales that offer natural protection to reptiles are an excellent source of protection for humans as well. The problem is that very few reptiles give up their skins willingly, and the most fearsome crocodiles are more than a match for a poorly armed hunter.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates a balance of protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

This style of armor is common in the Black Kingdoms.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91295_ShortDesc", "A helmet crafted from the skull of Hyena")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91295_LongDesc", "The Dogs of the Desert are a mysterious clan who inhabit the northern reaches of the desert. Their obsession with capturing and taming Hyenas and their fanatical worship of the god known as Jhebbal Sag keeps them aloof from the other factions in the region.\nThe fact that they wear uncured furs and unclean bones probably doesn\'t help.\nSome might question wearing fur in the warmth of the desert, but nights can be brutally cold and the slopes of the mountain are not that far to the north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91310_ShortDesc", "An armor of old Vanir design")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91310_LongDesc", "This armor is of Vanir design and thus, protects against colder climates. In addition, the armor scraps used to build this armor have been infused by the magic and craftsmanship of the Giant Kings which bestows additional properties. This piece of armor periodically removes bleeding from the wearer and grants a bonus to Grit.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91315_ShortDesc", "This is the true power of the Warmaker\'s Champion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91315_LongDesc", "Crafted by infusing the rusty pieces of the Warmaker\'s armor with an assortment of magical ingredients, this armor is the pinnacle of heavy armors. It withstands an enormous amount of punishment. The magical energies that surge through this helmet grant additional Grit and also functions as a breathing mask.")

The magical energies that surge through these leggings grant additional Encumbrance and repairs the equipped weapon for a slight amount when the wearer takes damage.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91320_ShortDesc", "An ancient helmet with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91320_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It is sorcery - grisly black magic from the grim youth of the world. An awful shape has risen out of the shades of the Past, and none can stand before it.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This eldritch helm bears markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the names Deathbringer, Kinscourge, and Maimer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91321_ShortDesc", "An ancient chestpiece with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91321_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I have lain in your arms, panting with the violence of our love; you have held and crushed and conquered me, drawing my soul to your lips with the fierceness of your bruising kisses. My heart is welded to your heart, my soul is part of your soul! Were I still in death and you fighting for life, I would come back to the abyss to aid you--aye, whether my spirit floated with the purple sails on the crystal sea of paradise, or writhed in the molten flames of hell! I am yours, and all the gods and all their eternities shall not sever us!</> - Queen of the Black Coast

This eldritch chest armor bears markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the names Tyros and Telith.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91322_ShortDesc", "Ancient gauntlets with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91322_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Those eyes grew and became gigantic, and in them the Cimmerian glimpsed the reality of all the abysmal and blasphemous horrors that lurk in the outer darkness of formless voids and nighted gulfs.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

These eldritch gauntlets bear markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper of the hybrid half-child of the humans and the Giant-kings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91323_ShortDesc", "Ancient leg armor with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91323_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Wits and swords are as straws against the wisdom of the Darkness...</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

This eldritch leg armor bears markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the names Klael the Warmaker, The Archivist, and the Priestking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91324_ShortDesc", "Ancient plated boots with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91324_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">By Crom, I do not like this place, where dead men rise, and sleeping men vanish into the bellies of shadows!</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

These eldritch boots bear markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the name of the Witch Queen.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92000_ShortDesc", "A helmet made of thick reptile leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92000_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then for the first time humans appeared: dark-skinned, hawk-faced men in copper and leather harness, bearing bows - the warriors of pre-historic Stygia.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

The overlapping scales that offer natural protection to reptiles are an excellent source of protection for humans as well. The problem is that very few reptiles give up their skins willingly, and the most fearsome crocodiles are more than a match for a poorly armed hunter.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates a balance of protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

This style of armor is common in the Black Kingdoms.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92010_ShortDesc", "A helmet made of thick reptile leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92010_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He plunged through the undergrowth, hip-deep in the marshes; dived headlong into the deep water, heedless of sharks or crocodiles, and swam to the galley and was clambering up the chain on to the deck, dripping and exultant, before the watch saw him.</> - The hour of the Dragon

Only the chosen of Sobek are allowed to wear this armor. The scales themselves are thicker than regular crocodile scales, and it has been further reinforced by star metal plates. As a result, the armor is much heavier than normal medium armor but offers additional protection.

This armor does not grant any bonus to heat or cold-protection.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92015_LongDesc", "Prophets, Centors, Legates and Protectors of the faith of Asura, the Followers of Asura are known for their worldly knowledge as well as their helpfulness. \n\nThese clothes do not protect against the weather but do grant attribute bonuses.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92088_ShortDesc", "An old, battered helm of Nemedian make")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92088_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The last glints of the sun shone on the golden banner of Nemedia with the scarlet dragon, unfurled in the breeze above the pavilion of King Tarascus on an eminence near the eastern cliffs. But the shadow of the western cliffs fell like a vast purple pall across the tents and the army of Aquilonia, and upon the black banner with its golden lion that floated above King Conan\'s pavilion.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThis helmet, battered as it may be, provides ample protection. In addition, while worn, it will repair any wielded weapon each time you take damage.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92089_ShortDesc", "This summons a protector of Hanuman to your side")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92089_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">They entered a court paved with marble which gleamed whitely in the starlight. A short flight of broad marble steps led up to the pillared portico. The great bronze doors stood wide open as they had stood for centuries. But no worshippers burnt incense within. In the day men and women might come timidly into the shrine and place offerings to the ape-god on the black altar. At night the people shunned the temple of Hanuman as hares shun the lair of the serpent.</> - Shadows in Zamboula\n\nThis boon was granted by Hanuman after a human sacrifice was placed in his hands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92094_ShortDesc", "This bow has a demonic entity bound to it")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92094_LongDesc", "It is unknown as to which specific demonic entity is bound to this bow, but whichever it is, it hungers for death. A pity, then, that the entity this demon possessed was merely a goat. Otherwise, this weapon could have been quite formidable.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92095_ShortDesc", "This War-Axe randomly causes additional damage")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92095_LongDesc", "Crafted by the legendary but mad blacksmith Jhus Thorse, this war-axe has the hallmarks of an incredibly well-made axe - in parts. Jhus was growing increasingly mad and forgetful with age. Some parts of the axe-blade has been sharpened to an incredible edge, while others have barely gotten any attention. This has the effect that when the axe hits a target it might - or might not - do extra damage depending on which part of the axe actually hits the target.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92096_ShortDesc", "This shield has a sharpened edge")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92096_LongDesc", "Crafted by the smith Azir Taras as a gift to his brother Ap\'Thum on his wedding day. The edges of this shield have been sharpened to a razor edge and due to the shape of the shield, it makes it impossible to deflect blows without cutting one-self.\n\nUpon receiving the shield as, Azir is rumored to have thrown it out the window. Hearing screams from the streets below, Azir and Ap\'Thum looked out the window only to find the shield had cut off the head of the father of the soon-to-be bride.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92098_ShortDesc", "A bow crafted from the bones of a winged demon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92098_LongDesc", "This bow is made from the hollow bones of the Nest Mother. Its construction is awkward yet powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92099_ShortDesc", "Arrows made from the hollowed bones of a winged demon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92099_LongDesc", "These arrows were not crafted as much as ripped from the dead bodies of the winged Children of Jhil.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92100_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92100_LongDesc", "Infused with Darfari witch-craft, this mask allows the wearer to see in darkness.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92101_ShortDesc", "A blouse traditionally worn by Darfari dancers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92101_LongDesc", "This enchanted chest-piece grants more armor than what one would initially suspect.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92102_ShortDesc", "Shemitish tunic commonly worn in the meadowland cities")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92102_LongDesc", "Made from the finest silks, this armor has been reinforced while still retaining its weight. The craftsmanship is nothing less than magnificent.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92103_ShortDesc", "Shemitish leggings commonly worn in the meadowland cities")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92103_LongDesc", "Made from the finest silks, this armor has been reinforced while still retaining its weight. The craftsmanship is nothing less than magnificent.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92104_ShortDesc", "A pair of pants worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92104_LongDesc", "Enchanted, or perhaps corrupted, by the presence of the Winged Death, these pants have been infused with unholy magic, granting the wearer additional attribute enhancements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92105_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92105_LongDesc", "Enchanted, or perhaps corrupted, by the presence of the Winged Death, these boots have been infused with unholy magic, granting the wearer additional attribute enhancements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92106_ShortDesc", "A crudely-fashioned eye patch")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92106_LongDesc", "Sought after by the Vanir as a holy relic of the gods, this Eye-patch may blind one eye but grants terrific strength in return.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92107_ShortDesc", "A horned steel helmet")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92107_LongDesc", "An incredibly durable helmet made from the finest materials.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92108_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92108_LongDesc", "Wrested from the clutches of the undead in the Unnamed City, this old Stygian helmet has seen better days but even though it is old, the craftsmanship still shines through.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92109_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92109_LongDesc", "Infused with strange magic, this harness periodically cleanses the wearer from poison.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92110_ShortDesc", "A plumed helmet favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92110_LongDesc", "This helmet protects against gas and sandstorms alike.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92111_ShortDesc", "A leather vest and pauldron in Aquilonian style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92111_LongDesc", "Magnificent in its make and a sight feared by anyone that opposes the glory of the Aquilonian legions.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92112_ShortDesc", "A helmet forged from mysterious star metal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92112_LongDesc", "This helmet seems to have more padding than armor, resulting in a helmet that is extremely warm.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92113_ShortDesc", "Plated boots are forged from mysterious star metal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92113_LongDesc", "Lined with the fur of mammoths, these boots are warm and comfortable and their grip allows the wearer to carry weight more reliably.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92114_ShortDesc", "A helmet made of thick reptile leather")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92114_LongDesc", "This helm grants the wearer a bonus to their strength.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92115_ShortDesc", "Gauntlets made of thick reptile leather")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92115_LongDesc", "These gauntlets grant the wearer a bonus to their grit.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92116_ShortDesc", "A helmet made of thick reptile leather")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92116_LongDesc", "Crafted from the scales of the Red Mother, this helmet grants an inordinate amount of cold protection.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92117_ShortDesc", "A helmet crafted from the skull of Hyena")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92117_LongDesc", "Crafted from the feathers of the Winged Death, and the skull of an undead hyena, this helmet corrupts while at the same time granting high armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92119_ShortDesc", "A still beating heart")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92119_LongDesc", "The heart, still beating, was taken from the chest of a nordheimer hero. A worthy sacrifice to Ymir.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92124_ShortDesc", "A horn to call upon Ymirs favor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92124_LongDesc", "Blowing this horn will summon a Frost Giant to your side. A strange allegiance but once the horn has been sounded, an unbreakable bond is crafted.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92127_ShortDesc", "A coating that harms the undead")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92127_LongDesc", "Cimmerians fear not creatures of flesh and blood but those of an undead nature cannot be killed by normal means. Forced to adapt people of the Forgotten Tribe found a way to make the rotting flesh sear by coating their weapons with this salve.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92133_ShortDesc", "A fragment of a stone tablet with runes carved on it")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92133_LongDesc", "The genious of Thorgar was rumored to be unrivalled in the days of old. His descendants inherited tablets with recipes carved in ancient runes supposedly only legible to his closest kin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92134_ShortDesc", "An aged manuscript")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92134_LongDesc", "Contrary to a common belief, the teachings of a frost giant did not teach Thorgar smithing skills. In actuality, his skills were honed by countless experimentations with ice and steel. Some of his findings are noted down in this parchment. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92135_ShortDesc", "An ancient crest")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92135_LongDesc", "A symbol of acknowledgement and status among Aesir craftsmen. Thorgar received it from King Dunkar as a reward for his contributions to the tribe.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92136_ShortDesc", "An Aesir helmet made of star metal and covered with black ice")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92136_LongDesc", "An ancient armor piece worn by the most competent and feared Aesir warrior in the Exiled Lands. This armor is the greatest accomplishment of a fabled blacksmith named Thorgar of the North.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92137_ShortDesc", "An Aesir chestpiece made of starmetal and covered with black ice")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92137_LongDesc", "An ancient armor piece worn by the most competent and feared Aesir warrior in the Exiled Lands. This armor is the greatest accomplishment of a fabled blacksmith named Thorgar of the North.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92138_ShortDesc", "Aesir Leggings made of starmetal and covered with black ice")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92138_LongDesc", "An ancient armor piece worn by the most competent and feared Aesir warrior in the Exiled Lands. This armor is the greatest accomplishment of a fabled blacksmith named Thorgar of the North.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92139_ShortDesc", "Aesir gauntlets made of starmetal and covered with black ice")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92139_LongDesc", "An ancient armor piece worn by the most competent and feared Aesir warrior in the Exiled Lands. This armor is the greatest accomplishment of a fabled blacksmith named Thorgar of the North.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92140_ShortDesc", "Aesir boots made of starmetal and covered with black ice")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92140_LongDesc", "An ancient armor piece worn by the most competent and feared Aesir warrior in the Exiled Lands. This armor is the greatest accomplishment of a fabled blacksmith named Thorgar of the North.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92141_ShortDesc", "A scroll describing the process for making Aesir armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92141_LongDesc", "This scroll contains the knowledge of a long lost method of crafting the Pride of Aesir armor set capable of withstanding most cruel elements of the North.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92142_ShortDesc", "A spiced dish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92142_LongDesc", "A dish made from the innards of Shoebills, fried with honey, spices and short fibrous strains from nearby plants. This dish will grant protection against cold climates. It also burns your tongue - ever so slightly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92144_ShortDesc", "A mask with a breathable pocket of air inside.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92144_LongDesc", "This mask allows the wearer to stay under water longer. It does not function in a magical way - rather - the mask has a built in air-pocket which grants additional air while diving.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92145_ShortDesc", "Aclohol. Alloco? Alocolol? it\'s booze.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92145_LongDesc", "This will get you good and drunk and make you speak like a pirate.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92147_ShortDesc", "This dust corrupts but grants night-vision")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92147_LongDesc", "The process of making Argossean Dream Dust is a secret kept by the Black Hand that they do not share willingly. Not that many would be interested in it anyway, given the side-effects. One cannot deny it\'s usefulness though.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92149_ShortDesc", "An improvised bar brawling weapon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92149_LongDesc", "For all weapons there is one end that is particularly unpleasant. Whomever broke this bottle made certain that the amount of unpleasant ends should vastly outnumber the amount of safe ones.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92150_ShortDesc", "Ornate and luxurious.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92150_LongDesc", "While gold is malleable and easily bendable, this sword has a core of solid steel. Many an opponents last words when seeing this sword has been \'And what do you expect to cut with tha.. aaargghhh!\'")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92151_ShortDesc", "Ornate and luxurious.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92151_LongDesc", "While gold is malleable and bends easily, this shield has a core of solid steel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92159_ShortDesc", "A pearl")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92159_LongDesc", "Hard. Glistening. Produced by a mollusk. All that you could possibly want.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92160_ShortDesc", "An infant gorilla")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92160_LongDesc", "The wealth of Hyborian nations is built upon the backs of their beasts of burden and those who know how to handle an animal. And the mark of a man can be weighed by the manner in which he treats the least of his animals. Feed them and give them a place to live and they can be the greatest allies in the world. Neglect them and reap the consequences.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92161_ShortDesc", "An outfit worn by the Black Corsairs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92161_LongDesc", "This outfit is reserved for the elite of the Black Hand - the Black Corsairs. These clothes are fashioned in such a way that they are comfortable and do not restrict movement.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92162_ShortDesc", "An outfit worn by the Black Corsairs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92162_LongDesc", "This outfit is reserved for the elite of the Black Hand - the Black Corsairs. These clothes are fashioned in such a way that they are comfortable and do not restrict movement.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92163_ShortDesc", "An outfit worn by the Black Corsairs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92163_LongDesc", "This outfit is reserved for the elite of the Black Hand - the Black Corsairs. These clothes are fashioned in such a way that they are comfortable and do not restrict movement.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92164_ShortDesc", "An outfit worn by the Black Corsairs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92164_LongDesc", "This outfit is reserved for the elite of the Black Hand - the Black Corsairs. These clothes are fashioned in such a way that they are comfortable and do not restrict movement.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92165_ShortDesc", "An outfit worn by the Black Corsairs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92165_LongDesc", "This outfit is reserved for the elite of the Black Hand - the Black Corsairs. These clothes are fashioned in such a way that they are comfortable and do not restrict movement.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92166_ShortDesc", "A well-used cleaver")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92166_LongDesc", "Razor Gord\'s favourite weapon as well as a useful tool, this cleaver has seen much use. It has been very well taken care of and has a reinforced core of steel. Razor Gord is rumored to have repeatedly demonstrated its use on his least favored sous-chefs.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92167_ShortDesc", "An incredibly sharp Cutlass")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92167_LongDesc", "Named the \'Seasalt Cutlass\' by virtue of it\'s notably sharp sting when forcefully inserted into people\'s mouth, this weapon has coined the term \'Salting the wound\' by the pirates of the Black Cove.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92168_ShortDesc", "Strands of black fiber")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92168_LongDesc", "These strands of black fiber comes from a plant not commonly found in the Exiled Lands. Where the pirates of the Black Cove has gotten it from is a mystery.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92169_ShortDesc", "Spiced tea")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92169_LongDesc", "This tea has an immediate warming effect on whomever imbibes it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92170_ShortDesc", "A spiced dish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92170_LongDesc", "This dish has an immediate warming effect on whomever eats it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92171_ShortDesc", "A spiced dish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92171_LongDesc", "This dish has an immediate warming effect on whomever eats it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92172_ShortDesc", "A spiced dish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92172_LongDesc", "This dish has an immediate warming effect on whomever eats it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92173_ShortDesc", "A spiced dish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92173_LongDesc", "This dish has an immediate warming effect on whomever eats it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92174_ShortDesc", "A rare luxury item in the Exiled Lands")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92174_LongDesc", "While normal spice is relatively easy to obtain, the more zesty and tasty spices are still a luxury commodity.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92175_ShortDesc", "Reading this scroll will grand you knowledge")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92175_LongDesc", "Reading this scroll will teach you how to craft the Vehemence Elixir.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92176_ShortDesc", "An incredibly sharp cutlass")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92176_LongDesc", "The favored weapon of the Black Corsairs, this cutlass has been meticulously sharpened and the craftsmanship behind it is very high.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92178_ShortDesc", "A weapon oil that increases weapon damage temporarily")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92178_LongDesc", "Prepared by a secret process, known only to those slaves of the Giant-kings who toiled in the arena, oils such as these were used to subtly influence the outcomes of arena combat.\nThis oil, when coating a weapon, causes additional pain with every blow, until the coating has worn off.\nThe downside is that the oil is acidic and eats away at the weapon over time, rendering it brittle and much more likely to break.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92179_ShortDesc", "A weapon oil that increases the armor penetration of a weapon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92179_LongDesc", "Prepared by a secret process, known only to those slaves of the Giant-kings who toiled in the arena, oils such as these were used to subtly influence the outcomes of arena combat.\nThis oil, when coating a weapon, causes the weapon to slide toward weak points in the armor, allowing it to more easily penetrate the surface.\nThe downside is that the oil is acidic and eats away at the weapon over time, rendering it brittle and much more likely to break.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92180_ShortDesc", "A weapon oil that decreases the stamina cost of a weapon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92180_LongDesc", "Prepared by a secret process, known only to those slaves of the Giant-kings who toiled in the arena, oils such as these were used to subtly influence the outcomes of arena combat.\nThis oil, when coating a weapon, seems to ease the passage of the weapon through the air. Blades cut more easily, and maces seem to leap forward of their own volition.\nThe downside is that the oil is acidic and eats away at the weapon over time, rendering it brittle and much more likely to break.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92181_ShortDesc", "A weapon oil that increases the concussion damage of a weapon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92181_LongDesc", "Prepared by a secret process, known only to those slaves of the Giant-kings who toiled in the arena, oils such as these were used to subtly influence the outcomes of arena combat.\nThis oil, when coating a weapon, gives off a powerful, sweet odor that makes those who smell it feel lethargic. When used in battle, it is not certain whether the wounds inflicted, or just the odor are responsible for the additional concussive effect.\nThe downside is that the oil is acidic and eats away at the weapon over time, rendering it brittle and much more likely to break.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92182_ShortDesc", "A tool oil that enhances the effectiveness of harvesting")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92182_LongDesc", "Prepared by a secret process, known only to those slaves of the Giant-kings who toiled in the arena, oils such as these were used to subtly influence the outcomes of arena combat.\nThis oil was discarded when it appeared to have no significant use in combat, stacked in leaky barrels in a corner of the arena. Later, it was observed that the oil, when in contact with organic matter, seemed to expand and mimic the characteristics of simple inorganic and organic structures. The arena slaves began using on the tools while harvesting meat from the corpses of the fallen, and it created an abundance unheard of in the arena before.\nThe downside is that the oil is acidic and eats away at the weapon over time, rendering it brittle and much more likely to break.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92186_ShortDesc", "A set of armor joints made for maneuverability")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92186_LongDesc", "These armor joints will allow an increased range of movement when climbing.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92187_ShortDesc", "A set of reinforcing plates that can attached to increase the strength of armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92187_LongDesc", "Designed to protect in battle, it can be disastrous if armor shatters beneath a powerful blow. Wise warriors seek to shore up their weaknesses, often by reinforcing the weaker joints of their armor.\n\nAttaching these thick plates to any set of clothing will increase its armor value considerably.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92188_ShortDesc", "A set of tools that increase both damage and armor  penetration")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92188_LongDesc", "This set of tools contain various implements to enhance the damage as well as armor penetration of a weapon. Modifying a weapon in this fashion will greatly reduce the durability of the weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92189_ShortDesc", "A fitting for a weapon that allows for greater handling")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92189_LongDesc", "This weapon fitting increases the damage for quick and light attacks but does so by removing some of the weight behind the blows, reducing heavy damage as a trade-off.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92190_ShortDesc", "A reinforcement that can be used to make weapons and armor more durable")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92190_LongDesc", "A warrior relies on their strength, their skill and their weapon to carry them in battle. If any of these are broken in the clash of swords, it puts life and limb at risk.

This reinforcement can be used to find the flaws in a weapon or piece of armor and buttress them against the storm of battle.

This advanced reinforcement will increase the durability of a weapon or a piece of armor slightly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92191_ShortDesc", "A set of bulky armor plates to fit inside armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92191_LongDesc", "These armor plates fit snugly in or over armor pieces but increases the weight of such armors greatly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92192_ShortDesc", "A treatise explaining the usage of various weapon oils")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92192_LongDesc", "Spoken in a wavering, ancient voice, this memory note contains the ramblings of an ancient Giant-king on the various oils developed and used by the slaves of the arena.\nThough the Priestking gave him strict instructions never to reveal the nature of oils to others, the arena master took it upon himself to record the knowledge, in case it might be of use to others of his kind in the future.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92200_ShortDesc", "A helm worn by the Khari Overseers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92200_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The job of managing the slave legion fell to the overseers, a hard-hearted lot tasked with the messy business of motivating human chattle to serve, fight for, and often die in service of their masters. \n\nThis open-faced light helm offers moderate protection against blows - but shields the wearer from direct sunlight and hateful glances from the enslaved. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92201_ShortDesc", "Shoulder and upper-chest protection worn by the Khari Overseers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92201_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The job of managing the slave legion fell to the overseers, a hard-hearted lot tasked with the messy business of motivating human chattle to serve, fight for, and often die in service of their masters. \n\nIn hot, arid climates, the mantle offers a modicum of chest and shoulder protection without the enclosing the wearer -- like an extremely small poncho.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92202_ShortDesc", "Ornamental bracers worn by Khari Overseers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92202_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The job of managing the slave legion fell to the overseers, a hard-hearted lot tasked with the messy business of motivating human chattle to serve, fight for, and often die in service of their masters. \n\nThese largely decorative bracers offer only the slightest hint at actual protection, but look good doing it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92203_ShortDesc", "A leather skirt that protects the upper thighs of the Overseers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92203_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The job of managing the slave legion fell to the overseers, a hard-hearted lot tasked with the messy business of motivating human chattle to serve, fight for, and often die in service of their masters. \n\nThis knee-length leather skirt is designed to protect the upper thighs from attacks without impeding mobility.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92204_ShortDesc", "Sandals worn by the Khari Overseers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92204_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The job of managing the slave legion fell to the overseers, a hard-hearted lot tasked with the messy business of motivating human chattle to serve, fight for, and often die in service of their masters. \n\nThese sandals lace along the length of the calf, allowing the wearer freedom of movement while protecting the front of the leg. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92205_ShortDesc", "A light helmet designed to intimidate.")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92205_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The role of maintaining a steady supply to the Khari slave markets fell to the Raider crews, a villainous corps of black-souled reavers with a reputation for unmatched cruelty. 

Sightings of the snake-headed prows of the Khari Raider crews often meant mothers would slay their weak or enfeebled children rather than see them suffer at the hands of the pitiless slavers.  

This leather helm and mask combination provides moderate protection to the head, but are primarily designed to project fear and intimidation.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92206_ShortDesc", "A chestguard made in the style of the Khari")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92206_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The role of maintaining a steady supply to the Khari slave markets fell to the Raider crews, a villainous corps of black-souled reavers with a reputation for unmatched cruelty. 

Sightings of the snake-headed prows of the Khari Raider crews often meant mothers would slay their weak or enfeebled children rather than see them suffer at the hands of the pitiless slavers.  

The remarkable weave of this dark copper mail chestpiece offers excellent protection for the neck, shoulders and belly, without trapping heat. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92207_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Khari Raiders. ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92207_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The role of maintaining a steady supply to the Khari slave markets fell to the Raider crews, a villainous corps of black-souled reavers with a reputation for unmatched cruelty. 

Sightings of the snake-headed prows of the Khari Raider crews often meant mothers would slay their weak or enfeebled children rather than see them suffer at the hands of the pitiless slavers.  

These bracers protect the forearm and can be used to deflect superficial blows, thus keeping the wearer swinging and fighting just a little longer. ")

Sightings of the snake-headed prows of the Khari Raider crews often meant mothers would slay their weak or enfeebled children rather than see them suffer at the hands of the pitiless slavers.  

This knee-length mail skirt is designed to protect the upper thighs from attacks without impeding mobility. ")

These sandals lace along the length of the calf, allowing the wearer freedom of movement while protecting the front of the leg. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92210_ShortDesc", "A Helm worn by Khari soldiers in the field.")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92210_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world.  

While many of the slave legions were used as expendable fodder, those demonstrating exceptional dedication or performance in the field could earn a kind of freedom with promotion to the regular infantry ranks. Historians believe that a cadre of these 'free-men soldiers,' possibly even Lemurian exiles, were involved with sparking the rebellion that led to the eventual decline and dissolution of the Khari empire.  

Like the Khari Overseer and Raider headpieces, the Soldier's helm was designed for intimidation first and protection second. Still, the hardened segmented armour offers excellent defense against slashing and piercing attacks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92211_ShortDesc", "A mail chestpiece worn by Khari soldiers in the field.")
column4:

Historians believe that a cadre of these 'free-men soldiers,' possibly even Lemurian exiles, were involved with sparking the rebellion that led to the eventual decline and dissolution of the Khari empire.  

The centerpiece of the Khari soldier's kit is an intricately woven latticework of scale mail framed by a series of interlocking shoulder plates that offer the maximum protection without sacrificing mobility.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92215_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers crafted in the lost art of a dead civilization")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92215_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Its composition was something like copper, but much harder, and it was carved with hieroglyphics, like those found on the more ancient menhirs in southern Stygia.</> - The God in the Bowl

Historians link the rise and eventual fall of the Khari empire to its dominion over the slave trade. In fact, it's believed the Khari gained their reputation as master crafters through the careful theft and assimilation of knowledge held by those they enslaved.

When the inevitable occurred and slave turned against master, Khari survivors fled west to the desert where they encountered the last remaining vestiges of the serpent people. As devout worshippers of Set, the Khari venerated the serpent folk as living scions of their beloved reptile God and laid the foundations for the kingdom that would later be known as Stygia. What finally befell the Khari and their scaled patrons is lost to time.

Daggers are a weapon used with passion by the untrained and with a cold dispassion by the trained. Unseasoned warriors consider swords the superior weapon - until they come across a master, twin blades flashing as they dash and dart within the reach of their enemies and disembowel them. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92223_ShortDesc", "A mount for traversing the harsh Exiled Lands")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92223_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The women were traveling slowly, on foot and on the overloaded horses. The swift-footed Picts would run them down within a mile, unless - he took his position behind a tangle of fallen logs beside the trail. The road west of him was lighted by the burning cabin, and when the Picts came he saw them first - black furtive figures etched against the distant glare.</> - Beyond the Black River\n\nA properly bred horse can mean the difference between life and death. In the Exiled Lands, horses can be used as pack animals, mounts for combat or for quickly traversing the dangers of the harsh lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_899195_ShortDesc", "A potion that incites rage and strength")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_899195_LongDesc", "Drinking this potion will make the imbiber fly into a berserk frenzy, increasing damage and armor but  prevent healing. Once the effects of the potion wears off, the imbiber becomes fatigued.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_899196_ShortDesc", "Ancient desert elixir, drinking causes shivering under the hottest sun and burn the skin on cold winter nights.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_899196_LongDesc", "Created by mad sorcerers of Stygia this elixir allowed their armies to withstand the cruelest of hazards and would have paved a way to conquest of the northern lands was it not for the Aquilonian armies stopping them during the battle of Styx. All the trails revealing a true nature of magical concoctions ended there and recipe was never found.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_9000006_ShortDesc", "A pair of primitive stone-bladed knives")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_9000006_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Conan went with it, bruised, battered, invincible, hanging on like a bulldog to the hilt of his saber which he could not withdraw, tearing and ripping at the shuddering bulk with the poniard in his left hand, goring it to ribbons.</> - The Slithering Shadow

Sharpened stones serving as primitive daggers with limited ranged for fast, stabbing attacks.

Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Even the most primitive weapons can mean the difference between life and death for an Exile.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51469_ShortDesc", "Heavy, unwieldy hammer for repairing structures")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51469_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Khosatral Khel rose and lived and waxed mighty once more. It pleased him to restore the city as it was in the days before its fall.</> - The Devil in Iron

Crafted for utility, this hammer is an unwieldy tool when used for anything other than pounding on stone or wood.

It is inevitable that time, the elements, and the beasts of the Exiled Lands will take their toll on structures. With the repair hammer and the correct combination of materials, almost anything can be repaired with a few hefty swings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51471_ShortDesc", "An arrow formed from ivory ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51471_LongDesc", "Like cultures and customs, the value of ivory depends upon the kingdom where it is seen.

In the Hyborian kingdoms, where elephants and other creatures are rare, it is a tangible sign of both wealth and power. In the Black Kingdoms, it is common - few warriors exist in those lands who do not possess an ivory handled dagger or jewelry.

It is a great source of trade between the north and the south - indeed it could be said that ivory is the primary reason that merchants dare make the dangerous journey along the Black Coast to trade for it in Kush.

This ivory arrow, honed to perfection, is excellently balanced and will cause great damage.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51472_ShortDesc", "A bolt formed from ivory")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51472_LongDesc", "Like cultures and customs, the value of ivory depends upon the kingdom where it is seen.

This ivory bolt, honed to perfection, is excellently balanced and will cause great damage.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51473_ShortDesc", "Claws that unleash the rage of the beast")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51473_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A man from the Tauran couldn't mistake the mark of a panther's claws. No. It's a forest devil summoned by Zogar Sag to carry out his revenge.</> - Beyond the Black River

With these equipped, the world takes on a red tinge. The power of Jhebbal Sag surges and the beast takes control.

With these equipped, new combinations of moves unlock and a warrior becomes a feral beast in combat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51475_ShortDesc", "Stolen from the undead grasp of the Gate Guardian")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51475_LongDesc", "Crafted by the Giant Kings and put into the hands of one of the most trusted slaves in the employ of the Warmaker, this axe is marvellously crafted and has cleft untold heads in two. It is very easy to wield and as such, strikes with the weapon are very accurate.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51476_ShortDesc", "A massive hammer of black glass")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51476_LongDesc", "A sharp-edged, glassy stone. Not easily worked like iron or steel, obsidian can still be made into ridiculously brittle weapons.\n\nMauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51479_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword of black glass")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51479_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I pay my way with steel!' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun. 'By Crom, man, if you don't get under way, I'll drench this galley in the blood of its crew!'</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this sword is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.")

Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this sword is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51482_ShortDesc", "Short, sharp blades of black glass")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51482_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, these daggers are made of obsidian. They are brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.\n\nDaggers are a weapon used with passion by the untrained and with a cold dispassion by the trained. Unseasoned warriors consider swords the superior weapon - until they come across a master, twin blades flashing as they dash and dart within the reach of their enemies and disembowel them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51485_ShortDesc", "A mace of black glass")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51485_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The three soldiers-men-at-arms wearing the emblem of the royal guards-rushed at the king, and one felled the squire with a blow of a mace.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this mace is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes, bypassing the protection of their armor through sheer force.")
