column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51801_ShortDesc", "A blunt, brittle sword")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51801_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> In the old free days, all I needed was a sharp sword and a straight path to my enemies. </> - The Phoenix on the Sword

This sword, created by binding a pair of sharpened stones to a hardwood branch, is unwieldy and unbalanced. More akin to a club than an actual bladed weapon, it will nevertheless be a capable tool for those trained in its use.

In the ice-locked lands north of Vanaheim and Asgard, adventurers tell of a tribe of man-apes who speak in the fashion of men and fashion rough weapons from stone and ice.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51808_ShortDesc", "A weapon imitating the power of the Warmaker")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51808_LongDesc", "This weapon imitates the look and power of the Warmaker\'s blade. It might not be as powerful but it nevertheless instills fear in any opponent that faces the wrong end of it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51809_ShortDesc", "A weapon imitating the power of the Warmaker")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51809_LongDesc", "This weapon imitates the look and power of the Warmaker\'s hammer. It might not be as powerful but it nevertheless instills fear in any opponent that faces the wrong end of it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51810_ShortDesc", "A sickle-sword used by the Stygian nobility")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51810_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> It was prince Kutamun, naked but for a loincloth, his harness hacked away, his crested helmet dented, his limbs splashed with blood. With a terrible shout he hurled his broken hilt full into Conan's face, and leaping, seized the stallion's bridle.</> - Black Colossus

The favoured weapon of Stygian royalty, the khopesh is traditionally cast in bronze and hilted in pure ivory. With the development of stronger metals, the Stygian smiths began using iron and steel during their creation, and diluting out the bronze cast which made them pleasing to the nobility. 

Interestingly, this weapon has more in common with an axe than a sword and is best used for hacking and chopping rather than slicing and dicing.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51811_ShortDesc", "A serviceable broadsword of iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51811_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The subtle tongue, the sophist guile, they fail when the broadswords sing;</> - The Road of Kings

A double bladed straight sword, the broadsword is popular among warriors and mercenaries from the Hyborian kingdoms. Equally suited to thrusting and slashing, a good broadsword can cut through mail shirts and cleave limbs and necks.

It is the hilt of a broadsword that represents its origin. It is easy to indentify the basket-hilted swords of Zingara and the heavy crosspiece hilts of the Hyperboreans. This sword does not bear any markers of origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51812_ShortDesc", "A sickle-sword used by the Stygian nobility")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51812_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> It was prince Kutamun, naked but for a loincloth, his harness hacked away, his crested helmet dented, his limbs splashed with blood. With a terrible shout he hurled his broken hilt full into Conan's face, and leaping, seized the stallion's bridle.</> - Black Colossus

The favoured weapon of Stygian royalty, the khopesh is traditionally cast in bronze and hilted in pure ivory. With the development of stronger metals, the Stygian smiths began using iron and steel during their creation, and diluting out the bronze cast which made them pleasing to the nobility. 

Interestingly, this weapon has more in common with an axe than a sword and is best used for hacking and chopping rather than slicing and dicing.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51813_ShortDesc", "An ancient khopesh marked in strange runes")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51813_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> You shall go down the dark road to Acheron, which is the road of silence and the night. The dark empire, unreborn, shall remain a legend and a black memory.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This khopesh, made from an ancient design, seems to suck away the warmth and daylight. A relic of the past, the shape of it calls up shadow-haunted memories of ape-gods squatting on shattered altars.

It whispers ceaselessly to its bearer and slowly, inevitably, tears their sanity apart.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51814_ShortDesc", "An exceptional broadsword of iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51814_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The subtle tongue, the sophist guile, they fail when the broadswords sing;</> - The Road of Kings

A double bladed straight sword, the broadsword is popular among warriors and mercenaries from the Hyborian kingdoms. Equally suited to thrusting and slashing, a good broadsword can cut through mail shirts and cleave limbs and necks.

It is the hilt of a broadsword that represents its origin. It is easy to indentify the basket-hilted swords of Zingara and the heavy crosspiece hilts of the Hyperboreans.

Due to the exceptional craftsmanship of this weapon, it will do more damage and take longer to break than other weapons of this type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51815_ShortDesc", "A flawless broadsword of iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51815_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The subtle tongue, the sophist guile, they fail when the broadswords sing;</> - The Road of Kings

A double bladed straight sword, the broadsword is popular among warriors and mercenaries from the Hyborian kingdoms. Equally suited to thrusting and slashing, a good broadsword can cut through mail shirts and cleave limbs and necks.

It is the hilt of a broadsword that represents its origin. It is easy to indentify the basket-hilted swords of Zingara and the heavy crosspiece hilts of the Hyperboreans.

This weapon is truly flawless and will do a lot more damage and take longer to break than other weapons of this type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51816_ShortDesc", "A broadsword carved with the symbol of the phoenix")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51816_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And as he stood, bewildered at the strangeness of his dream, he realized that he was gripping his sword in his hand. And his hair prickled at the nape of his neck, for on the broad blade was carven a symbol- the outline of a phoenix.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

When the world was young, there was a great sage known as Epimetreus. Little is known of the shadowy past in which he fought with Set, the arch-demon, but it is known that for all the days of his life he strove against the worshippers, votaries and acolytes of the Old Serpent.

It is rumored that in times of need the ghost of Epimetreus flies on unseen wings to aid the kingdom of Aquilonia, and that the symbol of the phoenix belongs to the sage as much as it does to Mitra.

In any case, there is nothing to distinguish this sword from any other - save the glowing symbol of the phoenix carved into the blade.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51817_ShortDesc", "A Khopesh stamped with the symbol of the serpent")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51817_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The common men of Stygia were not allowed to wear swords, and the mantle was not voluminous enough to hide the Cimmerian's long blade, but Conan buckled to his hip a Ghanta knife, a weapon borne by the fierce desert men who dwelt to the south of the Stygians, a broad, heavy, slightly curved blade of fine steel, edged like a razor and long enough to dismember a man.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

It is forbidden in the kingdom of Stygia for the common man to bear a sword, but the khopesh, particularly one that has taken part in the bloody rituals of Set, is allowed.

This khopesh appears to be made of steel, yet it is tinted the bronze color that Stygian ceremonial garb requires. The symbol engraved on the blade is the symbol of Set, the sacred serpent. Blades such as these are passed among the priesthood and given to those who show particular fervor when participating in the rites of blood.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51818_ShortDesc", "A sickle-sword used by the Stygian nobility")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51818_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> It was prince Kutamun, naked but for a loincloth, his harness hacked away, his crested helmet dented, his limbs splashed with blood. With a terrible shout he hurled his broken hilt full into Conan's face, and leaping, seized the stallion's bridle.</> - Black Colossus

The favoured weapon of Stygian royalty, the khopesh is traditionally cast in bronze and hilted in pure ivory. With the development of stronger metals, the Stygian smiths began using iron and steel during their creation, and diluting out the bronze cast which made them pleasing to the nobility. 

Interestingly, this weapon has more in common with an axe than a sword and is best used for hacking and chopping rather than slicing and dicing.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51821_ShortDesc", "A curved sword with a single sharp edge")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51821_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> A man on a giant horse whirled, slashed and smote apparently at thin air, and from another direction swept a wild horde of riders, their curved swords flashing in the moonlight.</> - Drums in Tombalku

Straddling the line between the traditional khopesh of Stygia and broadsword favoured in the northern kingdoms, the falcata is forward curved blade with a single edge on the concave side.

The distinctive hooked hilt helps to prevent the weapon from jarring free of the hands during battle. There is much dispute about the origin of the weapon, considering its similarity to the Argossean kopis and the Stygian khopesh.  This falcata bears no marking which would betray its origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51822_ShortDesc", "A slashing weapon favoured by pirates")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51822_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> At this kind of fighting the freebooters of the sea were at their stoutest; their arrows and bolts tore holes in the charging horde, their cutlasses hewed the wild men from the palisades they strove to scale.</> - The Black Stranger

Favoured by sailors from the Western ocean to the Vilayet, the cutlass is a short, curved sword capable of hacking through ropes, canvas, wood, and flesh.

Forged of cheap iron, cutlasses are usually splotched with rust due to their time spent near salt water.  This cutlass does not bear any markers of origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51825_ShortDesc", "A weapon infused by a sliver of the power of the Warmaker")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51825_LongDesc", "This weapon was forged ages ago by one of the Giant King\'s smiths. It vibrates in anticipation for the coming slaughter. The very act of holding it requires all the willpower you can muster and only the most steadfast warriors can resist to succumb to the dark powers infused into this blade. Unworthy wielders of this weapon will not be able to wield this weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51831_ShortDesc", "A common, thin bladed, double-edged sword")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51831_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> They stopped short. Conan faced them, not a naked man roused mazed and unarmed out of deep sleep to be butchered like a sheep, but a barbarian wide-awake and at bay, partly armored, and with his long sword in his hand.</>
The Phoenix on the Sword

Longsword has become a catch-all phrase for the mongrel swords of a thousand different makes that don't align easily with one simple classification.
The only description of a longsword that seems to be agreed upon is that they are double-bladed and straight. Beyond that they vary wildly from grooved blades to smooth blades, long hilts to short hilts, one-handed and two-handed variations.
This example is plain, straight and intended to be wielded in a single hand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51832_ShortDesc", "A razor sharp tool for scraping hides")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51832_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">But a bat has flown over the Mountains of the Dead and drawn your image in blood on the white tiger\'s hide that hangs before the long hut where sleep the Four Brothers of the Night.</> - Beyond the Black River\n\nBefore preparation, hides must be scraped to remove excess fibres and clots of skin. The best hide scrapers are sharp, easy to weild and leave a smooth line of transition so that it is easy to see which part of the hide still requires treatment.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51833_ShortDesc", "A primitive axe, shaped by crude materials and bone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51833_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">With an awful shriek the witch sank down, writhing in convulsions, grasping at the naked blade as it was withdrawn, smoking and dripping.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nBone is a brittle substance that breaks easily under even a small amount of force. Anything made of bone will fall apart quickly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51834_ShortDesc", "A shield made from old tusks")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51834_LongDesc", "Made from tusks as opposed to bone, this shield is stronger than it\'s more basic cousin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51841_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel sword of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51841_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Stand aside, girl,' he mumbled. 'Now is the feasting of swords.'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk
Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the blade of this broadsword, baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Swords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51844_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel axe of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51844_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He did not wonder at the strangeness of it all, not even when two gigantic figures rose up to bar his way. The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

Shaped of steel and marked with the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan, this battle-axe is sharp, durable and capable of inflicting vicious wounds.

Battle-axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes.

Cimmerian clans often engage in violent local conflict and the battle-axe is a preferred weapon for breaching the wood-walled settlements and laying waste to the rival clansmen within.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51850_ShortDesc", "A cudgel of Darfari make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51850_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He wondered how many poor devils had been bludgeoned in their sleep and dragged out of that room and down the road that ran through the shadowed palm groves to the roasting pit.</>  - Shadows in Zamboula

This sinister weapon is made of the bones of a human arm bound to a large fragment of stone. 

Bone is a brittle substance that breaks easily under even a small amount of force. Anything made of bone will fall apart quickly.")
